12 /** \class TClass
13 TClass instances represent classes, structs and namespaces in the ROOT type system.
14 
15 TClass instances are created starting from different sources of information:
16 1. TStreamerInfo instances saved in a ROOT file which is opened. This is called in jargon an *emulated TClass*.
17 2. From TProtoClass instances saved in a ROOT pcm file created by the dictionary generator and the dictionary itself.
18 3. From a lookup in the AST built by cling.
19 
20 If a TClass instance is built through the mechanisms 1. and 2., it does not contain information about methods of the
21 class/struct/namespace it represents. Conversely, if built through 3. or 1., it does not carry the information which is necessary
22 to ROOT to perform I/O of instances of the class/struct it represents.
23 The mechanisms 1., 2. and 3. are not mutually exclusive: it can happen that during the execution of the program, all
24 the three are triggered, modifying the state of the TClass instance.
25 
26 In order to retrieve a TClass instance from the type system, a query can be executed as follows through the static
27 TClass::GetClass method:
28 ```{.cpp}
29 auto myClassTClass_0 = TClass::GetClass("myClass");
30 auto myClassTClass_1 = TClass::GetClass<myClass>();
31 auto myClassTClass_2 = TClass::GetClass(myClassTypeInfo);
32 ```
33 
34 The name of classes is crucial for ROOT. A careful procedure of *name normalization* is carried out for
35 each and every class. A *normalized name* is a valid C++ class name.
36 In order to access the name of a class within the ROOT type system, the method TClass::GetName() can be used.
37 */
38

155 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
156 /// Extract this part of the name
157 /// 1. Templates ns::ns2::,,,::THISPART<...
158 /// 2. Namespaces,classes ns::ns2::,,,::THISPART
159 
160 void TClass::TDeclNameRegistry::AddQualifiedName(const char *name)
161 {
162  // Sanity check
163  auto strLen = strlen(name);
164  if (strLen == 0) return;
165  // find <. If none, put end of string
166  const char* endCharPtr = strchr(name, '<');
167  endCharPtr = !endCharPtr ? &name[strLen] : endCharPtr;
168  // find last : before the <. If not found, put begin of string
169  const char* beginCharPtr = endCharPtr;
170  while (beginCharPtr!=name){
171  if (*beginCharPtr==':'){
172  beginCharPtr++;
173  break;
174  }
175  beginCharPtr--;
176  }
177  beginCharPtr = beginCharPtr!=endCharPtr ? beginCharPtr : name;
178  std::string s(beginCharPtr, endCharPtr);
179  if (fVerbLevel>1)
180  printf("TDeclNameRegistry::AddQualifiedName Adding key %s for class/namespace %s\n", s.c_str(), name);
181  ROOT::Internal::TSpinLockGuard slg(fSpinLock);
182  fClassNamesSet.insert(s);
183 }
184 
185 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
186 
187 Bool_t TClass::TDeclNameRegistry::HasDeclName(const char *name) const
188 {
189  Bool_t found = false;
190  {
191  ROOT::Internal::TSpinLockGuard slg(fSpinLock);
192  found = fClassNamesSet.find(name) != fClassNamesSet.end();
193  }
194  return found;
195 }

205  printf(" - %s\n", key.c_str());
206  }

236 struct ObjRepoValue {

242 static TVirtualMutex* gOVRMutex = 0;
243 typedef std::multimap<void*, ObjRepoValue> RepoCont_t;
244 static RepoCont_t gObjectVersionRepository;
245 
246 static void RegisterAddressInRepository(const char * /*where*/, void *location, const TClass *what)
247 {
248  // Register the object for special handling in the destructor.
249 
250  Version_t version = what->GetClassVersion();
251 // if (!gObjectVersionRepository.count(location)) {
252 // Info(where, "Registering address %p of class '%s' version %d", location, what->GetName(), version);
253 // } else {
254 // Warning(where, "Registering address %p again of class '%s' version %d", location, what->GetName(), version);
255 // }
256  {
257  R__LOCKGUARD2(gOVRMutex);
258  gObjectVersionRepository.insert(RepoCont_t::value_type(location, RepoCont_t::mapped_type(what,version)));
259  }
260 #if 0
261  // This code could be used to prevent an address to be registered twice.
262  std::pair<RepoCont_t::iterator, Bool_t> tmp = gObjectVersionRepository.insert(RepoCont_t::value_type>(location, RepoCont_t::mapped_type(what,version)));
263  if (!tmp.second) {
264  Warning(where, "Reregistering an object of class '%s' version %d at address %p", what->GetName(), version, p);
265  gObjectVersionRepository.erase(tmp.first);
266  tmp = gObjectVersionRepository.insert(RepoCont_t::value_type>(location, RepoCont_t::mapped_type(what,version)));
267  if (!tmp.second) {
268  Warning(where, "Failed to reregister an object of class '%s' version %d at address %p", what->GetName(), version, location);
269  }
270  }
271 #endif
272 }
273 
274 static void UnregisterAddressInRepository(const char * /*where*/, void *location, const TClass *what)
275 {
276  // Remove an address from the repository of address/object.
277 
278  R__LOCKGUARD2(gOVRMutex);
279  RepoCont_t::iterator cur = gObjectVersionRepository.find(location);
280  for (; cur != gObjectVersionRepository.end();) {
281  RepoCont_t::iterator tmp = cur++;
282  if ((tmp->first == location) && (tmp->second.fVersion == what->GetClassVersion())) {
283  // -- We still have an address, version match.
284  // Info(where, "Unregistering address %p of class '%s' version %d", location, what->GetName(), what->GetClassVersion());
285  gObjectVersionRepository.erase(tmp);
286  } else {
287  // -- No address, version match, we've reached the end.
288  break;
289  }
290  }
291 }
292 
293 static void MoveAddressInRepository(const char * /*where*/, void *oldadd, void *newadd, const TClass *what)
294 {
295  // Register in the repository that an object has moved.
296 
297  // Move not only the object itself but also any base classes or sub-objects.
298  size_t objsize = what->Size();
299  long delta = (char*)newadd - (char*)oldadd;
300  R__LOCKGUARD2(gOVRMutex);
301  RepoCont_t::iterator cur = gObjectVersionRepository.find(oldadd);
302  for (; cur != gObjectVersionRepository.end();) {
303  RepoCont_t::iterator tmp = cur++;
304  if (oldadd <= tmp->first && tmp->first < ( ((char*)oldadd) + objsize) ) {
305  // The location is within the object, let's move it.
306 
307  gObjectVersionRepository.insert(RepoCont_t::value_type(((char*)tmp->first)+delta, RepoCont_t::mapped_type(tmp->second.fClass,tmp->second.fVersion)));
308  gObjectVersionRepository.erase(tmp);
309 
310  } else {
311  // -- No address, version match, we've reached the end.
312  break;
313  }
314  }
315 }

319 namespace ROOT {
320 #define R__USE_STD_MAP
321  class TMapTypeToTClass {
322 #if defined R__USE_STD_MAP
323  // This wrapper class allow to avoid putting #include <map> in the
324  // TROOT.h header file.
325  public:
326  typedef std::map<std::string,TClass*> IdMap_t;
327  typedef IdMap_t::key_type key_type;
328  typedef IdMap_t::const_iterator const_iterator;
329  typedef IdMap_t::size_type size_type;
330 #ifdef R__WIN32
331  // Window's std::map does NOT defined mapped_type
332  typedef TClass* mapped_type;
333 #else
334  typedef IdMap_t::mapped_type mapped_type;
335 #endif
336 
337  private:
338  IdMap_t fMap;
339 
340  public:
341  void Add(const key_type &key, mapped_type &obj)
342  {
343  // Add the <key,obj> pair to the map.
344  fMap[key] = obj;
345  }
346  mapped_type Find(const key_type &key) const
347  {
348  // Find the type corresponding to the key.
349  IdMap_t::const_iterator iter = fMap.find(key);
350  mapped_type cl = 0;
351  if (iter != fMap.end()) cl = iter->second;
352  return cl;
353  }
354  void Remove(const key_type &key) {
355  // Remove the type corresponding to the key.
356  fMap.erase(key);
357  }
358 #else
359  private:
360  TMap fMap;
361 
362  public:
363 #ifdef R__COMPLETE_MEM_TERMINATION
364  TMapTypeToTClass() {
365  TIter next(&fMap);
366  TObjString *key;
367  while((key = (TObjString*)next())) {
368  delete key;
369  }
370  }
371 #endif
372  void Add(const char *key, TClass *&obj) {
373  TObjString *realkey = new TObjString(key);
374  fMap.Add(realkey, obj);
375  }
376  TClass* Find(const char *key) const {
377  const TPair *a = (const TPair *)fMap.FindObject(key);
378  if (a) return (TClass*) a->Value();
379  return 0;
380  }
381  void Remove(const char *key) {
382  TObjString realkey(key);
383  TObject *actual = fMap.Remove(&realkey);
384  delete actual;
385  }
386 #endif
387  };

389  class TMapDeclIdToTClass {
390  // Wrapper class for the multimap of DeclId_t and TClass.
391  public:
392  typedef multimap<TDictionary::DeclId_t, TClass*> DeclIdMap_t;
393  typedef DeclIdMap_t::key_type key_type;
394  typedef DeclIdMap_t::mapped_type mapped_type;
395  typedef DeclIdMap_t::const_iterator const_iterator;
396  typedef std::pair <const_iterator, const_iterator> equal_range;
397  typedef DeclIdMap_t::size_type size_type;
398 
399  private:
400  DeclIdMap_t fMap;
401 
402  public:
403  void Add(const key_type &key, mapped_type obj)
404  {
405  // Add the <key,obj> pair to the map.
406  std::pair<const key_type, mapped_type> pair = make_pair(key, obj);
407  fMap.insert(pair);
408  }
409  size_type CountElementsWithKey(const key_type &key)
410  {
411  return fMap.count(key);
412  }
413  equal_range Find(const key_type &key) const
414  {
415  // Find the type corresponding to the key.
416  return fMap.equal_range(key);
417  }
418  void Remove(const key_type &key) {
419  // Remove the type corresponding to the key.
420  fMap.erase(key);
421  }
422  };
423 }

447 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
448 /// static: Add a class to the list and map of classes.
449 
450 void TClass::AddClass(TClass *cl)
451 {
452  if (!cl) return;
453 
454  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
455  gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->Add(cl);
456  if (cl->GetTypeInfo()) {
457  GetIdMap()->Add(cl->GetTypeInfo()->name(),cl);
458  }
459  if (cl->fClassInfo) {
460  GetDeclIdMap()->Add((void*)(cl->fClassInfo), cl);
461  }
462 }
463 
464 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
465 /// static: Add a TClass* to the map of classes.
466 
467 void TClass::AddClassToDeclIdMap(TDictionary::DeclId_t id, TClass* cl)
468 {
469  if (!cl || !id) return;
470  GetDeclIdMap()->Add(id, cl);
471 }
472 
473 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
474 /// static: Remove a class from the list and map of classes
475 
476 void TClass::RemoveClass(TClass *oldcl)
477 {
478  if (!oldcl) return;
479 
480  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
481  gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->Remove(oldcl);
482  if (oldcl->GetTypeInfo()) {
483  GetIdMap()->Remove(oldcl->GetTypeInfo()->name());
484  }
485  if (oldcl->fClassInfo) {
486  //GetDeclIdMap()->Remove((void*)(oldcl->fClassInfo));
487  }
488 }

490 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
491 
492 void TClass::RemoveClassDeclId(TDictionary::DeclId_t id)
493 {
494  if (!id) return;
495  GetDeclIdMap()->Remove(id);
496 }

519 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
520 /// Print value of member mname.
521 ///
522 /// This method is called by the ShowMembers() method for each
523 /// data member when object.Dump() is invoked.
524 ///
525 /// - cl is the pointer to the current class
526 /// - pname is the parent name (in case of composed objects)
527 /// - mname is the data member name
528 /// - add is the data member address
529 
530 void TDumpMembers::Inspect(TClass *cl, const char *pname, const char *mname, const void *add, Bool_t /* isTransient */)
531 {
532  const Int_t kvalue = 30;
533 #ifdef R__B64
534  const Int_t ktitle = 50;
535 #else
536  const Int_t ktitle = 42;
537 #endif
538  const Int_t kline = 1024;
539  Int_t cdate = 0;
540  Int_t ctime = 0;
541  UInt_t *cdatime = 0;
542  char line[kline];
543 
544  TDataType *membertype;
545  EDataType memberDataType = kNoType_t;
546  const char *memberName;
547  const char *memberFullTypeName;
548  const char *memberTitle;
549  Bool_t isapointer;
550  Bool_t isbasic;
551 
552  if (TDataMember *member = cl->GetDataMember(mname)) {
553  if (member->GetDataType()) {
554  memberDataType = (EDataType)member->GetDataType()->GetType();
555  }
556  memberName = member->GetName();
557  memberFullTypeName = member->GetFullTypeName();
558  memberTitle = member->GetTitle();
559  isapointer = member->IsaPointer();
560  isbasic = member->IsBasic();
561  membertype = member->GetDataType();
562  } else if (!cl->IsLoaded()) {
563  // The class is not loaded, hence it is 'emulated' and the main source of
564  // information is the StreamerInfo.
565  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = cl->GetStreamerInfo();
566  if (!info) return;
567  const char *cursor = mname;
568  while ( (*cursor)=='*' ) ++cursor;
569  TString elname( cursor );
570  Ssiz_t pos = elname.Index("[");
571  if ( pos != kNPOS ) {
572  elname.Remove( pos );
573  }
574  TStreamerElement *element = (TStreamerElement*)info->GetElements()->FindObject(elname.Data());
575  if (!element) return;
576  memberFullTypeName = element->GetTypeName();
577 
578  memberDataType = (EDataType)element->GetType();
579 
580  memberName = element->GetName();
581  memberTitle = element->GetTitle();
582  isapointer = element->IsaPointer() || element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kCharStar;
583  membertype = gROOT->GetType(memberFullTypeName);
584 
585  isbasic = membertype !=0;
586  } else {
587  return;
588  }
589 
590 
591  Bool_t isdate = kFALSE;
592  if (strcmp(memberName,"fDatime") == 0 && memberDataType == kUInt_t) {
593  isdate = kTRUE;
594  }
595  Bool_t isbits = kFALSE;
596  if (strcmp(memberName,"fBits") == 0 && memberDataType == kUInt_t) {
597  isbits = kTRUE;
598  }
599  TClass * dataClass = TClass::GetClass(memberFullTypeName);
600  Bool_t isTString = (dataClass == TString::Class());
601  static TClassRef stdClass("std::string");
602  Bool_t isStdString = (dataClass == stdClass);
603 
604  Int_t i;
605  for (i = 0;i < kline; i++) line[i] = ' ';
606  line[kline-1] = 0;
607  snprintf(line,kline,"%s%s ",pname,mname);
608  i = strlen(line); line[i] = ' ';
609 
610  // Encode data value or pointer value
611  char *pointer = (char*)add;
612  char **ppointer = (char**)(pointer);
613 
614  if (isapointer) {
615  char **p3pointer = (char**)(*ppointer);
616  if (!p3pointer)
617  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"->0");
618  else if (!isbasic) {
619  if (!fNoAddr) {
620  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"->%lx ", (Long_t)p3pointer);
621  }
622  } else if (membertype) {
623  if (!strcmp(membertype->GetTypeName(), "char")) {
624  i = strlen(*ppointer);
625  if (kvalue+i > kline) i=kline-1-kvalue;
626  Bool_t isPrintable = kTRUE;
627  for (Int_t j = 0; j < i; j++) {
628  if (!std::isprint((*ppointer)[j])) {
629  isPrintable = kFALSE;
630  break;
631  }
632  }
633  if (isPrintable) {
634  strncpy(line + kvalue, *ppointer, i);
635  line[kvalue+i] = 0;
636  } else {
637  line[kvalue] = 0;
638  }
639  } else {
640  strncpy(&line[kvalue], membertype->AsString(p3pointer), TMath::Min(kline-1-kvalue,(int)strlen(membertype->AsString(p3pointer))));
641  }
642  } else if (!strcmp(memberFullTypeName, "char*") ||
643  !strcmp(memberFullTypeName, "const char*")) {
644  i = strlen(*ppointer);
645  if (kvalue+i >= kline) i=kline-1-kvalue;
646  Bool_t isPrintable = kTRUE;
647  for (Int_t j = 0; j < i; j++) {
648  if (!std::isprint((*ppointer)[j])) {
649  isPrintable = kFALSE;
650  break;
651  }
652  }
653  if (isPrintable) {
654  strncpy(line + kvalue, *ppointer, std::min( i, kline - kvalue));
655  line[kvalue+i] = 0;
656  } else {
657  line[kvalue] = 0;
658  }
659  } else {
660  if (!fNoAddr) {
661  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"->%lx ", (Long_t)p3pointer);
662  }
663  }
664  } else if (membertype) {
665  if (isdate) {
666  cdatime = (UInt_t*)pointer;
667  TDatime::GetDateTime(cdatime[0],cdate,ctime);
668  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"%d/%d",cdate,ctime);
669  } else if (isbits) {
670  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"0x%08x", *(UInt_t*)pointer);
671  } else {
672  strncpy(&line[kvalue], membertype->AsString(pointer), TMath::Min(kline-1-kvalue,(int)strlen(membertype->AsString(pointer))));
673  }
674  } else {
675  if (isStdString) {
676  std::string *str = (std::string*)pointer;
677  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"%s",str->c_str());
678  } else if (isTString) {
679  TString *str = (TString*)pointer;
680  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"%s",str->Data());
681  } else {
682  if (!fNoAddr) {
683  snprintf(&line[kvalue],kline-kvalue,"->%lx ", (Long_t)pointer);
684  }
685  }
686  }
687  // Encode data member title
688  if (isdate == kFALSE && strcmp(memberFullTypeName, "char*") && strcmp(memberFullTypeName, "const char*")) {
689  i = strlen(&line[0]); line[i] = ' ';
690  assert(250 > ktitle);
691  strlcpy(&line[ktitle],memberTitle,250-ktitle+1); // strlcpy copy 'size-1' characters.
692  }
693  Printf("%s", line);
694 }

710 class TBuildRealData : public TMemberInspector {
711 
712 private:
713  void *fRealDataObject;
714  TClass *fRealDataClass;
715 
716 public:
717  TBuildRealData(void *obj, TClass *cl) {
718  // Main constructor.
719  fRealDataObject = obj;
720  fRealDataClass = cl;
721  }
722  using TMemberInspector::Inspect;
723  void Inspect(TClass *cl, const char *parent, const char *name, const void *addr, Bool_t isTransient);
724 
725 };
726 
727 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
728 /// This method is called from ShowMembers() via BuildRealdata().
729 
730 void TBuildRealData::Inspect(TClass* cl, const char* pname, const char* mname, const void* add, Bool_t isTransient)
731 {
732  TDataMember* dm = cl->GetDataMember(mname);
733  if (!dm) {
734  return;
735  }
736 
737  Bool_t isTransientMember = kFALSE;
738 
739  if (!dm->IsPersistent()) {
740  // For the DataModelEvolution we need access to the transient member.
741  // so we now record them in the list of RealData.
742  isTransientMember = kTRUE;
743  isTransient = kTRUE;
744  }
745 
746  TString rname( pname );
747  // Take into account cases like TPaveStats->TPaveText->TPave->TBox.
748  // Check that member is in a derived class or an object in the class.
749  if (cl != fRealDataClass) {
750  if (!fRealDataClass->InheritsFrom(cl)) {
751  Ssiz_t dot = rname.Index('.');
752  if (dot == kNPOS) {
753  return;
754  }
755  rname[dot] = '\0';
756  if (!fRealDataClass->GetDataMember(rname)) {
757  //could be a data member in a base class like in this example
758  // class Event : public Data {
759  // class Data : public TObject {
760  // EventHeader fEvtHdr;
761  // class EventHeader {
762  // Int_t fEvtNum;
763  // Int_t fRun;
764  // Int_t fDate;
765  // EventVertex fVertex;
766  // class EventVertex {
767  // EventTime fTime;
768  // class EventTime {
769  // Int_t fSec;
770  // Int_t fNanoSec;
771  if (!fRealDataClass->GetBaseDataMember(rname)) {
772  return;
773  }
774  }
775  rname[dot] = '.';
776  }
777  }
778 
779  Long_t offset = Long_t(((Long_t) add) - ((Long_t) fRealDataObject));
780 
781  if (TClassEdit::IsStdArray(dm->GetTypeName())){ // We tackle the std array case
782  TString rdName;
783  TRealData::GetName(rdName,dm);
784  rname += rdName;
785  TRealData* rd = new TRealData(rname.Data(), offset, dm);
786  fRealDataClass->GetListOfRealData()->Add(rd);
787  return;
788  }
789 
790  rname += mname;
791 
792  if (dm->IsaPointer()) {
793  // Data member is a pointer.
794  TRealData* rd = new TRealData(rname, offset, dm);
795  if (isTransientMember) { rd->SetBit(TRealData::kTransient); };
796  fRealDataClass->GetListOfRealData()->Add(rd);
797  } else {
798  // Data Member is a basic data type.
799  TRealData* rd = new TRealData(rname, offset, dm);
800  if (isTransientMember) { rd->SetBit(TRealData::kTransient); };
801  if (!dm->IsBasic()) {
802  rd->SetIsObject(kTRUE);
803 
804  // Make sure that BuildReadData is called for any abstract
805  // bases classes involved in this object, i.e for all the
806  // classes composing this object (base classes, type of
807  // embedded object and same for their data members).
808  //
809  TClass* dmclass = TClass::GetClass(dm->GetTypeName(), kTRUE, isTransient);
810  if (!dmclass) {
811  dmclass = TClass::GetClass(dm->GetTrueTypeName(), kTRUE, isTransient);
812  }
813  if (dmclass) {
814  if ((dmclass != cl) && !dm->IsaPointer()) {
815  if (dmclass->GetCollectionProxy()) {
816  TClass* valcl = dmclass->GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass();
817  // We create the real data for the content of the collection to help the case
818  // of split branches in a TTree (where the node for the data member itself
819  // might have been elided). However, in some cases, like transient members
820  // and/or classes, the content might not be create-able. An example is the
821  // case of a map<A,B> where either A or B does not have default constructor
822  // and thus the compilation of the default constructor for pair<A,B> will
823  // fail (noisily) [This could also apply to any template instance, where it
824  // might have a default constructor definition that can not be compiled due
825  // to the template parameter]
826  if (valcl) {
827  Bool_t wantBuild = kTRUE;
828  if (valcl->Property() & kIsAbstract) wantBuild = kFALSE;
829  if ( (isTransient)
830  && (dmclass->GetCollectionProxy()->GetProperties() & TVirtualCollectionProxy::kIsEmulated)
831  && (!valcl->IsLoaded()) ) {
832  // Case where the collection dictionary was not requested and
833  // the content's dictionary was also not requested.
834  // [This is a super set of what we need, but we can't really detect it :(]
835  wantBuild = kFALSE;
836  }
837 
838  if (wantBuild) valcl->BuildRealData(0, isTransient);
839  }
840  } else {
841  void* addrForRecursion = 0;
842  if (GetObjectValidity() == kValidObjectGiven)
843  addrForRecursion = const_cast<void*>(add);
844 
845  dmclass->BuildRealData(addrForRecursion, isTransient);
846  }
847  }
848  }
849  }
850  fRealDataClass->GetListOfRealData()->Add(rd);
851  }
852 }

855 //______________________________________________________________________________
856 //______________________________________________________________________________

858 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
859 
860 class TAutoInspector : public TMemberInspector {
861 public:
862  Int_t fCount;
863  TBrowser *fBrowser;
864 
865  TAutoInspector(TBrowser *b) {
866  // main constructor.
867  fBrowser = b; fCount = 0; }
868  virtual ~TAutoInspector() { }
869  using TMemberInspector::Inspect;
870  virtual void Inspect(TClass *cl, const char *parent, const char *name, const void *addr, Bool_t isTransient);
871  virtual Bool_t IsTreatingNonAccessibleTypes() {return kFALSE;}
872 };
873 
874 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
875 /// This method is called from ShowMembers() via AutoBrowse().
876 
877 void TAutoInspector::Inspect(TClass *cl, const char *tit, const char *name,
878  const void *addr, Bool_t /* isTransient */)
879 {
880  if(tit && strchr(tit,'.')) return ;
881  if (fCount && !fBrowser) return;
882 
883  TString ts;
884 
885  if (!cl) return;
886  //if (*(cl->GetName()) == 'T') return;
887  if (*name == '*') name++;
888  int ln = strcspn(name,"[ ");
889  TString iname(name,ln);
890 
891  ClassInfo_t *classInfo = cl->GetClassInfo();
892  if (!classInfo) return;
893 
894  // Browse data members
895  DataMemberInfo_t *m = gCling->DataMemberInfo_Factory(classInfo);
896  TString mname;
897 
898  int found=0;
899  while (gCling->DataMemberInfo_Next(m)) { // MemberLoop
900  mname = gCling->DataMemberInfo_Name(m);
901  mname.ReplaceAll("*","");
902  if ((found = (iname==mname))) break;
903  }
904  assert(found);
905 
906  // we skip: non static members and non objects
907  // - the member G__virtualinfo inserted by the CINT RTTI system
908 
909  //Long_t prop = m.Property() | m.Type()->Property();
910  Long_t prop = gCling->DataMemberInfo_Property(m) | gCling->DataMemberInfo_TypeProperty(m);
911  if (prop & kIsStatic) return;
912  if (prop & kIsFundamental) return;
913  if (prop & kIsEnum) return;
914  if (mname == "G__virtualinfo") return;
915 
916  int size = sizeof(void*);
917 
918  int nmax = 1;
919  if (prop & kIsArray) {
920  for (int dim = 0; dim < gCling->DataMemberInfo_ArrayDim(m); dim++) nmax *= gCling->DataMemberInfo_MaxIndex(m,dim);
921  }
922 
923  std::string clmName(TClassEdit::ShortType(gCling->DataMemberInfo_TypeName(m),
924  TClassEdit::kDropTrailStar) );
925  TClass * clm = TClass::GetClass(clmName.c_str());
926  R__ASSERT(clm);
927  if (!(prop & kIsPointer)) {
928  size = clm->Size();
929  if (size==0) size = gCling->DataMemberInfo_TypeSize(m);
930  }
931 
932 
933  gCling->DataMemberInfo_Delete(m);
934  TVirtualCollectionProxy *proxy = clm->GetCollectionProxy();
935 
936  for(int i=0; i<nmax; i++) {
937 
938  char *ptr = (char*)addr + i*size;
939 
940  void *obj = (prop & kIsPointer) ? *((void**)ptr) : (TObject*)ptr;
941 
942  if (!obj) continue;
943 
944  fCount++;
945  if (!fBrowser) return;
946 
947  TString bwname;
948  TClass *actualClass = clm->GetActualClass(obj);
949  if (clm->IsTObject()) {
950  TObject *tobj = (TObject*)clm->DynamicCast(TObject::Class(),obj);
951  bwname = tobj->GetName();
952  } else {
953  bwname = actualClass->GetName();
954  bwname += "::";
955  bwname += mname;
956  }
957 
958  if (!clm->IsTObject() ||
959  bwname.Length()==0 ||
960  strcmp(bwname.Data(),actualClass->GetName())==0) {
961  bwname = name;
962  int l = strcspn(bwname.Data(),"[ ");
963  if (l<bwname.Length() && bwname[l]=='[') {
964  char cbuf[13]; snprintf(cbuf,13,"[%02d]",i);
965  ts.Replace(0,999,bwname,l);
966  ts += cbuf;
967  bwname = (const char*)ts;
968  }
969  }
970 
971  if (proxy==0) {
972 
973  fBrowser->Add(obj,clm,bwname);
974 
975  } else {
976  TClass *valueCl = proxy->GetValueClass();
977 
978  if (valueCl==0) {
979 
980  fBrowser->Add( obj, clm, bwname );
981 
982  } else {
983  TVirtualCollectionProxy::TPushPop env(proxy, obj);
984  TClass *actualCl = 0;
985 
986  int sz = proxy->Size();
987 
988  char fmt[] = {"#%09d"};
989  fmt[3] = '0'+(int)log10(double(sz))+1;
990  char buf[20];
991  for (int ii=0;ii<sz;ii++) {
992  void *p = proxy->At(ii);
993 
994  if (proxy->HasPointers()) {
995  p = *((void**)p);
996  if(!p) continue;
997  actualCl = valueCl->GetActualClass(p);
998  p = actualCl->DynamicCast(valueCl,p,0);
999  }
1000  fCount++;
1001  snprintf(buf,20,fmt,ii);
1002  ts = bwname;
1003  ts += buf;
1004  fBrowser->Add( p, actualCl, ts );
1005  }
1006  }
1007  }
1008  }
1009 }

1135  fBase(0), fData(0), fEnums(0), fFuncTemplate(0), fMethod(0), fAllPubData(0),

1138  fInstanceCount(0), fOnHeap(0),
1139  fCheckSum(0), fCollectionProxy(0), fClassVersion(0), fClassInfo(0),
1140  fTypeInfo(0), fShowMembers(0),
1141  fStreamer(0), fIsA(0), fGlobalIsA(0), fIsAMethod(0),
1142  fMerge(0), fResetAfterMerge(0), fNew(0), fNewArray(0), fDelete(0), fDeleteArray(0),
1143  fDestructor(0), fDirAutoAdd(0), fStreamerFunc(0), fConvStreamerFunc(0), fSizeof(-1),
1144  fCanSplit(-1), fProperty(0), fClassProperty(0), fHasRootPcmInfo(kFALSE), fCanLoadClassInfo(kFALSE),

1156  }

1159  ::Fatal("TClass::TClass",
1160  "A TClass entry cannot be initialized in a state different from kForwardDeclared or kEmulated.");

1187  fDestructor(0), fDirAutoAdd(0), fStreamerFunc(0), fConvStreamerFunc(0), fSizeof(-1),
1188  fCanSplit(-1), fProperty(0), fClassProperty(0), fHasRootPcmInfo(kFALSE), fCanLoadClassInfo(kFALSE),
1189  fIsOffsetStreamerSet(kFALSE), fVersionUsed(kFALSE), fRuntimeProperties(0), fOffsetStreamer(0), fStreamerType(TClass::kDefault),
1190  fState(kNoInfo),
1191  fCurrentInfo(0), fLastReadInfo(0), fRefProxy(0),
1192  fSchemaRules(0), fStreamerImpl(&TClass::StreamerDefault)
1193 {
1194  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
1195 
1196  if (!gROOT)
1197  ::Fatal("TClass::TClass", "ROOT system not initialized");
1198 
1199  fDeclFileLine = -2; // -2 for standalone TClass (checked in dtor)
1200 
1201  SetBit(kLoading);
1202  if (!gInterpreter)
1203  ::Fatal("TClass::TClass", "gInterpreter not initialized");
1204 
1205  if (!classInfo || !gInterpreter->ClassInfo_IsValid(classInfo)) {
1206  MakeZombie();
1207  fState = kNoInfo;
1208  } else {
1209  fName = gInterpreter->ClassInfo_FullName(classInfo);
1210 
1211  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
1212  Init(fName, cversion, 0, 0, dfil, ifil, dl, il, classInfo, silent);
1213  }
1214  ResetBit(kLoading);
1215 
1216  fConversionStreamerInfo = 0;
1217 }

1279 
1280 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1281 /// we found at least one equivalent.
1282 /// let's force a reload
1283 
1284 void TClass::ForceReload (TClass* oldcl)
1285 {
1286  TClass::RemoveClass(oldcl);
1287 
1288  if (oldcl->CanIgnoreTObjectStreamer()) {
1289  IgnoreTObjectStreamer();
1290  }
1291 
1292  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info;
1293  TIter next(oldcl->GetStreamerInfos());
1294  while ((info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)next())) {
1295  info->Clear("build");
1296  info->SetClass(this);
1297  fStreamerInfo->AddAtAndExpand(info,info->GetClassVersion());
1298  }
1299  oldcl->fStreamerInfo->Clear();
1300 
1301  oldcl->ReplaceWith(this);
1302  delete oldcl;
1303 }
1304 
1305 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1306 /// Initialize a TClass object. This object contains the full dictionary
1307 /// of a class. It has list to baseclasses, datamembers and methods.
1308 
1309 void TClass::Init(const char *name, Version_t cversion,
1310  const std::type_info *typeinfo, TVirtualIsAProxy *isa,
1311  const char *dfil, const char *ifil, Int_t dl, Int_t il,
1312  ClassInfo_t *givenInfo,
1313  Bool_t silent)
1314 {
1315  if (!gROOT)
1316  ::Fatal("TClass::TClass", "ROOT system not initialized");
1317  if (!name || !name[0]) {
1318  ::Error("TClass::Init", "The name parameter is invalid (null or empty)");
1319  MakeZombie();
1320  return;
1321  }
1322  // Always strip the default STL template arguments (from any template argument or the class name)
1323  fName = TClassEdit::ShortType(name, TClassEdit::kDropStlDefault).c_str();
1324  fClassVersion = cversion;
1325  fDeclFileName = dfil ? dfil : "";
1326  fImplFileName = ifil ? ifil : "";
1327  fDeclFileLine = dl;
1328  fImplFileLine = il;
1329  fTypeInfo = typeinfo;
1330  fIsA = isa;
1331  if ( fIsA ) fIsA->SetClass(this);
1332  // See also TCling::GenerateTClass() which will update fClassVersion after creation!
1333  fStreamerInfo = new TObjArray(fClassVersion+2+10,-1); // +10 to read new data by old
1334  fProperty = -1;
1335  fClassProperty = 0;
1336 
1337  ResetInstanceCount();
1338 
1339  TClass *oldcl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(fName.Data());
1340 
1341  InsertTClassInRegistryRAII insertRAII(fState,fName,fNoInfoOrEmuOrFwdDeclNameRegistry);
1342 
1343  if (oldcl && oldcl->TestBit(kLoading)) {
1344  // Do not recreate a class while it is already being created!
1345 
1346  // We can no longer reproduce this case, to check whether we are, we use
1347  // this code:
1348  // Fatal("Init","A bad replacement for %s was requested\n",name);
1349  return;
1350  }
1351 
1352  TClass **persistentRef = 0;
1353  if (oldcl) {
1354 
1355  persistentRef = oldcl->fPersistentRef.exchange(0);
1356 
1357  // The code from here is also in ForceReload.
1358  TClass::RemoveClass(oldcl);
1359  // move the StreamerInfo immediately so that there are
1360  // properly updated!
1361 
1362  if (oldcl->CanIgnoreTObjectStreamer()) {
1363  IgnoreTObjectStreamer();
1364  }
1365  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info;
1366 
1367  TIter next(oldcl->GetStreamerInfos());
1368  while ((info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)next())) {
1369  // We need to force a call to BuildOld
1370  info->Clear("build");
1371  info->SetClass(this);
1372  fStreamerInfo->AddAtAndExpand(info,info->GetClassVersion());
1373  }
1374  oldcl->fStreamerInfo->Clear();
1375  // The code diverges here from ForceReload.
1376 
1377  // Move the Schema Rules too.
1378  fSchemaRules = oldcl->fSchemaRules;
1379  oldcl->fSchemaRules = 0;
1380  }
1381 
1382  SetBit(kLoading);
1383  // Advertise ourself as the loading class for this class name
1384  TClass::AddClass(this);
1385 
1386  Bool_t isStl = TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(fName);
1387 
1388  if (!gInterpreter)
1389  ::Fatal("TClass::Init", "gInterpreter not initialized");
1390 
1391  if (givenInfo) {
1392  bool invalid = !gInterpreter->ClassInfo_IsValid(givenInfo);
1393  bool notloaded = !gInterpreter->ClassInfo_IsLoaded(givenInfo);
1394  auto property = gInterpreter->ClassInfo_Property(givenInfo);
1395 
1396  if (invalid || (notloaded && (property & kIsNamespace)) ||
1397  !(property & (kIsClass | kIsStruct | kIsNamespace))) {
1398  if (!TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(fName.Data())) {
1399  MakeZombie();
1400  fState = kNoInfo;
1401  TClass::RemoveClass(this);
1402  return;
1403  }
1404  }
1405 
1406  fClassInfo = gInterpreter->ClassInfo_Factory(givenInfo);
1407  fCanLoadClassInfo = false; // avoids calls to LoadClassInfo() if info is already loaded
1408  }
1409 
1410  // We need to check if the class it is not fwd declared for the cases where we
1411  // created a TClass directly in the kForwardDeclared state. Indeed in those cases
1412  // fClassInfo will always be nullptr.
1413  if (fState!=kForwardDeclared && !fClassInfo) {
1414 
1415  if (fState == kHasTClassInit) {
1416  // If the TClass is being generated from a ROOT dictionary,
1417  // even though we do not seem to have a CINT dictionary for
1418  // the class, we will will try to load it anyway UNLESS
1419  // the class is an STL container (or string).
1420  // This is because we do not expect the CINT dictionary
1421  // to be present for all STL classes (and we can handle
1422  // the lack of CINT dictionary in that cases).
1423  // However, the cling the dictionary no longer carries
1424  // an instantiation with it, unless we request the loading
1425  // here *or* the user explicitly instantiate the template
1426  // we would not have a ClassInfo for the template
1427  // instantiation.
1428  fCanLoadClassInfo = kTRUE;
1429  // Here we check and grab the info from the rootpcm.
1430  TProtoClass *proto = TClassTable::GetProtoNorm(GetName());
1431  if (proto && proto->FillTClass(this)) {
1432  fHasRootPcmInfo = kTRUE;
1433  }
1434  }
1435  if (!fHasRootPcmInfo && gInterpreter->CheckClassInfo(fName, /* autoload = */ kTRUE)) {
1436  gInterpreter->SetClassInfo(this); // sets fClassInfo pointer
1437  if (fClassInfo) {
1438  // This should be moved out of GetCheckSum itself however the last time
1439  // we tried this cause problem, in particular in the end-of-process operation.
1440  // fCheckSum = GetCheckSum(kLatestCheckSum);
1441  } else {
1442  if (!fClassInfo) {
1443  if (IsZombie()) {
1444  TClass::RemoveClass(this);
1445  return;
1446  }
1447  }
1448  }
1449  }
1450  }
1451  if (!silent && (!fClassInfo && !fCanLoadClassInfo) && !isStl && fName.First('@')==kNPOS &&
1452  !TClassEdit::IsInterpreterDetail(fName.Data()) ) {
1453  if (fState == kHasTClassInit) {
1454  if (fImplFileLine == -1 && fClassVersion == 0) {
1455  // We have a 'transient' class with a ClassDefInline and apparently no interpreter
1456  // information. Since it is transient, it is more than likely that the lack
1457  // will be harmles.
1458  } else {
1459  ::Error("TClass::Init", "no interpreter information for class %s is available even though it has a TClass "
1460  "initialization routine.",
1461  fName.Data());
1462  }
1463  } else {
1464  // In this case we initialised this TClass instance starting from the fwd declared state
1465  // and we know we have no dictionary: no need to warn
1466  ::Warning("TClass::Init", "no dictionary for class %s is available", fName.Data());
1467  }
1468  }
1469 
1470  fgClassCount++;
1471  SetUniqueID(fgClassCount);
1472 
1473  // Make the typedef-expanded -> original hash table entries.
1474  // There may be several entries for any given key.
1475  // We only make entries if the typedef-expanded name
1476  // is different from the original name.
1477  TString resolvedThis;
1478  if (!givenInfo && strchr (name, '<')) {
1479  if ( fName != name) {
1480  if (!fgClassTypedefHash) {
1481  fgClassTypedefHash = new THashTable (100, 5);
1482  fgClassTypedefHash->SetOwner (kTRUE);
1483  }
1484 
1485  fgClassTypedefHash->Add (new TNameMapNode (name, fName));
1486  SetBit (kHasNameMapNode);
1487 
1488  }
1489  resolvedThis = TClassEdit::ResolveTypedef (name, kTRUE);
1490  if (resolvedThis != name) {
1491  if (!fgClassTypedefHash) {
1492  fgClassTypedefHash = new THashTable (100, 5);
1493  fgClassTypedefHash->SetOwner (kTRUE);
1494  }
1495 
1496  fgClassTypedefHash->Add (new TNameMapNode (resolvedThis, fName));
1497  SetBit (kHasNameMapNode);
1498  }
1499 
1500  }
1501 
1502  //In case a class with the same name had been created by TVirtualStreamerInfo
1503  //we must delete the old class, importing only the StreamerInfo structure
1504  //from the old dummy class.
1505  if (oldcl) {
1506 
1507  oldcl->ReplaceWith(this);
1508  delete oldcl;
1509 
1510  } else if (!givenInfo && resolvedThis.Length() > 0 && fgClassTypedefHash) {
1511 
1512  // Check for existing equivalent.
1513 
1514  if (resolvedThis != fName) {
1515  oldcl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(resolvedThis);
1516  if (oldcl && oldcl != this) {
1517  persistentRef = oldcl->fPersistentRef.exchange(0);
1518  ForceReload (oldcl);
1519  }
1520  }
1521  TIter next( fgClassTypedefHash->GetListForObject(resolvedThis) );
1522  while ( TNameMapNode* htmp = static_cast<TNameMapNode*> (next()) ) {
1523  if (resolvedThis != htmp->String()) continue;
1524  oldcl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(htmp->fOrigName); // gROOT->GetClass (htmp->fOrigName, kFALSE);
1525  if (oldcl && oldcl != this) {
1526  persistentRef = oldcl->fPersistentRef.exchange(0);
1527  ForceReload (oldcl);
1528  }
1529  }
1530  }
1531  if (fClassInfo) {
1532  SetTitle(gCling->ClassInfo_Title(fClassInfo));
1533  if ( fDeclFileName == 0 || fDeclFileName[0] == '\0' ) {
1534  fDeclFileName = kUndeterminedClassInfoName;
1535  // Missing interface:
1536  // fDeclFileLine = gInterpreter->ClassInfo_FileLine( fClassInfo );
1537 
1538  // But really do not want to set ImplFileLine as it is currently the
1539  // marker of being 'loaded' or not (reminder loaded == has a TClass bootstrap).
1540  }
1541  }
1542 
1543  if (persistentRef) {
1544  fPersistentRef = persistentRef;
1545  } else {
1546  fPersistentRef = new TClass*;
1547  }
1548  *fPersistentRef = this;
1549 
1550  if ( isStl || !strncmp(GetName(),"stdext::hash_",13) || !strncmp(GetName(),"__gnu_cxx::hash_",16) ) {
1551  if (fState != kHasTClassInit) {
1552  // If we have a TClass compiled initialization, we can safely assume that
1553  // there will also be a collection proxy.
1554  fCollectionProxy = TVirtualStreamerInfo::Factory()->GenEmulatedProxy( GetName(), silent );
1555  if (fCollectionProxy) {
1556  fSizeof = fCollectionProxy->Sizeof();
1557 
1558  // Numeric Collections have implicit conversions:
1559  GetSchemaRules(kTRUE);
1560 
1561  } else if (!silent) {
1562  Warning("Init","Collection proxy for %s was not properly initialized!",GetName());
1563  }
1564  if (fStreamer==0) {
1565  fStreamer = TVirtualStreamerInfo::Factory()->GenEmulatedClassStreamer( GetName(), silent );
1566  }
1567  }
1568  } else if (!strncmp(GetName(),"std::pair<",10) || !strncmp(GetName(),"pair<",5) ) {
1569  // std::pairs have implicit conversions
1570  GetSchemaRules(kTRUE);
1571  }
1572 
1573  ResetBit(kLoading);
1574 }
1575 
1576 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1577 /// TClass dtor. Deletes all list that might have been created.
1578 
1579 TClass::~TClass()
1580 {
1581  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
1582 
1583  // Remove from the typedef hashtables.
1584  if (fgClassTypedefHash && TestBit (kHasNameMapNode)) {
1585  TString resolvedThis = TClassEdit::ResolveTypedef (GetName(), kTRUE);
1586  TIter next (fgClassTypedefHash->GetListForObject (resolvedThis));
1587  while ( TNameMapNode* htmp = static_cast<TNameMapNode*> (next()) ) {
1588  if (resolvedThis == htmp->String() && htmp->fOrigName == GetName()) {
1589  fgClassTypedefHash->Remove (htmp);
1590  delete htmp;
1591  break;
1592  }
1593  }
1594  }
1595 
1596  // Not owning lists, don't call Delete()
1597  // But this still need to be done first because the TList destructor
1598  // does access the object contained (via GetObject()->TestBit(kCanDelete))
1599  delete fStreamer; fStreamer =0;
1600  delete fAllPubData; fAllPubData =0;
1601  delete fAllPubMethod; fAllPubMethod=0;
1602 
1603  delete fPersistentRef.load();
1604 
1605  if (fBase.load())
1606  (*fBase).Delete();
1607  delete fBase.load(); fBase = 0;
1608 
1609  if (fData)
1610  fData->Delete();
1611  delete fData; fData = 0;
1612 
1613  if (fEnums.load())
1614  (*fEnums).Delete();
1615  delete fEnums.load(); fEnums = 0;
1616 
1617  if (fFuncTemplate)
1618  fFuncTemplate->Delete();
1619  delete fFuncTemplate; fFuncTemplate = 0;
1620 
1621  if (fMethod.load())
1622  (*fMethod).Delete();
1623  delete fMethod.load(); fMethod=0;
1624 
1625  if (fRealData)
1626  fRealData->Delete();
1627  delete fRealData; fRealData=0;
1628 
1629  if (fStreamerInfo)
1630  fStreamerInfo->Delete();
1631  delete fStreamerInfo; fStreamerInfo = nullptr;
1632 
1633  if (fDeclFileLine >= -1)
1634  TClass::RemoveClass(this);
1635 
1636  gCling->ClassInfo_Delete(fClassInfo);
1637  fClassInfo=0;
1638 
1639  if (fClassMenuList)
1640  fClassMenuList->Delete();
1641  delete fClassMenuList; fClassMenuList=0;
1642 
1643  fIsOffsetStreamerSet=kFALSE;
1644 
1645  if ( fIsA ) delete fIsA;
1646 
1647  if ( fRefProxy ) fRefProxy->Release();
1648  fRefProxy = 0;
1649 
1650  delete fStreamer;
1651  delete fCollectionProxy;
1652  delete fIsAMethod.load();
1653  delete fSchemaRules;
1654  if (fConversionStreamerInfo.load()) {
1655  std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>::iterator it;
1656  std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>::iterator end = (*fConversionStreamerInfo).end();
1657  for( it = (*fConversionStreamerInfo).begin(); it != end; ++it ) {
1658  delete it->second;
1659  }
1660  delete fConversionStreamerInfo.load();
1661  }
1662 }
1663 
1664 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1665 
1666 namespace {
1667  Int_t ReadRulesContent(FILE *f)
1668  {
1669  // Read a class.rules file which contains one rule per line with comment
1670  // starting with a #
1671  // Returns the number of rules loaded.
1672  // Returns -1 in case of error.
1673 
1674  R__ASSERT(f!=0);
1675  TString rule(1024);
1676  int c, state = 0;
1677  Int_t count = 0;
1678 
1679  while ((c = fgetc(f)) != EOF) {
1680  if (c == 13) // ignore CR
1681  continue;
1682  if (c == '\n') {
1683  if (state != 3) {
1684  state = 0;
1685  if (rule.Length() > 0) {
1686  if (TClass::AddRule(rule)) {
1687  ++count;
1688  }
1689  rule.Clear();
1690  }
1691  }
1692  continue;
1693  }
1694  switch (state) {
1695  case 0: // start of line
1696  switch (c) {
1697  case ' ':
1698  case '\t':
1699  break;
1700  case '#':
1701  state = 1;
1702  break;
1703  default:
1704  state = 2;
1705  break;
1706  }
1707  break;
1708 
1709  case 1: // comment
1710  break;
1711 
1712  case 2: // rule
1713  switch (c) {
1714  case '\\':
1715  state = 3; // Continuation request
1716  default:
1717  break;
1718  }
1719  break;
1720  }
1721  switch (state) {
1722  case 2:
1723  rule.Append(c);
1724  break;
1725  }
1726  }
1727  return count;
1728  }
1729 }
1730 
1731 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1732 /// Read the class.rules files from the default location:.
1733 /// $ROOTSYS/etc/class.rules (or ROOTETCDIR/class.rules)
1734 
1735 Int_t TClass::ReadRules()
1736 {
1737  static const char *suffix = "class.rules";
1738  TString sname = suffix;
1739  gSystem->PrependPathName(TROOT::GetEtcDir(), sname);
1740 
1741  Int_t res = -1;
1742 
1743  FILE * f = fopen(sname,"r");
1744  if (f != 0) {
1745  res = ReadRulesContent(f);
1746  fclose(f);
1747  } else {
1748  ::Error("TClass::ReadRules()", "Cannot find rules file %s", sname.Data());
1749  }
1750  return res;
1751 }
1752 
1753 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1754 /// Read a class.rules file which contains one rule per line with comment
1755 /// starting with a #
1756 /// - Returns the number of rules loaded.
1757 /// - Returns -1 in case of error.
1758 
1759 Int_t TClass::ReadRules( const char *filename )
1760 {
1761  if (!filename || !filename[0]) {
1762  ::Error("TClass::ReadRules", "no file name specified");
1763  return -1;
1764  }
1765 
1766  FILE * f = fopen(filename,"r");
1767  if (f == 0) {
1768  ::Error("TClass::ReadRules","Failed to open %s\n",filename);
1769  return -1;
1770  }
1771  Int_t count = ReadRulesContent(f);
1772 
1773  fclose(f);
1774  return count;
1775 
1776 }
1777 
1778 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1779 /// Add a schema evolution customization rule.
1780 /// The syntax of the rule can be either the short form:
1781 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
1782 /// [type=Read] classname membername [attributes=... ] [version=[...] ] [checksum=[...] ] [oldtype=...] [code={...}]
1783 /// ~~~
1784 /// or the long form
1785 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
1786 /// [type=Read] sourceClass=classname [targetclass=newClassname] [ source="type membername; [type2 membername2]" ]
1787 /// [target="membername3;membername4"] [attributes=... ] [version=...] [checksum=...] [code={...}|functionname]
1788 /// ~~~
1789 ///
1790 /// For example to set HepMC::GenVertex::m_event to _not_ owned the object it is pointing to:
1791 /// HepMC::GenVertex m_event attributes=NotOwner
1792 ///
1793 /// Semantic of the tags:
1794 /// - type : the type of the rule, valid values: Read, ReadRaw, Write, WriteRaw, the default is 'Read'.
1795 /// - sourceClass : the name of the class as it is on the rule file
1796 /// - targetClass : the name of the class as it is in the current code ; defaults to the value of sourceClass
1797 /// - source : the types and names of the data members from the class on file that are needed, the list is separated by semi-colons ';'
1798 /// - oldtype: in the short form only, indicates the type on disk of the data member.
1799 /// - target : the names of the data members updated by this rule, the list is separated by semi-colons ';'
1800 /// - attributes : list of possible qualifiers among: Owner, NotOwner
1801 /// - version : list of the version of the class layout that this rule applies to. The syntax can be [1,4,5] or [2-] or [1-3] or [-3]
1802 /// - checksum : comma delimited list of the checksums of the class layout that this rule applies to.
1803 /// - code={...} : code to be executed for the rule or name of the function implementing it.
1804 
1805 Bool_t TClass::AddRule( const char *rule )
1806 {
1807  ROOT::TSchemaRule *ruleobj = new ROOT::TSchemaRule();
1808  if (! ruleobj->SetFromRule( rule ) ) {
1809  delete ruleobj;
1810  return kFALSE;
1811  }
1812 
1813  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
1814 
1815  TClass *cl = TClass::GetClass( ruleobj->GetTargetClass() );
1816  if (!cl) {
1817  // Create an empty emulated class for now.
1818  cl = gInterpreter->GenerateTClass(ruleobj->GetTargetClass(), /* emulation = */ kTRUE, /*silent = */ kTRUE);
1819  }
1820  ROOT::Detail::TSchemaRuleSet* rset = cl->GetSchemaRules( kTRUE );
1821 
1822  TString errmsg;
1823  if( !rset->AddRule( ruleobj, ROOT::Detail::TSchemaRuleSet::kCheckConflict, &errmsg ) ) {
1824  ::Warning( "TClass::AddRule", "The rule for class: \"%s\": version, \"%s\" and data members: \"%s\" has been skipped because it conflicts with one of the other rules (%s).",
1825  ruleobj->GetTargetClass(), ruleobj->GetVersion(), ruleobj->GetTargetString(), errmsg.Data() );
1826  delete ruleobj;
1827  return kFALSE;
1828  }
1829  return kTRUE;
1830 }

1890 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1891 /// Browse objects of of the class described by this TClass object.
1892 
1893 Int_t TClass::Browse(void *obj, TBrowser *b) const
1894 {
1895  if (!obj) return 0;
1896 
1897  TClass *actual = GetActualClass(obj);
1898  if (IsTObject()) {
1899  // Call TObject::Browse.
1900 
1901  if (!fIsOffsetStreamerSet) {
1902  CalculateStreamerOffset();
1903  }
1904  TObject* realTObject = (TObject*)((size_t)obj + fOffsetStreamer);
1905  realTObject->Browse(b);
1906  return 1;
1907  } else if (actual != this) {
1908  return actual->Browse(obj, b);
1909  } else if (GetCollectionProxy()) {
1910 
1911  // do something useful.
1912 
1913  } else {
1914  TAutoInspector insp(b);
1915  CallShowMembers(obj,insp,kFALSE);
1916  return insp.fCount;
1917  }
1918 
1919  return 0;
1920 }

1922 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1923 /// This method is called by a browser to get the class information.
1924 
1925 void TClass::Browse(TBrowser *b)
1926 {
1927  if (!HasInterpreterInfo()) return;
1928 
1929  if (b) {
1930  if (!fRealData) BuildRealData();
1931 
1932  b->Add(GetListOfDataMembers(), "Data Members");
1933  b->Add(GetListOfRealData(), "Real Data Members");
1934  b->Add(GetListOfMethods(), "Methods");
1935  b->Add(GetListOfBases(), "Base Classes");
1936  }
1937 }
1938 
1939 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1940 /// Build a full list of persistent data members.
1941 /// Scans the list of all data members in the class itself and also
1942 /// in all base classes. For each persistent data member, inserts a
1943 /// TRealData object in the list fRealData.
1944 ///
1945 
1946 void TClass::BuildRealData(void* pointer, Bool_t isTransient)
1947 {
1948 
1949  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
1950 
1951  // Only do this once.
1952  if (fRealData) {
1953  return;
1954  }
1955 
1956  if (fClassVersion == 0) {
1957  isTransient = kTRUE;
1958  }
1959 
1960  // When called via TMapFile (e.g. Update()) make sure that the dictionary
1961  // gets allocated on the heap and not in the mapped file.
1962  TMmallocDescTemp setreset;
1963 
1964  // Handle emulated classes and STL containers specially.
1965  if (!HasInterpreterInfo() || TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(GetName(), 0) || TClassEdit::IsSTLBitset(GetName())) {
1966  // We are an emulated class or an STL container.
1967  fRealData = new TList;
1968  BuildEmulatedRealData("", 0, this);
1969  return;
1970  }
1971 
1972  // return early on string
1973  static TClassRef clRefString("std::string");
1974  if (clRefString == this) {
1975  return;
1976  }
1977 
1978  // Complain about stl classes ending up here (unique_ptr etc) - except for
1979  // pair where we will build .first, .second just fine
1980  // and those for which the user explicitly requested a dictionary.
1981  if (!isTransient && GetState() != kHasTClassInit
1982  && TClassEdit::IsStdClass(GetName())
1983  && strncmp(GetName(), "pair<", 5) != 0) {
1984  Error("BuildRealData", "Inspection for %s not supported!", GetName());
1985  }
1986 
1987  // The following statement will recursively call
1988  // all the subclasses of this class.
1989  fRealData = new TList;
1990  TBuildRealData brd(pointer, this);
1991 
1992  // CallShowMember will force a call to InheritsFrom, which indirectly
1993  // calls TClass::GetClass. It forces the loading of new typedefs in
1994  // case some of them were not yet loaded.
1995  if ( ! CallShowMembers(pointer, brd, isTransient) ) {
1996  if ( isTransient ) {
1997  // This is a transient data member, so it is probably fine to not have
1998  // access to its content. However let's no mark it as definitively setup,
1999  // since another class might use this class for a persistent data member and
2000  // in this case we really want the error message.
2001  delete fRealData;
2002  fRealData = 0;
2003  } else {
2004  Error("BuildRealData", "Cannot find any ShowMembers function for %s!", GetName());
2005  }
2006  }
2007 
2008  // Take this opportunity to build the real data for base classes.
2009  // In case one base class is abstract, it would not be possible later
2010  // to create the list of real data for this abstract class.
2011  TBaseClass* base = 0;
2012  TIter next(GetListOfBases());
2013  while ((base = (TBaseClass*) next())) {
2014  if (base->IsSTLContainer()) {
2015  continue;
2016  }
2017  TClass* c = base->GetClassPointer();
2018  if (c) {
2019  c->BuildRealData(0, isTransient);
2020  }
2021  }
2022 }
2023 
2024 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2025 /// Build the list of real data for an emulated class
2026 
2027 void TClass::BuildEmulatedRealData(const char *name, Long_t offset, TClass *cl)
2028 {
2029  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2030 
2031  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info;
2032  if (Property() & kIsAbstract) {
2033  info = GetStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated();
2034  } else {
2035  info = GetStreamerInfo();
2036  }
2037  if (!info) {
2038  // This class is abstract, but we don't yet have a SteamerInfo for it ...
2039  Error("BuildEmulatedRealData","Missing StreamerInfo for %s",GetName());
2040  // Humm .. no information ... let's bail out
2041  return;
2042  }
2043 
2044  TIter next(info->GetElements());
2045  TStreamerElement *element;
2046  while ((element = (TStreamerElement*)next())) {
2047  Int_t etype = element->GetType();
2048  Long_t eoffset = element->GetOffset();
2049  TClass *cle = element->GetClassPointer();
2050  if (element->IsBase() || etype == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kBase) {
2051  //base class are skipped in this loop, they will be added at the end.
2052  continue;
2053  } else if (etype == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kTObject ||
2054  etype == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kTNamed ||
2055  etype == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject ||
2056  etype == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAny) {
2057  //member class
2058  TString rdname; rdname.Form("%s%s",name,element->GetFullName());
2059  TRealData *rd = new TRealData(rdname,offset+eoffset,0);
2060  if (gDebug > 0) printf(" Class: %s, adding TRealData=%s, offset=%ld\n",cl->GetName(),rd->GetName(),rd->GetThisOffset());
2061  cl->GetListOfRealData()->Add(rd);
2062  // Now we a dot
2063  rdname.Form("%s%s.",name,element->GetFullName());
2064  if (cle) cle->BuildEmulatedRealData(rdname,offset+eoffset,cl);
2065  } else {
2066  //others
2067  TString rdname; rdname.Form("%s%s",name,element->GetFullName());
2068  TRealData *rd = new TRealData(rdname,offset+eoffset,0);
2069  if (gDebug > 0) printf(" Class: %s, adding TRealData=%s, offset=%ld\n",cl->GetName(),rd->GetName(),rd->GetThisOffset());
2070  cl->GetListOfRealData()->Add(rd);
2071  }
2072  //if (fClassInfo==0 && element->IsBase()) {
2073  // if (fBase==0) fBase = new TList;
2074  // TClass *base = element->GetClassPointer();
2075  // fBase->Add(new TBaseClass(this, cl, eoffset));
2076  //}
2077  }
2078  // The base classes must added last on the list of real data (to help with ambiguous data member names)
2079  next.Reset();
2080  while ((element = (TStreamerElement*)next())) {
2081  Int_t etype = element->GetType();
2082  if (element->IsBase() || etype == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kBase) {
2083  //base class
2084  Long_t eoffset = element->GetOffset();
2085  TClass *cle = element->GetClassPointer();
2086  if (cle) cle->BuildEmulatedRealData(name,offset+eoffset,cl);
2087  }
2088  }
2089 }

2092 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2093 /// Calculate the offset between an object of this class to
2094 /// its base class TObject. The pointer can be adjusted by
2095 /// that offset to access any virtual method of TObject like
2096 /// Streamer() and ShowMembers().
2097 
2098 void TClass::CalculateStreamerOffset() const
2099 {
2100  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2101  if (!fIsOffsetStreamerSet && HasInterpreterInfo()) {
2102  // When called via TMapFile (e.g. Update()) make sure that the dictionary
2103  // gets allocated on the heap and not in the mapped file.
2104 
2105  TMmallocDescTemp setreset;
2106  fOffsetStreamer = const_cast<TClass*>(this)->GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse(TObject::Class());
2107  if (fStreamerType == kTObject) {
2108  fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerTObjectInitialized;
2109  }
2110  fIsOffsetStreamerSet = kTRUE;
2111  }
2112 }
2113 
2114 
2115 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2116 /// Call ShowMembers() on the obj of this class type, passing insp and parent.
2117 /// isATObject is -1 if unknown, 0 if it is not a TObject, and 1 if it is a TObject.
2118 /// The function returns whether it was able to call ShowMembers().
2119 
2120 Bool_t TClass::CallShowMembers(const void* obj, TMemberInspector &insp, Bool_t isTransient) const
2121 {
2122  if (fShowMembers) {
2123  // This should always works since 'pointer' should be pointing
2124  // to an object of the actual type of this TClass object.
2125  fShowMembers(obj, insp, isTransient);
2126  return kTRUE;
2127  } else {
2128 
2129  if (fCanLoadClassInfo) LoadClassInfo();
2130  if (fClassInfo) {
2131 
2132  if (strcmp(GetName(), "string") == 0) {
2133  // For std::string we know that we do not have a ShowMembers
2134  // function and that it's okay.
2135  return kTRUE;
2136  }
2137  // Since we do have some dictionary information, let's
2138  // call the interpreter's ShowMember.
2139  // This works with Cling to support interpreted classes.
2140  gInterpreter->InspectMembers(insp, obj, this, isTransient);
2141  return kTRUE;
2142 
2143  } else if (TVirtualStreamerInfo* sinfo = GetStreamerInfo()) {
2144  sinfo->CallShowMembers(obj, insp, isTransient);
2145  return kTRUE;
2146  } // isATObject
2147  } // fShowMembers is set
2148 
2149  return kFALSE;
2150 }
2151 
2152 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2153 /// Do a ShowMembers() traversal of all members and base classes' members
2154 /// using the reflection information from the interpreter. Works also for
2155 /// interpreted objects.
2156 
2157 void TClass::InterpretedShowMembers(void* obj, TMemberInspector &insp, Bool_t isTransient)
2158 {
2159  return gInterpreter->InspectMembers(insp, obj, this, isTransient);
2160 }
2161 
2162 Bool_t TClass::CanSplitBaseAllow()
2163 {
2164  if (fCanSplit >= 0) {
2165  return ! ( fCanSplit & 0x2 );
2166  }
2167 
2168  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2169 
2170  if (GetCollectionProxy() != nullptr) {
2171  // A collection can never affect its derived class 'splittability'
2172  return kTRUE;
2173  }
2174 
2175  if (this == TRef::Class()) { fCanSplit = 2; return kFALSE; }
2176  if (this == TRefArray::Class()) { fCanSplit = 2; return kFALSE; }
2177  if (this == TArray::Class()) { fCanSplit = 2; return kFALSE; }
2178  if (this == TClonesArray::Class()) { fCanSplit = 1; return kTRUE; }
2179  if (this == TCollection::Class()) { fCanSplit = 2; return kFALSE; }
2180 
2181  // TTree is not always available (for example in rootcling), so we need
2182  // to grab it silently.
2183  auto refTreeClass( TClass::GetClass("TTree",kTRUE,kTRUE) );
2184  if (this == refTreeClass) { fCanSplit = 2; return kFALSE; }
2185 
2186  if (!HasDataMemberInfo()) {
2187  TVirtualStreamerInfo *sinfo = ((TClass *)this)->GetCurrentStreamerInfo();
2188  if (sinfo==0) sinfo = GetStreamerInfo();
2189  TIter next(sinfo->GetElements());
2190  TStreamerElement *element;
2191  while ((element = (TStreamerElement*)next())) {
2192  if (element->IsA() == TStreamerBase::Class()) {
2193  TClass *clbase = element->GetClassPointer();
2194  if (!clbase) {
2195  // If there is a missing base class, we can't split the immediate
2196  // derived class.
2197  fCanSplit = 0;
2198  return kFALSE;
2199  } else if (!clbase->CanSplitBaseAllow()) {
2200  fCanSplit = 2;
2201  return kFALSE;
2202  }
2203  }
2204  }
2205  }
2206 
2207  // If we don't have data member info there is no more information
2208  // we can find out.
2209  if (!HasDataMemberInfo()) return kTRUE;
2210 
2211  TObjLink *lnk = GetListOfBases() ? fBase.load()->FirstLink() : 0;
2212 
2213  // Look at inheritance tree
2214  while (lnk) {
2215  TClass *c;
2216  TBaseClass *base = (TBaseClass*) lnk->GetObject();
2217  c = base->GetClassPointer();
2218  if(!c) {
2219  // If there is a missing base class, we can't split the immediate
2220  // derived class.
2221  fCanSplit = 0;
2222  return kFALSE;
2223  } else if (!c->CanSplitBaseAllow()) {
2224  fCanSplit = 2;
2225  return kFALSE;
2226  }
2227  lnk = lnk->Next();
2228  }
2229  return kTRUE;
2230 }
2231 
2232 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2233 /// Return true if the data member of this TClass can be saved separately.
2234 
2235 Bool_t TClass::CanSplit() const
2236 {
2237  // Note: add the possibility to set it for the class and the derived class.
2238  // save the info in TVirtualStreamerInfo
2239  // deal with the info in MakeProject
2240  if (fCanSplit >= 0) {
2241  // The user explicitly set the value
2242  return (fCanSplit & 0x1) == 1;
2243  }
2244 
2245  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2246  TClass *This = const_cast<TClass*>(this);
2247 
2248  if (this == TObject::Class()) { This->fCanSplit = 1; return kTRUE; }
2249  if (fName == "TClonesArray") { This->fCanSplit = 1; return kTRUE; }
2250  if (fRefProxy) { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2251  if (fName.BeginsWith("TVectorT<")) { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2252  if (fName.BeginsWith("TMatrixT<")) { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2253  if (fName == "string") { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2254  if (fName == "std::string") { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2255 
2256  if (GetCollectionProxy()!=0) {
2257  // For STL collection we need to look inside.
2258 
2259  // However we do not split collections of collections
2260  // nor collections of strings
2261  // nor collections of pointers (unless explicit request (see TBranchSTL)).
2262 
2263  if (GetCollectionProxy()->HasPointers()) { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2264 
2265  TClass *valueClass = GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass();
2266  if (valueClass == 0) { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2267  static TClassRef stdStringClass("std::string");
2268  if (valueClass==TString::Class() || valueClass==stdStringClass)
2269  { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2270  if (!valueClass->CanSplit()) { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2271  if (valueClass->GetCollectionProxy() != 0) { This->fCanSplit = 0; return kFALSE; }
2272 
2273  Int_t stl = -TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(GetName(), 0);
2274  if ((stl==ROOT::kSTLmap || stl==ROOT::kSTLmultimap)
2275  && !valueClass->HasDataMemberInfo())
2276  {
2277  This->fCanSplit = 0;
2278  return kFALSE;
2279  }
2280 
2281  This->fCanSplit = 1;
2282  return kTRUE;
2283 
2284  }
2285 
2286  if (GetStreamer() != nullptr || fStreamerFunc != nullptr) {
2287 
2288  // We have an external custom streamer provided by the user, we must not
2289  // split it.
2290  This->fCanSplit = 0;
2291  return kFALSE;
2292 
2293  } else if ( TestBit(TClass::kHasCustomStreamerMember) ) {
2294 
2295  // We have a custom member function streamer or
2296  // an older (not StreamerInfo based) automatic streamer.
2297  This->fCanSplit = 0;
2298  return kFALSE;
2299  }
2300 
2301  if (Size()==1) {
2302  // 'Empty' class there is nothing to split!.
2303  This->fCanSplit = 0;
2304  return kFALSE;
2305  }
2306 
2307 
2308  if ( !This->CanSplitBaseAllow() ) {
2309  return kFALSE;
2310  }
2311 
2312  This->fCanSplit = 1;
2313  return kTRUE;
2314 }

2318 /// class, see EClassProperty in TDictionary.h
2319 
2320 Long_t TClass::ClassProperty() const
2321 {
2322  if (fProperty == -1) Property();
2323  return fClassProperty;
2324 }
2325 
2326 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2327 /// Create a Clone of this TClass object using a different name but using the same 'dictionary'.
2328 /// This effectively creates a hard alias for the class name.
2329 
2330 TObject *TClass::Clone(const char *new_name) const
2331 {
2332  if (new_name == 0 || new_name[0]=='\0' || fName == new_name) {
2333  Error("Clone","The name of the class must be changed when cloning a TClass object.");
2334  return 0;
2335  }
2336 
2337  // Need to lock access to TROOT::GetListOfClasses so the cloning happens atomically
2338  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2339  // Temporarily remove the original from the list of classes.
2340  TClass::RemoveClass(const_cast<TClass*>(this));
2341 
2342  TClass *copy;
2343  if (fTypeInfo) {
2344  copy = new TClass(GetName(),
2345  fClassVersion,
2346  *fTypeInfo,
2347  new TIsAProxy(*fTypeInfo),
2348  GetDeclFileName(),
2349  GetImplFileName(),
2350  GetDeclFileLine(),
2351  GetImplFileLine());
2352  } else {
2353  copy = new TClass(GetName(),
2354  fClassVersion,
2355  GetDeclFileName(),
2356  GetImplFileName(),
2357  GetDeclFileLine(),
2358  GetImplFileLine());
2359  }
2360  copy->fShowMembers = fShowMembers;
2361  // Remove the copy before renaming it
2362  TClass::RemoveClass(copy);
2363  copy->fName = new_name;
2364  TClass::AddClass(copy);
2365 
2366  copy->SetNew(fNew);
2367  copy->SetNewArray(fNewArray);
2368  copy->SetDelete(fDelete);
2369  copy->SetDeleteArray(fDeleteArray);
2370  copy->SetDestructor(fDestructor);
2371  copy->SetDirectoryAutoAdd(fDirAutoAdd);
2372  copy->fStreamerFunc = fStreamerFunc;
2373  copy->fConvStreamerFunc = fConvStreamerFunc;
2374  if (fStreamer) {
2375  copy->AdoptStreamer(fStreamer->Generate());
2376  }
2377  // If IsZombie is true, something went wrong and we will not be
2378  // able to properly copy the collection proxy
2379  if (fCollectionProxy && !copy->IsZombie()) {
2380  copy->CopyCollectionProxy(*fCollectionProxy);
2381  }
2382  copy->SetClassSize(fSizeof);
2383  if (fRefProxy) {
2384  copy->AdoptReferenceProxy( fRefProxy->Clone() );
2385  }
2386  TClass::AddClass(const_cast<TClass*>(this));
2387  return copy;
2388 }
2389 
2390 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2391 /// Copy the argument.
2392 
2393 void TClass::CopyCollectionProxy(const TVirtualCollectionProxy &orig)
2394 {
2395 // // This code was used too quickly test the STL Emulation layer
2396 // Int_t k = TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(GetName());
2397 // if (k==1||k==-1) return;
2398 
2399  delete fCollectionProxy;
2400  fCollectionProxy = orig.Generate();
2401 }

2403 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2404 /// Draw detailed class inheritance structure.
2405 /// If a class B inherits from a class A, the description of B is drawn
2406 /// on the right side of the description of A.
2407 /// Member functions overridden by B are shown in class A with a blue line
2408 /// erasing the corresponding member function
2409 
2410 void TClass::Draw(Option_t *option)
2411 {
2412  if (!HasInterpreterInfo()) return;
2413 
2414  TVirtualPad *padsav = gPad;
2415 
2416  // Should we create a new canvas?
2417  TString opt=option;
2418  if (!padsav || !opt.Contains("same")) {
2419  TVirtualPad *padclass = (TVirtualPad*)(gROOT->GetListOfCanvases())->FindObject("R__class");
2420  if (!padclass) {
2421  gROOT->ProcessLine("new TCanvas(\"R__class\",\"class\",20,20,1000,750);");
2422  } else {
2423  padclass->cd();
2424  }
2425  }
2426 
2427  if (gPad) gPad->DrawClassObject(this,option);
2428 
2429  if (padsav) padsav->cd();
2430 }

2432 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2433 /// Dump contents of object on stdout.
2434 /// Using the information in the object dictionary
2435 /// each data member is interpreted.
2436 /// If a data member is a pointer, the pointer value is printed
2437 /// 'obj' is assume to point to an object of the class describe by this TClass
2438 ///
2439 /// The following output is the Dump of a TArrow object:
2440 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
2441 /// fAngle 0 Arrow opening angle (degrees)
2442 /// fArrowSize 0.2 Arrow Size
2443 /// fOption.*fData
2444 /// fX1 0.1 X of 1st point
2445 /// fY1 0.15 Y of 1st point
2446 /// fX2 0.67 X of 2nd point
2447 /// fY2 0.83 Y of 2nd point
2448 /// fUniqueID 0 object unique identifier
2449 /// fBits 50331648 bit field status word
2450 /// fLineColor 1 line color
2451 /// fLineStyle 1 line style
2452 /// fLineWidth 1 line width
2453 /// fFillColor 19 fill area color
2454 /// fFillStyle 1001 fill area style
2455 /// ~~~
2456 ///
2457 /// If noAddr is true, printout of all pointer values is skipped.
2458 
2459 void TClass::Dump(const void *obj, Bool_t noAddr /*=kFALSE*/) const
2460 {
2461 
2462  Long_t prObj = noAddr ? 0 : (Long_t)obj;
2463  if (IsTObject()) {
2464  if (!fIsOffsetStreamerSet) {
2465  CalculateStreamerOffset();
2466  }
2467  TObject *tobj = (TObject*)((Long_t)obj + fOffsetStreamer);
2468 
2469 
2470  if (sizeof(this) == 4)
2471  Printf("==> Dumping object at: 0x%08lx, name=%s, class=%s\n",prObj,tobj->GetName(),GetName());
2472  else
2473  Printf("==> Dumping object at: 0x%016lx, name=%s, class=%s\n",prObj,tobj->GetName(),GetName());
2474  } else {
2475 
2476  if (sizeof(this) == 4)
2477  Printf("==> Dumping object at: 0x%08lx, class=%s\n",prObj,GetName());
2478  else
2479  Printf("==> Dumping object at: 0x%016lx, class=%s\n",prObj,GetName());
2480  }
2481 
2482  TDumpMembers dm(noAddr);
2483  if (!CallShowMembers(obj, dm, kFALSE)) {
2484  Info("Dump", "No ShowMembers function, dumping disabled");
2485  }
2486 }
