2488 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2489 /// Introduce an escape character (@) in front of a special chars.
2490 /// You need to use the result immediately before it is being overwritten.
2491 
2492 char *TClass::EscapeChars(const char *text) const
2493 {
2494  static const UInt_t maxsize = 255;
2495  static char name[maxsize+2]; //One extra if last char needs to be escaped
2496 
2497  UInt_t nch = strlen(text);
2498  UInt_t icur = 0;
2499  for (UInt_t i = 0; i < nch && icur < maxsize; ++i, ++icur) {
2500  if (text[i] == '\"' || text[i] == '[' || text[i] == '~' ||
2501  text[i] == ']' || text[i] == '&' || text[i] == '#' ||
2502  text[i] == '!' || text[i] == '^' || text[i] == '<' ||
2503  text[i] == '?' || text[i] == '>') {
2504  name[icur] = '@';
2505  ++icur;
2506  }
2507  name[icur] = text[i];
2508  }
2509  name[icur] = 0;
2510  return name;
2511 }
2512 
2513 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2514 /// Return a pointer the the real class of the object.
2515 /// This is equivalent to object->IsA() when the class has a ClassDef.
2516 /// It is REQUIRED that object is coming from a proper pointer to the
2517 /// class represented by 'this'.
2518 /// Example: Special case:
2519 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
2520 /// class MyClass : public AnotherClass, public TObject
2521 /// ~~~
2522 /// then on return, one must do:
2523 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
2524 /// TObject *obj = (TObject*)((void*)myobject)directory->Get("some object of MyClass");
2525 /// MyClass::Class()->GetActualClass(obj); // this would be wrong!!!
2526 /// ~~~
2527 /// Also if the class represented by 'this' and NONE of its parents classes
2528 /// have a virtual ptr table, the result will be 'this' and NOT the actual
2529 /// class.
2530 
2531 TClass *TClass::GetActualClass(const void *object) const
2532 {
2533  if (object==0) return (TClass*)this;
2534  if (fIsA) {
2535  return (*fIsA)(object); // ROOT::IsA((ThisClass*)object);
2536  } else if (fGlobalIsA) {
2537  return fGlobalIsA(this,object);
2538  } else {
2539  if (IsTObject()) {
2540 
2541  if (!fIsOffsetStreamerSet) {
2542  CalculateStreamerOffset();
2543  }
2544  TObject* realTObject = (TObject*)((size_t)object + fOffsetStreamer);
2545 
2546  return realTObject->IsA();
2547  }
2548 
2549  if (HasInterpreterInfo()) {
2550 
2551  TVirtualIsAProxy *isa = 0;
2552  if (GetClassInfo() && gCling->ClassInfo_HasMethod(fClassInfo,"IsA")) {
2553  isa = (TVirtualIsAProxy*)gROOT->ProcessLineFast(TString::Format("new ::TInstrumentedIsAProxy<%s>(0);",GetName()));
2554  }
2555  else {
2556  isa = (TVirtualIsAProxy*)gROOT->ProcessLineFast(TString::Format("new ::TIsAProxy(typeid(%s));",GetName()));
2557  }
2558  if (isa) {
2559  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2560  const_cast<TClass*>(this)->fIsA = isa;
2561  }
2562  if (fIsA) {
2563  return (*fIsA)(object); // ROOT::IsA((ThisClass*)object);
2564  }
2565  }
2566  TVirtualStreamerInfo* sinfo = GetStreamerInfo();
2567  if (sinfo) {
2568  return sinfo->GetActualClass(object);
2569  }
2570  return (TClass*)this;
2571  }
2572 }
2573 
2574 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2575 /// Return pointer to the base class "classname". Returns 0 in case
2576 /// "classname" is not a base class. Takes care of multiple inheritance.
2577 
2578 TClass *TClass::GetBaseClass(const char *classname)
2579 {
2580  // check if class name itself is equal to classname
2581  if (strcmp(GetName(), classname) == 0) return this;
2582 
2583  if (!HasDataMemberInfo()) return 0;
2584 
2585  // Make sure we deal with possible aliases, we could also have normalized
2586  // the name.
2587  TClass *search = TClass::GetClass(classname,kTRUE,kTRUE);
2588 
2589  if (search) return GetBaseClass(search);
2590  else return 0;
2591 }
2592 
2593 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2594 /// Return pointer to the base class "cl". Returns 0 in case "cl"
2595 /// is not a base class. Takes care of multiple inheritance.
2596 
2597 TClass *TClass::GetBaseClass(const TClass *cl)
2598 {
2599  // check if class name itself is equal to classname
2600  if (cl == this) return this;
2601 
2602  if (!HasDataMemberInfo()) return 0;
2603 
2604  TObjLink *lnk = GetListOfBases() ? fBase.load()->FirstLink() : 0;
2605 
2606  // otherwise look at inheritance tree
2607  while (lnk) {
2608  TClass *c, *c1;
2609  TBaseClass *base = (TBaseClass*) lnk->GetObject();
2610  c = base->GetClassPointer();
2611  if (c) {
2612  if (cl == c) return c;
2613  c1 = c->GetBaseClass(cl);
2614  if (c1) return c1;
2615  }
2616  lnk = lnk->Next();
2617  }
2618  return 0;
2619 }
2620 
2621 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2622 /// Return data member offset to the base class "cl".
2623 /// - Returns -1 in case "cl" is not a base class.
2624 /// - Returns -2 if cl is a base class, but we can't find the offset
2625 /// because it's virtual.
2626 /// Takes care of multiple inheritance.
2627 
2628 Int_t TClass::GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse(const TClass *cl)
2629 {
2630  // check if class name itself is equal to classname
2631  if (cl == this) return 0;
2632 
2633  if (!fBase.load()) {
2634  if (fCanLoadClassInfo) LoadClassInfo();
2635  // If the information was not provided by the root pcm files and
2636  // if we can not find the ClassInfo, we have to fall back to the
2637  // StreamerInfo
2638  if (!fClassInfo) {
2639  TVirtualStreamerInfo *sinfo = GetCurrentStreamerInfo();
2640  if (!sinfo) return -1;
2641  TStreamerElement *element;
2642  Int_t offset = 0;
2643 
2644  TObjArray &elems = *(sinfo->GetElements());
2645  Int_t size = elems.GetLast()+1;
2646  for(Int_t i=0; i<size; i++) {
2647  element = (TStreamerElement*)elems[i];
2648  if (element->IsBase()) {
2649  if (element->IsA() == TStreamerBase::Class()) {
2650  TStreamerBase *base = (TStreamerBase*)element;
2651  TClass *baseclass = base->GetClassPointer();
2652  if (!baseclass) return -1;
2653  Int_t subOffset = baseclass->GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse(cl);
2654  if (subOffset == -2) return -2;
2655  if (subOffset != -1) return offset+subOffset;
2656  offset += baseclass->Size();
2657  } else if (element->IsA() == TStreamerSTL::Class()) {
2658  TStreamerSTL *base = (TStreamerSTL*)element;
2659  TClass *baseclass = base->GetClassPointer();
2660  if (!baseclass) return -1;
2661  Int_t subOffset = baseclass->GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse(cl);
2662  if (subOffset == -2) return -2;
2663  if (subOffset != -1) return offset+subOffset;
2664  offset += baseclass->Size();
2665 
2666  } else {
2667  Error("GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse","Unexpected element type for base class: %s\n",element->IsA()->GetName());
2668  }
2669  }
2670  }
2671  return -1;
2672  }
2673  }
2674 
2675  TClass *c;
2676  Int_t off;
2677  TBaseClass *inh;
2678  TObjLink *lnk = 0;
2679  if (fBase.load() == 0)
2680  lnk = GetListOfBases()->FirstLink();
2681  else
2682  lnk = fBase.load()->FirstLink();
2683 
2684  // otherwise look at inheritance tree
2685  while (lnk) {
2686  inh = (TBaseClass *)lnk->GetObject();
2687  //use option load=kFALSE to avoid a warning like:
2688  //"Warning in <TClass::TClass>: no dictionary for class TRefCnt is available"
2689  //We can not afford to not have the class if it exist, so we
2690  //use kTRUE.
2691  c = inh->GetClassPointer(kTRUE); // kFALSE);
2692  if (c) {
2693  if (cl == c) {
2694  if ((inh->Property() & kIsVirtualBase) != 0)
2695  return -2;
2696  return inh->GetDelta();
2697  }
2698  off = c->GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse(cl);
2699  if (off == -2) return -2;
2700  if (off != -1) {
2701  return off + inh->GetDelta();
2702  }
2703  }
2704  lnk = lnk->Next();
2705  }
2706  return -1;
2707 }
2708 
2709 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2710 /// - Return data member offset to the base class "cl".
2711 /// - Returns -1 in case "cl" is not a base class.
2712 /// Takes care of multiple inheritance.
2713 
2714 Int_t TClass::GetBaseClassOffset(const TClass *toBase, void *address, bool isDerivedObject)
2715 {
2716  // Warning("GetBaseClassOffset","Requires the use of fClassInfo for %s to %s",GetName(),toBase->GetName());
2717 
2718  if (this == toBase) return 0;
2719 
2720  if ((!address /* || !has_virtual_base */) &&
2721  (!HasInterpreterInfoInMemory() || !toBase->HasInterpreterInfoInMemory())) {
2722  // At least of the ClassInfo have not been loaded in memory yet and
2723  // since there is no virtual base class (or we don't have enough so it
2724  // would not make a difference) we can use the 'static' information
2725  Int_t offset = GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse (toBase);
2726  if (offset != -2) {
2727  return offset;
2728  }
2729  return offset;
2730  }
2731 
2732  ClassInfo_t* derived = GetClassInfo();
2733  ClassInfo_t* base = toBase->GetClassInfo();
2734  if(derived && base) {
2735  // TClingClassInfo::GetBaseOffset takes the lock.
2736  return gCling->ClassInfo_GetBaseOffset(derived, base, address, isDerivedObject);
2737  }
2738  else {
2739  Int_t offset = GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse (toBase);
2740  if (offset != -2) {
2741  return offset;
2742  }
2743  }
2744  return -1;
2745 }
2746 
2747 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2748 /// Return pointer to (base) class that contains datamember.
2749 
2750 TClass *TClass::GetBaseDataMember(const char *datamember)
2751 {
2752  if (!HasDataMemberInfo()) return 0;
2753 
2754  // Check if data member exists in class itself
2755  TDataMember *dm = GetDataMember(datamember);
2756  if (dm) return this;
2757 
2758  // if datamember not found in class, search in next base classes
2759  TBaseClass *inh;
2760  TIter next(GetListOfBases());
2761  while ((inh = (TBaseClass *) next())) {
2762  TClass *c = inh->GetClassPointer();
2763  if (c) {
2764  TClass *cdm = c->GetBaseDataMember(datamember);
2765  if (cdm) return cdm;
2766  }
2767  }
2768 
2769  return 0;
2770 }
2771 
2772 namespace {
2773  // A local Helper class used to keep 2 pointer (the collection proxy
2774  // and the class streamer) in the thread local storage.
2775 
2776  struct TClassLocalStorage {
2777  TClassLocalStorage() : fCollectionProxy(0), fStreamer(0) {};
2778 
2779  TVirtualCollectionProxy *fCollectionProxy;
2780  TClassStreamer *fStreamer;
2781 
2782  static TClassLocalStorage *GetStorage(const TClass *cl)
2783  {
2784  // Return the thread storage for the TClass.
2785 
2786  void **thread_ptr = (*gThreadTsd)(0,ROOT::kClassThreadSlot);
2787  if (thread_ptr) {
2788  if (*thread_ptr==0) *thread_ptr = new TExMap();
2789  TExMap *lmap = (TExMap*)(*thread_ptr);
2790  ULong_t hash = TString::Hash(&cl, sizeof(void*));
2791  ULong_t local = 0;
2792  UInt_t slot;
2793  if ((local = (ULong_t)lmap->GetValue(hash, (Long_t)cl, slot)) != 0) {
2794  } else {
2795  local = (ULong_t) new TClassLocalStorage();
2796  lmap->AddAt(slot, hash, (Long_t)cl, local);
2797  }
2798  return (TClassLocalStorage*)local;
2799  }
2800  return 0;
2801  }
2802  };
2803 }

2805 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2806 /// Return the 'type' of the STL the TClass is representing.
2807 /// and return ROOT::kNotSTL if it is not representing an STL collection.
2808 
2809 ROOT::ESTLType TClass::GetCollectionType() const
2810 {
2811  auto proxy = GetCollectionProxy();
2812  if (proxy) return (ROOT::ESTLType)proxy->GetCollectionType();
2813  return ROOT::kNotSTL;
2814 }

2817 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2818 /// Return the proxy describing the collection (if any).
2819 
2820 TVirtualCollectionProxy *TClass::GetCollectionProxy() const
2821 {
2822  // Use assert, so that this line (slow because of the TClassEdit) is completely
2823  // removed in optimized code.
2824  assert(TestBit(kLoading) || !TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(fName) || fCollectionProxy || 0 == "The TClass for the STL collection has no collection proxy!");
2825  if (gThreadTsd && fCollectionProxy) {
2826  TClassLocalStorage *local = TClassLocalStorage::GetStorage(this);
2827  if (local == 0) return fCollectionProxy;
2828  if (local->fCollectionProxy==0) local->fCollectionProxy = fCollectionProxy->Generate();
2829  return local->fCollectionProxy;
2830  }
2831  return fCollectionProxy;
2832 }
2833 
2834 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2835 /// Return the Streamer Class allowing streaming (if any).
2836 
2837 TClassStreamer *TClass::GetStreamer() const
2838 {
2839  if (gThreadTsd && fStreamer) {
2840  TClassLocalStorage *local = TClassLocalStorage::GetStorage(this);
2841  if (local==0) return fStreamer;
2842  if (local->fStreamer==0) {
2843  local->fStreamer = fStreamer->Generate();
2844  const std::type_info &orig = ( typeid(*fStreamer) );
2845  if (!local->fStreamer) {
2846  Warning("GetStreamer","For %s, the TClassStreamer (%s) passed's call to Generate failed!",GetName(),orig.name());
2847  } else {
2848  const std::type_info &copy = ( typeid(*local->fStreamer) );
2849  if (strcmp(orig.name(),copy.name())!=0) {
2850  Warning("GetStreamer","For %s, the TClassStreamer passed does not properly implement the Generate method (%s vs %s)\n",GetName(),orig.name(),copy.name());
2851  }
2852  }
2853  }
2854  return local->fStreamer;
2855  }
2856  return fStreamer;
2857 }

2878 TVirtualIsAProxy* TClass::GetIsAProxy() const

2882 
2883 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2884 /// Static method returning pointer to TClass of the specified class name.
2885 /// If load is true an attempt is made to obtain the class by loading
2886 /// the appropriate shared library (directed by the rootmap file).
2887 /// If silent is 'true', do not warn about missing dictionary for the class.
2888 /// (typically used for class that are used only for transient members)
2889 /// Returns 0 in case class is not found.
2890 
2891 TClass *TClass::GetClass(const char *name, Bool_t load, Bool_t silent)
2892 {
2893  if (!name || !name[0]) return 0;
2894 
2895  if (strstr(name, "(anonymous)")) return 0;
2896  if (strncmp(name,"class ",6)==0) name += 6;
2897  if (strncmp(name,"struct ",7)==0) name += 7;
2898 
2899  if (!gROOT->GetListOfClasses()) return 0;
2900 
2901  // FindObject will take the read lock before actually getting the
2902  // TClass pointer so we will need not get a partially initialized
2903  // object.
2904  TClass *cl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(name);
2905 
2906  // Early return to release the lock without having to execute the
2907  // long-ish normalization.
2908  if (cl && (cl->IsLoaded() || cl->TestBit(kUnloading))) return cl;
2909 
2910  R__WRITE_LOCKGUARD(ROOT::gCoreMutex);
2911 
2912  // Now that we got the write lock, another thread may have constructed the
2913  // TClass while we were waiting, so we need to do the checks again.
2914 
2915  cl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(name);
2916  if (cl) {
2917  if (cl->IsLoaded() || cl->TestBit(kUnloading)) return cl;
2918 
2919  // We could speed-up some of the search by adding (the equivalent of)
2920  //
2921  // if (cl->GetState() == kInterpreter) return cl
2922  //
2923  // In this case, if a ROOT dictionary was available when the TClass
2924  // was first requested it would have been used and if a ROOT dictionary is
2925  // loaded later on TClassTable::Add will take care of updating the TClass.
2926  // So as far as ROOT dictionary are concerned, if the current TClass is
2927  // in interpreted state, we are sure there is nothing to load.
2928  //
2929  // However (see TROOT::LoadClass), the TClass can also be loaded/provided
2930  // by a user provided TClassGenerator. We have no way of knowing whether
2931  // those do (or even can) behave the same way as the ROOT dictionary and
2932  // have the 'dictionary is now available for use' step informs the existing
2933  // TClass that their dictionary is now available.
2934 
2935  //we may pass here in case of a dummy class created by TVirtualStreamerInfo
2936  load = kTRUE;
2937  }
2938 
2939  // To avoid spurious auto parsing, let's check if the name as-is is
2940  // known in the TClassTable.
2941  DictFuncPtr_t dict = TClassTable::GetDictNorm(name);
2942  if (dict) {
2943  // The name is normalized, so the result of the first search is
2944  // authoritative.
2945  if (!cl && !load) return 0;
2946 
2947  TClass *loadedcl = (dict)();
2948  if (loadedcl) {
2949  loadedcl->PostLoadCheck();
2950  return loadedcl;
2951  }
2952 
2953  // We should really not fall through to here, but if we do, let's just
2954  // continue as before ...
2955  }
2956 
2957  std::string normalizedName;
2958  Bool_t checkTable = kFALSE;
2959 
2960  if (!cl) {
2961  {
2962  TInterpreter::SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoloadOff(gInterpreter);
2963  TClassEdit::GetNormalizedName(normalizedName, name);
2964  }
2965  // Try the normalized name.
2966  if (normalizedName != name) {
2967  cl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(normalizedName.c_str());
2968 
2969  if (cl) {
2970  if (cl->IsLoaded() || cl->TestBit(kUnloading)) return cl;
2971 
2972  //we may pass here in case of a dummy class created by TVirtualStreamerInfo
2973  load = kTRUE;
2974  }
2975  checkTable = kTRUE;
2976  }
2977  } else {
2978  normalizedName = cl->GetName(); // Use the fact that all TClass names are normalized.
2979  checkTable = load && (normalizedName != name);
2980  }
2981 
2982  if (!load) return 0;
2983 
2984 // This assertion currently fails because of
2985 // TClass *c1 = TClass::GetClass("basic_iostream<char,char_traits<char> >");
2986 // TClass *c2 = TClass::GetClass("std::iostream");
2987 // where the TClassEdit normalized name of iostream is basic_iostream<char>
2988 // i.e missing the addition of the default parameter. This is because TClingLookupHelper
2989 // uses only 'part' of TMetaUtils::GetNormalizedName.
2990 
2991 // if (!cl) {
2992 // TDataType* dataType = (TDataType*)gROOT->GetListOfTypes()->FindObject(name);
2993 // TClass *altcl = dataType ? (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(dataType->GetFullTypeName()) : 0;
2994 // if (altcl && normalizedName != altcl->GetName())
2995 // ::Fatal("TClass::GetClass","The existing name (%s) for %s is different from the normalized name: %s\n",
2996 // altcl->GetName(), name, normalizedName.c_str());
2997 // }
2998 
2999  TClass *loadedcl = 0;
3000  if (checkTable) {
3001  loadedcl = LoadClassDefault(normalizedName.c_str(),silent);
3002  } else {
3003  if (gInterpreter->AutoLoad(normalizedName.c_str(),kTRUE)) {
3004  loadedcl = LoadClassDefault(normalizedName.c_str(),silent);
3005  }
3006  // Maybe this was a typedef: let's try to see if this is the case
3007  if (!loadedcl){
3008  if (TDataType* theDataType = gROOT->GetType(normalizedName.c_str())){
3009  // We have a typedef: we get the name of the underlying type
3010  auto underlyingTypeName = theDataType->GetTypeName();
3011  // We see if we can bootstrap a class with it
3012  auto underlyingTypeDict = TClassTable::GetDictNorm(underlyingTypeName.Data());
3013  if (underlyingTypeDict){
3014  loadedcl = underlyingTypeDict();
3015  }
3016 
3017  }
3018  }
3019  }
3020  if (loadedcl) return loadedcl;
3021 
3022  // See if the TClassGenerator can produce the TClass we need.
3023  loadedcl = LoadClassCustom(normalizedName.c_str(),silent);
3024  if (loadedcl) return loadedcl;
3025 
3026  // We have not been able to find a loaded TClass, return the Emulated
3027  // TClass if we have one.
3028  if (cl) return cl;
3029 
3030  if (TClassEdit::IsSTLCont( normalizedName.c_str() )) {
3031 
3032  return gInterpreter->GenerateTClass(normalizedName.c_str(), kTRUE, silent);
3033  }
3034 
3035  // Check the interpreter only after autoparsing the template if any.
3036  {
3037  std::string::size_type posLess = normalizedName.find('<');
3038  if (posLess != std::string::npos) {
3039  gCling->AutoParse(normalizedName.substr(0, posLess).c_str());
3040  }
3041  }
3042 
3043  //last attempt. Look in CINT list of all (compiled+interpreted) classes
3044  if (gDebug>0){
3045  printf("TClass::GetClass: Header Parsing - The representation of %s was not found in the type system. A lookup in the interpreter is about to be tried: this can cause parsing. This can be avoided selecting %s in the linkdef/selection file.\n",normalizedName.c_str(), normalizedName.c_str());
3046  }
3047  if (normalizedName.length()) {
3048  auto cci = gInterpreter->CheckClassInfo(normalizedName.c_str(), kTRUE /* autoload */,
3049  kTRUE /*Only class, structs and ns*/);
3050 
3051  // We could have an interpreted class with an inline ClassDef, in this case we do not
3052  // want to create an 'interpreted' TClass but we want the one triggered via the call to
3053  // the Dictionary member. If we go ahead and generate the 'interpreted' version it will
3054  // replace if/when there is a call to IsA on an object of this type.
3055 
3056  if (cci == TInterpreter::kWithClassDefInline) {
3057  auto ci = gInterpreter->ClassInfo_Factory(normalizedName.c_str());
3058  auto funcDecl = gInterpreter->GetFunctionWithPrototype(ci, "Dictionary", "", false, ROOT::kExactMatch);
3059  auto method = gInterpreter->MethodInfo_Factory(funcDecl);
3060  typedef void (*tcling_callfunc_Wrapper_t)(void *, int, void **, void *);
3061  auto funcPtr = (tcling_callfunc_Wrapper_t)gInterpreter->MethodInfo_InterfaceMethod(method);
3062 
3063  TClass *res = nullptr;
3064  if (funcPtr)
3065  funcPtr(0, 0, nullptr, &res);
3066  // else
3067  // We could fallback to the interpreted case ...
3068  // For now just 'fail' (return nullptr)
3069 
3070  gInterpreter->MethodInfo_Delete(method);
3071  gInterpreter->ClassInfo_Delete(ci);
3072 
3073  return res;
3074  } else if (cci) {
3075  // Get the normalized name based on the decl (currently the only way
3076  // to get the part to add or drop the default arguments as requested by the user)
3077  std::string alternative;
3078  gInterpreter->GetInterpreterTypeName(normalizedName.c_str(), alternative, kTRUE);
3079  const char *altname = alternative.c_str();
3080  if (strncmp(altname, "std::", 5) == 0) {
3081  // For namespace (for example std::__1), GetInterpreterTypeName does
3082  // not strip std::, so we must do it explicitly here.
3083  altname += 5;
3084  }
3085  if (altname != normalizedName && strcmp(altname, name) != 0) {
3086  // altname now contains the full name of the class including a possible
3087  // namespace if there has been a using namespace statement.
3088 
3089  // At least in the case C<string [2]> (normalized) vs C<string[2]> (altname)
3090  // the TClassEdit normalization and the TMetaUtils normalization leads to
3091  // two different space layout. To avoid an infinite recursion, we also
3092  // add the test on (altname != name)
3093 
3094  return GetClass(altname, load);
3095  }
3096 
3097  TClass *ncl = gInterpreter->GenerateTClass(normalizedName.c_str(), /* emulation = */ kFALSE, silent);
3098  if (!ncl->IsZombie()) {
3099  return ncl;
3100  }
3101  delete ncl;
3102  }
3103  }
3104  return nullptr;
3105 }

3107 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3108 /// Return pointer to class with name.
3109 
3110 TClass *TClass::GetClass(const std::type_info& typeinfo, Bool_t load, Bool_t /* silent */)
3111 {
3112  if (!gROOT->GetListOfClasses())
3113  return 0;
3114 
3115  //protect access to TROOT::GetIdMap
3116  R__READ_LOCKGUARD(ROOT::gCoreMutex);
3117 
3118  TClass* cl = GetIdMap()->Find(typeinfo.name());
3119 
3120  if (cl && cl->IsLoaded()) return cl;
3121 
3122  R__WRITE_LOCKGUARD(ROOT::gCoreMutex);
3123 
3124  // Now that we got the write lock, another thread may have constructed the
3125  // TClass while we were waiting, so we need to do the checks again.
3126 
3127  cl = GetIdMap()->Find(typeinfo.name());
3128 
3129  if (cl) {
3130  if (cl->IsLoaded()) return cl;
3131  //we may pass here in case of a dummy class created by TVirtualStreamerInfo
3132  load = kTRUE;
3133  } else {
3134  // Note we might need support for typedefs and simple types!
3135 
3136  // TDataType *objType = GetType(name, load);
3137  //if (objType) {
3138  // const char *typdfName = objType->GetTypeName();
3139  // if (typdfName && strcmp(typdfName, name)) {
3140  // cl = GetClass(typdfName, load);
3141  // return cl;
3142  // }
3143  // }
3144  }
3145 
3146  if (!load) return 0;
3147 
3148  DictFuncPtr_t dict = TClassTable::GetDict(typeinfo);
3149  if (dict) {
3150  cl = (dict)();
3151  if (cl) cl->PostLoadCheck();
3152  return cl;
3153  }
3154  if (cl) return cl;
3155 
3156  TIter next(gROOT->GetListOfClassGenerators());
3157  TClassGenerator *gen;
3158  while( (gen = (TClassGenerator*) next()) ) {
3159  cl = gen->GetClass(typeinfo,load);
3160  if (cl) {
3161  cl->PostLoadCheck();
3162  return cl;
3163  }
3164  }
3165 
3166  // try autoloading the typeinfo
3167  int autoload_old = gCling->SetClassAutoloading(1);
3168  if (!autoload_old) {
3169  // Re-disable, we just meant to test
3170  gCling->SetClassAutoloading(0);
3171  }
3172  if (autoload_old && gInterpreter->AutoLoad(typeinfo,kTRUE)) {
3173  // Disable autoload to avoid potential infinite recursion
3174  TInterpreter::SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoloadOff(gInterpreter);
3175  cl = GetClass(typeinfo, load);
3176  if (cl) {
3177  return cl;
3178  }
3179  }
3180 
3181  // last attempt. Look in the interpreter list of all (compiled+interpreted)
3182  // classes
3183  cl = gInterpreter->GetClass(typeinfo, load);
3184 
3185  return cl; // Can be zero.
3186 }

3188 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3189 /// Static method returning pointer to TClass of the specified ClassInfo.
3190 /// If load is true an attempt is made to obtain the class by loading
3191 /// the appropriate shared library (directed by the rootmap file).
3192 /// If silent is 'true', do not warn about missing dictionary for the class.
3193 /// (typically used for class that are used only for transient members)
3194 /// Returns 0 in case class is not found.
3195 
3196 TClass *TClass::GetClass(ClassInfo_t *info, Bool_t load, Bool_t silent)
3197 {
3198  if (!info || !gCling->ClassInfo_IsValid(info)) return 0;
3199  if (!gROOT->GetListOfClasses()) return 0;
3200 
3201  // Technically we need the write lock only for the call to ClassInfo_FullName
3202  // and GenerateTClass but FindObject will take the read lock (and LoadClass will
3203  // take the write lock). Since taking/releasing the lock is expensive, let just
3204  // take the write guard and keep it.
3205  R__WRITE_LOCKGUARD(ROOT::gCoreMutex);
3206 
3207  // Get the normalized name.
3208  TString name( gCling->ClassInfo_FullName(info) );
3209 
3210  TClass *cl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(name);
3211 
3212  if (cl) {
3213  if (cl->IsLoaded()) return cl;
3214 
3215  //we may pass here in case of a dummy class created by TVirtualStreamerInfo
3216  load = kTRUE;
3217 
3218  }
3219 
3220  if (!load) return 0;
3221 
3222  TClass *loadedcl = 0;
3223  if (cl) loadedcl = gROOT->LoadClass(cl->GetName(),silent);
3224  else loadedcl = gROOT->LoadClass(name,silent);
3225 
3226  if (loadedcl) return loadedcl;
3227 
3228  if (cl) return cl; // If we found the class but we already have a dummy class use it.
3229 
3230  // We did not find a proper TClass but we do know (we have a valid
3231  // ClassInfo) that the class is known to the interpreter.
3232  TClass *ncl = gInterpreter->GenerateTClass(info, silent);
3233  if (!ncl->IsZombie()) {
3234  return ncl;
3235  } else {
3236  delete ncl;
3237  return 0;
3238  }
3239 }

3249 Bool_t TClass::GetClass(DeclId_t id, std::vector<TClass*> &classes)
3250 {
3251  if (!gROOT->GetListOfClasses()) return 0;
3252 
3253  DeclIdMap_t* map = GetDeclIdMap();
3254  // Get all the TClass pointer that have the same DeclId.
3255  DeclIdMap_t::equal_range iter = map->Find(id);
3256  if (iter.first == iter.second) return false;
3257  std::vector<TClass*>::iterator vectIt = classes.begin();
3258  for (DeclIdMap_t::const_iterator it = iter.first; it != iter.second; ++it)
3259  vectIt = classes.insert(vectIt, it->second);
3260  return true;
3261 }

3315 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3316 /// return offset for member name. name can be a data member in
3317 /// the class itself, one of its base classes, or one member in
3318 /// one of the aggregated classes.
3319 ///
3320 /// In case of an emulated class, the list of emulated TRealData is built
3321 
3322 Long_t TClass::GetDataMemberOffset(const char *name) const
3323 {
3324  TRealData *rd = GetRealData(name);
3325  if (rd) return rd->GetThisOffset();
3326  if (strchr(name,'[')==0) {
3327  // If this is a simple name there is a chance to find it in the
3328  // StreamerInfo even if we did not find it in the RealData.
3329  // For example an array name would be fArray[3] in RealData but
3330  // just fArray in the streamerInfo.
3331  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = const_cast<TClass*>(this)->GetCurrentStreamerInfo();
3332  if (info) {
3333  return info->GetOffset(name);
3334  }
3335  }
3336  return 0;
3337 }
3338 
3339 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3340 /// Return pointer to TRealData element with name "name".
3341 ///
3342 /// Name can be a data member in the class itself,
3343 /// one of its base classes, or a member in
3344 /// one of the aggregated classes.
3345 ///
3346 /// In case of an emulated class, the list of emulated TRealData is built.
3347 
3348 TRealData* TClass::GetRealData(const char* name) const
3349 {
3350  if (!fRealData) {
3351  const_cast<TClass*>(this)->BuildRealData();
3352  }
3353 
3354  if (!fRealData) {
3355  return 0;
3356  }
3357 
3358  if (!name) {
3359  return 0;
3360  }
3361 
3362  // First try just the whole name.
3363  TRealData* rd = (TRealData*) fRealData->FindObject(name);
3364  if (rd) {
3365  return rd;
3366  }
3367 
3368  std::string givenName(name);
3369 
3370  // Try ignoring the array dimensions.
3371  std::string::size_type firstBracket = givenName.find_first_of("[");
3372  if (firstBracket != std::string::npos) {
3373  // -- We are looking for an array data member.
3374  std::string nameNoDim(givenName.substr(0, firstBracket));
3375  TObjLink* lnk = fRealData->FirstLink();
3376  while (lnk) {
3377  TObject* obj = lnk->GetObject();
3378  std::string objName(obj->GetName());
3379  std::string::size_type pos = objName.find_first_of("[");
3380  // Only match arrays to arrays for now.
3381  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
3382  objName.erase(pos);
3383  if (objName == nameNoDim) {
3384  return static_cast<TRealData*>(obj);
3385  }
3386  }
3387  lnk = lnk->Next();
3388  }
3389  }
3390 
3391  // Now try it as a pointer.
3392  std::ostringstream ptrname;
3393  ptrname << "*" << givenName;
3394  rd = (TRealData*) fRealData->FindObject(ptrname.str().c_str());
3395  if (rd) {
3396  return rd;
3397  }
3398 
3399  // Check for a dot in the name.
3400  std::string::size_type firstDot = givenName.find_first_of(".");
3401  if (firstDot == std::string::npos) {
3402  // -- Not found, a simple name, all done.
3403  return 0;
3404  }
3405 
3406  //
3407  // At this point the name has a dot in it, so it is the name
3408  // of some contained sub-object.
3409  //
3410 
3411  // May be a pointer like in TH1: fXaxis.fLabels (in TRealdata is named fXaxis.*fLabels)
3412  std::string::size_type lastDot = givenName.find_last_of(".");
3413  std::ostringstream starname;
3414  starname << givenName.substr(0, lastDot) << ".*" << givenName.substr(lastDot + 1);
3415  rd = (TRealData*) fRealData->FindObject(starname.str().c_str());
3416  if (rd) {
3417  return rd;
3418  }
3419 
3420  // Strip the first component, it may be the name of
3421  // the branch (old TBranchElement code), and try again.
3422  std::string firstDotName(givenName.substr(firstDot + 1));
3423 
3424  // New attempt starting after the first "." if any,
3425  // this allows for the case that the first component
3426  // may have been a branch name (for TBranchElement).
3427  rd = (TRealData*) fRealData->FindObject(firstDotName.c_str());
3428  if (rd) {
3429  return rd;
3430  }
3431 
3432  // New attempt starting after the first "." if any,
3433  // but this time try ignoring the array dimensions.
3434  // Again, we are allowing for the case that the first
3435  // component may have been a branch name (for TBranchElement).
3436  std::string::size_type firstDotBracket = firstDotName.find_first_of("[");
3437  if (firstDotBracket != std::string::npos) {
3438  // -- We are looking for an array data member.
3439  std::string nameNoDim(firstDotName.substr(0, firstDotBracket));
3440  TObjLink* lnk = fRealData->FirstLink();
3441  while (lnk) {
3442  TObject* obj = lnk->GetObject();
3443  std::string objName(obj->GetName());
3444  std::string::size_type pos = objName.find_first_of("[");
3445  // Only match arrays to arrays for now.
3446  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
3447  objName.erase(pos);
3448  if (objName == nameNoDim) {
3449  return static_cast<TRealData*>(obj);
3450  }
3451  }
3452  lnk = lnk->Next();
3453  }
3454  }
3455 
3456  // New attempt starting after the first "." if any,
3457  // but this time check for a pointer type. Again, we
3458  // are allowing for the case that the first component
3459  // may have been a branch name (for TBranchElement).
3460  ptrname.str("");
3461  ptrname << "*" << firstDotName;
3462  rd = (TRealData*) fRealData->FindObject(ptrname.str().c_str());
3463  if (rd) {
3464  return rd;
3465  }
3466 
3467  // Last attempt in case a member has been changed from
3468  // a static array to a pointer, for example the member
3469  // was arr[20] and is now *arr.
3470  //
3471  // Note: In principle, one could also take into account
3472  // the opposite situation where a member like *arr has
3473  // been converted to arr[20].
3474  //
3475  // FIXME: What about checking after the first dot as well?
3476  //
3477  std::string::size_type bracket = starname.str().find_first_of("[");
3478  if (bracket == std::string::npos) {
3479  return 0;
3480  }
3481  rd = (TRealData*) fRealData->FindObject(starname.str().substr(0, bracket).c_str());
3482  if (rd) {
3483  return rd;
3484  }
3485 
3486  // Not found;
3487  return 0;
3488 }

3521 TList *TClass::GetListOfBases()

3525  if (fState == kHasTClassInit) {
3526

3528  // NOTE: Add test to prevent redo if another thread has already done the work.
3529  // if (!fHasRootPcmInfo) {
3530

3558 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3559 /// Return a list containing the TEnums of a class.
3560 ///
3561 /// The list returned is safe to use from multiple thread without explicitly
3562 /// taking the ROOT global lock.
3563 ///
3564 /// In the case the TClass represents a namespace, the returned list will
3565 /// implicit take the ROOT global lock upon any access (see TListOfEnumsWithLock)
3566 ///
3567 /// In the case the TClass represents a class or struct and requestListLoading
3568 /// is true, the list is immutable (and thus safe to access from multiple thread
3569 /// without taking the global lock at all).
3570 ///
3571 /// In the case the TClass represents a class or struct and requestListLoading
3572 /// is false, the list is mutable and thus we return a TListOfEnumsWithLock
3573 /// which will implicit take the ROOT global lock upon any access.
3574 
3575 TList *TClass::GetListOfEnums(Bool_t requestListLoading /* = kTRUE */)
3576 {
3577  auto temp = fEnums.load();
3578  if (temp) {
3579  if (requestListLoading) {
3580  if (fProperty == -1) Property();
3581  if (! ((kIsClass | kIsStruct | kIsUnion) & fProperty) ) {
3582  R__LOCKGUARD(gROOTMutex);
3583  temp->Load();
3584  } else if ( temp->IsA() == TListOfEnumsWithLock::Class() ) {
3585  // We have a class for which the list was not loaded fully at
3586  // first use.
3587  R__LOCKGUARD(gROOTMutex);
3588  temp->Load();
3589  }
3590  }
3591  return temp;
3592  }
3593 
3594  if (!requestListLoading) {
3595  if (fProperty == -1) Property();
3596  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3597  if (fEnums.load()) {
3598  return fEnums.load();
3599  }
3600 
3601  static bool fromRootCling = dlsym(RTLD_DEFAULT, "usedToIdentifyRootClingByDlSym");
3602 
3603  if (fromRootCling) // rootcling is single thread (this save some space in the rootpcm).
3604  fEnums = new TListOfEnums(this);
3605  else
3606  fEnums = new TListOfEnumsWithLock(this);
3607  return fEnums;
3608  }
3609 
3610  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3611  if (fEnums.load()) {
3612  (*fEnums).Load();
3613  return fEnums.load();
3614  }
3615  if (fProperty == -1) Property();
3616  if ( (kIsClass | kIsStruct | kIsUnion) & fProperty) {
3617  // For this case, the list will be immutable
3618  temp = new TListOfEnums(this);
3619  } else {
3620  //namespaces can have enums added to them
3621  temp = new TListOfEnumsWithLock(this);
3622  }
3623  temp->Load();
3624  fEnums = temp;
3625  return temp;
3626 }

3628 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3629 /// Return list containing the TDataMembers of a class.
3630 
3631 TList *TClass::GetListOfDataMembers(Bool_t load /* = kTRUE */)
3632 {
3633  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3634 
3635  if (!fData) {
3636  if (fCanLoadClassInfo && fState == kHasTClassInit) {
3637  // NOTE: Add test to prevent redo if another thread has already done the work.
3638  // if (!fHasRootPcmInfo) {
3639 
3640  // The members are in our ProtoClass; we don't need the class info.
3641  TProtoClass *proto = TClassTable::GetProtoNorm(GetName());
3642  if (proto && proto->FillTClass(this)) {
3643  // Not sure this code is still needed
3644  // R__ASSERT(kFALSE);
3645 
3646  fHasRootPcmInfo = kTRUE;
3647  return fData;
3648  }
3649  }
3650  fData = new TListOfDataMembers(this);
3651  }
3652  if (Property() & (kIsClass|kIsStruct|kIsUnion)) {
3653  // If the we have a class or struct or union, the order
3654  // of data members is the list is essential since it determines their
3655  // order on file. So we must always load. Also, the list is fixed
3656  // since the language does not allow to add members.
3657  if (!fData->IsLoaded()) fData->Load();
3658 
3659  } else if (load) fData->Load();
3660  return fData;
3661 }

3701 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3702 /// Returns a list of all public methods of this class and its base classes.
3703 /// Refers to a subset of the methods in GetListOfMethods() so don't do
3704 /// GetListOfAllPublicMethods()->Delete().
3705 /// Algorithm used to get the list is:
3706 /// - put all methods of the class in the list (also protected and private
3707 /// ones).
3708 /// - loop over all base classes and add only those methods not already in the
3709 /// list (also protected and private ones).
3710 /// - once finished, loop over resulting list and remove all private and
3711 /// protected methods.
3712 
3713 const TList *TClass::GetListOfAllPublicMethods(Bool_t load /* = kTRUE */)
3714 {
3715  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3716 
3717  if (!fAllPubMethod) fAllPubMethod = new TViewPubFunctions(this);
3718  if (load) {
3719  if (gDebug>0) Info("GetListOfAllPublicMethods","Header Parsing - Asking for all the methods of class %s: this can involve parsing.",GetName());
3720  fAllPubMethod->Load();
3721  }
3722  return fAllPubMethod;
3723 }

3725 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3726 /// Returns a list of all public data members of this class and its base
3727 /// classes. Refers to a subset of the data members in GetListOfDatamembers()
3728 /// so don't do GetListOfAllPublicDataMembers()->Delete().
3729 
3730 TList *TClass::GetListOfAllPublicDataMembers(Bool_t load /* = kTRUE */)
3731 {
3732  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3733 
3734  if (!fAllPubData) fAllPubData = new TViewPubDataMembers(this);
3735  if (load) fAllPubData->Load();
3736  return fAllPubData;
3737 }

3739 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3740 /// Returns list of methods accessible by context menu.
3741 
3742 void TClass::GetMenuItems(TList *list)
3743 {
3744  if (!HasInterpreterInfo()) return;
3745 
3746  // get the base class
3747  TIter nextBase(GetListOfBases(), kIterBackward);
3748  TBaseClass *baseClass;
3749  while ((baseClass = (TBaseClass *) nextBase())) {
3750  TClass *base = baseClass->GetClassPointer();
3751  if (base) base->GetMenuItems(list);
3752  }
3753 
3754  // remove methods redefined in this class with no menu
3755  TMethod *method, *m;
3756  TIter next(GetListOfMethods(), kIterBackward);
3757  while ((method = (TMethod*)next())) {
3758  m = (TMethod*)list->FindObject(method->GetName());
3759  if (method->IsMenuItem() != kMenuNoMenu) {
3760  if (!m)
3761  list->AddFirst(method);
3762  } else {
3763  if (m && m->GetNargs() == method->GetNargs())
3764  list->Remove(m);
3765  }
3766  }
3767 }

3792 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3793 /// Verify the base classes always.
3794 
3795 void TClass::GetMissingDictionariesForBaseClasses(TCollection& result, TCollection& visited, bool recurse)
3796 {
3797  TList* lb = GetListOfBases();
3798  if (!lb) return;
3799  TIter nextBase(lb);
3800  TBaseClass* base = 0;
3801  while ((base = (TBaseClass*)nextBase())) {
3802  TClass* baseCl = base->GetClassPointer();
3803  if (baseCl) {
3804  baseCl->GetMissingDictionariesWithRecursionCheck(result, visited, recurse);
3805  }
3806  }
3807 }
3808 
3809 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3810 /// Verify the Data Members.
3811 
3812 void TClass::GetMissingDictionariesForMembers(TCollection& result, TCollection& visited, bool recurse)
3813 {
3814  TListOfDataMembers* ldm = (TListOfDataMembers*)GetListOfDataMembers();
3815  if (!ldm) return ;
3816  TIter nextMemb(ldm);
3817  TDataMember * dm = 0;
3818  while ((dm = (TDataMember*)nextMemb())) {
3819  // If it is a transient
3820  if(!dm->IsPersistent()) {
3821  continue;
3822  }
3823  if (dm->Property() & kIsStatic) {
3824  continue;
3825  }
3826  // If it is a built-in data type.
3827  TClass* dmTClass = 0;
3828  if (dm->GetDataType()) {
3829  // We have a basic datatype.
3830  dmTClass = nullptr;
3831  // Otherwise get the string representing the type.
3832  } else if (dm->GetTypeName()) {
3833  dmTClass = TClass::GetClass(dm->GetTypeName());
3834  }
3835  if (dmTClass) {
3836  dmTClass->GetMissingDictionariesWithRecursionCheck(result, visited, recurse);
3837  }
3838  }
3839 }
3840 
3841 void TClass::GetMissingDictionariesForPairElements(TCollection& result, TCollection& visited, bool recurse)
3842 {
3843  // Pair is a special case and we have to check its elements for missing dictionaries
3844  // Pair is a transparent container so we should always look at its.
3845 
3846  TVirtualStreamerInfo *SI = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)this->GetStreamerInfo();
3847  for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
3848  TClass* pairElement = ((TStreamerElement*)SI->GetElements()->At(i))->GetClass();
3849  if (pairElement) {
3850  pairElement->GetMissingDictionariesWithRecursionCheck(result, visited, recurse);
3851  }
3852  }
3853 }
3854 
3855 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3856 /// From the second level of recursion onwards it is different state check.
3857 
3858 void TClass::GetMissingDictionariesWithRecursionCheck(TCollection& result, TCollection& visited, bool recurse)
3859 {
3860  if (result.FindObject(this) || visited.FindObject(this)) return;
3861 
3862  static TClassRef sCIString("string");
3863  if (this == sCIString) return;
3864 
3865  TClassEdit::TSplitType splitType(fName);
3866  if (splitType.IsTemplate()) {
3867  // We now treat special cases:
3868  // - pair
3869  // - unique_ptr
3870  // - array
3871  // - tuple
3872 
3873  // Small helper to get the TClass instance from a classname and recursively
3874  // investigate it
3875  auto checkDicts = [&](const string &clName){
3876  auto cl = TClass::GetClass(clName.c_str());
3877  if (!cl) {
3878  // We try to remove * and const from the type name if any
3879  const auto clNameShortType = TClassEdit::ShortType(clName.c_str(), 1);
3880  cl = TClass::GetClass(clNameShortType.c_str());
3881  }
3882  if (cl && !cl->HasDictionary()) {
3883  cl->GetMissingDictionariesWithRecursionCheck(result, visited, recurse);
3884  }
3885  };
3886 
3887  const auto &elements = splitType.fElements;
3888  const auto &templName = elements[0];
3889 
3890  // Special treatment for pair.
3891  if (templName == "pair") {
3892  GetMissingDictionariesForPairElements(result, visited, recurse);
3893  return;
3894  }
3895 
3896  // Special treatment of unique_ptr or array
3897  // They are treated together since they have 1 single template argument
3898  // which is interesting when checking for missing dictionaries.
3899  if (templName == "unique_ptr" || templName == "array") {
3900  checkDicts(elements[1]);
3901  return;
3902  }
3903 
3904  // Special treatment of tuple
3905  // This type must be treated separately since it can have N template
3906  // arguments which are interesting, unlike unique_ptr or array.
3907  if (templName == "tuple") {
3908  // -1 because the elements end with a list of the "stars", i.e. number of
3909  // * after the type name
3910  const auto nTemplArgs = elements.size() - 1;
3911  // loop starts at 1 because the first element is the template name
3912  for (auto iTemplArg = 1U; iTemplArg < nTemplArgs; ++iTemplArg) {
3913  checkDicts(elements[iTemplArg]);
3914  }
3915  return;
3916  }
3917  } // this is not a template
3918 
3919  if (!HasDictionary()) {
3920  result.Add(this);
3921  }
3922 
3923  visited.Add(this);
3924  //Check whether a custom streamer
3925  if (!TestBit(TClass::kHasCustomStreamerMember)) {
3926  if (GetCollectionProxy()) {
3927  // We need to look at the collection's content
3928  // The collection has different kind of elements the check would be required.
3929  TClass* t = 0;
3930  if ((t = GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass())) {
3931  if (!t->HasDictionary()) {
3932  t->GetMissingDictionariesWithRecursionCheck(result, visited, recurse);
3933  }
3934  }
3935  } else {
3936  if (recurse) {
3937  GetMissingDictionariesForMembers(result, visited, recurse);
3938  }
3939  GetMissingDictionariesForBaseClasses(result, visited, recurse);
3940  }
3941  }
3942 }
3943 
3944 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3945 /// Get the classes that have a missing dictionary starting from this one.
3946 /// - With recurse = false the classes checked for missing dictionaries are:
3947 /// the class itself, all base classes, direct data members,
3948 /// and for collection proxies the container's
3949 /// elements without iterating over the element's data members;
3950 /// - With recurse = true the classes checked for missing dictionaries are:
3951 /// the class itself, all base classes, recursing on the data members,
3952 /// and for the collection proxies recursion on the elements of the
3953 /// collection and iterating over the element's data members.
3954 
3955 void TClass::GetMissingDictionaries(THashTable& result, bool recurse)
3956 {
3957  // Top level recursion it different from the following levels of recursion.
3958 
3959  if (result.FindObject(this)) return;
3960 
3961  static TClassRef sCIString("string");
3962  if (this == sCIString) return;
3963 
3964  THashTable visited;
3965 
3966  if (strncmp(fName, "pair<", 5) == 0) {
3967  GetMissingDictionariesForPairElements(result, visited, recurse);
3968  return;
3969  }
3970 
3971  if (!HasDictionary()) {
3972  result.Add(this);
3973  }
3974 
3975  visited.Add(this);
3976 
3977  //Check whether a custom streamer
3978  if (!TestBit(TClass::kHasCustomStreamerMember)) {
3979  if (GetCollectionProxy()) {
3980  // We need to look at the collection's content
3981  // The collection has different kind of elements the check would be required.
3982  TClass* t = 0;
3983  if ((t = GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass())) {
3984  if (!t->HasDictionary()) {
3985  t->GetMissingDictionariesWithRecursionCheck(result, visited, recurse);
3986  }
3987  }
3988  } else {
3989  GetMissingDictionariesForMembers(result, visited, recurse);
3990  GetMissingDictionariesForBaseClasses(result, visited, recurse);
3991  }
3992  }
3993 }

4003 //______________________________________________________________________________
4004 //______________________________________________________________________________
4005 void TClass::ReplaceWith(TClass *newcl) const
4006 {
4007  // Inform the other objects to replace this object by the new TClass (newcl)
4008 
4009  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4010  //we must update the class pointers pointing to 'this' in all TStreamerElements
4011  TIter nextClass(gROOT->GetListOfClasses());
4012  TClass *acl;
4013  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info;
4014  TList tobedeleted;
4015 
4016  // Since we are in the process of replacing a TClass by a TClass
4017  // coming from a dictionary, there is no point in loading any
4018  // libraries during this search.
4019  TInterpreter::SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoloadOff(gInterpreter);
4020  while ((acl = (TClass*)nextClass())) {
4021  if (acl == newcl) continue;
4022 
4023  TIter nextInfo(acl->GetStreamerInfos());
4024  while ((info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)nextInfo())) {
4025 
4026  info->Update(this, newcl);
4027  }
4028 
4029  if (acl->GetCollectionProxy()) {
4030  acl->GetCollectionProxy()->UpdateValueClass(this, newcl);
4031  }
4032  // We should also inform all the TBranchElement :( but we do not have a master list :(
4033  }
4034 
4035  TIter delIter( &tobedeleted );
4036  while ((acl = (TClass*)delIter())) {
4037  delete acl;
4038  }
4039  gInterpreter->UnRegisterTClassUpdate(this);
4040 }

4048 }

4050 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4051 /// Make sure that the current ClassInfo is up to date.
4052 
4053 void TClass::ResetClassInfo()
4054 {
4055  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4056 
4057  InsertTClassInRegistryRAII insertRAII(fState,fName,fNoInfoOrEmuOrFwdDeclNameRegistry);
4058 
4059  if (fClassInfo) {
4060  TClass::RemoveClassDeclId(gInterpreter->GetDeclId(fClassInfo));
4061  gInterpreter->ClassInfo_Delete(fClassInfo);
4062  fClassInfo = 0;
4063  }
4064  // We can not check at this point whether after the unload there will
4065  // still be interpreter information about this class (as v5 was doing),
4066  // instead this function must only be called if the definition is (about)
4067  // to be unloaded.
4068 
4069  ResetCaches();
4070 
4071  // We got here because the definition Decl is about to be unloaded.
4072  if (fState != TClass::kHasTClassInit) {
4073  if (fStreamerInfo->GetEntries() != 0) {
4074  fState = TClass::kEmulated;
4075  } else {
4076  fState = TClass::kForwardDeclared;
4077  }
4078  } else {
4079  // if the ClassInfo was loaded for a class with a TClass Init and it
4080  // gets unloaded, should we guess it can be reloaded?
4081  fCanLoadClassInfo = kTRUE;
4082  }
4083 }

4085 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4086 /// To clean out all caches.
4087 
4088 void TClass::ResetCaches()
4089 {
4090  R__ASSERT(!TestBit(kLoading) && "Resetting the caches does not make sense during loading!" );
4091 
4092  // Not owning lists, don't call Delete(), but unload
4093  if (fData)
4094  fData->Unload();
4095  if (fEnums.load())
4096  (*fEnums).Unload();
4097  if (fMethod.load())
4098  (*fMethod).Unload();
4099 
4100  delete fAllPubData; fAllPubData = 0;
4101 
4102  if (fBase.load())
4103  (*fBase).Delete();
4104  delete fBase.load(); fBase = 0;
4105 
4106  if (fRealData)
4107  fRealData->Delete();
4108  delete fRealData; fRealData=0;
4109 }

4123 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4124 /// The ls function lists the contents of a class on stdout. Ls output
4125 /// is typically much less verbose then Dump().
4126 /// If options contains 'streamerinfo', run ls on the list of streamerInfos
4127 /// and the list of conversion streamerInfos.
4128 
4129 void TClass::ls(Option_t *options) const
4130 {
4131  TNamed::ls(options);
4132  if (options==0 || options[0]==0) return;
4133 
4134  if (strstr(options,"streamerinfo")!=0) {
4135  GetStreamerInfos()->ls(options);
4136 
4137  if (fConversionStreamerInfo.load()) {
4138  std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>::iterator it;
4139  std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>::iterator end = (*fConversionStreamerInfo).end();
4140  for( it = (*fConversionStreamerInfo).begin(); it != end; ++it ) {
4141  it->second->ls(options);
4142  }
4143  }
4144  }
4145 }

4147 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4148 /// Makes a customizable version of the popup menu list, i.e. makes a list
4149 /// of TClassMenuItem objects of methods accessible by context menu.
4150 /// The standard (and different) way consists in having just one element
4151 /// in this list, corresponding to the whole standard list.
4152 /// Once the customizable version is done, one can remove or add elements.
4153 
4154 void TClass::MakeCustomMenuList()
4155 {
4156  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4157  TClassMenuItem *menuItem;
4158 
4159  // Make sure fClassMenuList is initialized and empty.
4160  GetMenuList()->Delete();
4161 
4162  TList* methodList = new TList;
4163  GetMenuItems(methodList);
4164 
4165  TMethod *method;
4166  TMethodArg *methodArg;
4167  TClass *classPtr = 0;
4168  TIter next(methodList);
4169 
4170  while ((method = (TMethod*) next())) {
4171  // if go to a mother class method, add separator
4172  if (classPtr != method->GetClass()) {
4173  menuItem = new TClassMenuItem(TClassMenuItem::kPopupSeparator, this);
4174  fClassMenuList->AddLast(menuItem);
4175  classPtr = method->GetClass();
4176  }
4177  // Build the signature of the method
4178  TString sig;
4179  TList* margsList = method->GetListOfMethodArgs();
4180  TIter nextarg(margsList);
4181  while ((methodArg = (TMethodArg*)nextarg())) {
4182  sig = sig+","+methodArg->GetFullTypeName();
4183  }
4184  if (sig.Length()!=0) sig.Remove(0,1); // remove first comma
4185  menuItem = new TClassMenuItem(TClassMenuItem::kPopupUserFunction, this,
4186  method->GetName(), method->GetName(),0,
4187  sig.Data(),-1,TClassMenuItem::kIsSelf);
4188  if (method->IsMenuItem() == kMenuToggle) menuItem->SetToggle();
4189  fClassMenuList->Add(menuItem);
4190  }
4191  delete methodList;
4192 }

4196 /// 'arenaFrom' to the memory location 'arenaTo'.
4197 
4198 void TClass::Move(void *arenaFrom, void *arenaTo) const
4199 {
4200  // If/when we have access to a copy constructor (or better to a move
4201  // constructor), this function should also perform the data move.
4202  // For now we just information the repository.
4203 
4204  if ((GetState() <= kEmulated) && !fCollectionProxy) {
4205  MoveAddressInRepository("TClass::Move",arenaFrom,arenaTo,this);
4206  }
4207 }

4220 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4221 /// Return (create an empty one if needed) the list of functions.
4222 /// The major difference with GetListOfMethod is that this returns
4223 /// the internal type of fMethod and thus can not be made public.
4224 /// It also never 'loads' the content of the list.
4225 
4226 TListOfFunctions *TClass::GetMethodList()
4227 {
4228  if (!fMethod.load()) {
4229  std::unique_ptr<TListOfFunctions> temp{ new TListOfFunctions(this) };
4230  TListOfFunctions* expected = nullptr;
4231  if(fMethod.compare_exchange_strong(expected, temp.get()) ) {
4232  temp.release();
4233  }
4234  }
4235  return fMethod;
4236 }

4240 /// Return pointer to method without looking at parameters.
4241 /// Does not look in (possible) base classes.
4242 /// Has the side effect of loading all the TMethod object in the list
4243 /// of the class.
4244 
4245 TMethod *TClass::GetMethodAny(const char *method)
4246 {
4247  if (!HasInterpreterInfo()) return 0;
4248  return (TMethod*) GetMethodList()->FindObject(method);
4249 }
4250 
4251 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4252 /// Return pointer to method without looking at parameters.
4253 /// Does look in all base classes.
4254 
4255 TMethod *TClass::GetMethodAllAny(const char *method)
4256 {
4257  if (!HasInterpreterInfo()) return 0;
4258 
4259  TMethod* m = GetMethodAny(method);
4260  if (m) return m;
4261 
4262  TBaseClass *base;
4263  TIter nextb(GetListOfBases());
4264  while ((base = (TBaseClass *) nextb())) {
4265  TClass *c = base->GetClassPointer();
4266  if (c) {
4267  m = c->GetMethodAllAny(method);
4268  if (m) return m;
4269  }
4270  }
4271 
4272  return 0;
4273 }
4274 
4275 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4276 /// Find the best method (if there is one) matching the parameters.
4277 /// The params string must contain argument values, like "3189, \"aap\", 1.3".
4278 /// The function invokes GetClassMethod to search for a possible method
4279 /// in the class itself or in its base classes. Returns 0 in case method
4280 /// is not found.
4281 
4282 TMethod *TClass::GetMethod(const char *method, const char *params,
4283  Bool_t objectIsConst /* = kFALSE */)
4284 {
4285  if (fCanLoadClassInfo) LoadClassInfo();
4286  if (!fClassInfo) return 0;
4287 
4288  if (!gInterpreter)
4289  Fatal("GetMethod", "gInterpreter not initialized");
4290 
4291  TInterpreter::DeclId_t decl = gInterpreter->GetFunctionWithValues(fClassInfo,
4292  method, params,
4293  objectIsConst);
4294 
4295  if (!decl) return 0;
4296 
4297  // search recursively in this class or its base classes
4298  TMethod* f = FindClassOrBaseMethodWithId(decl);
4299  if (f) return f;
4300 
4301  Error("GetMethod",
4302  "\nDid not find matching TMethod <%s> with \"%s\" %sfor %s",
4303  method,params,objectIsConst ? "const " : "", GetName());
4304  return 0;
4305 }
4306 
4307 
4308 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4309 /// Find a method with decl id in this class or its bases.
4310 
4311 TMethod* TClass::FindClassOrBaseMethodWithId(DeclId_t declId) {
4312  if (TFunction* method = GetMethodList()->Get(declId))
4313  return static_cast<TMethod *>(method);
4314 
4315  for (auto item : *GetListOfBases())
4316  if (auto base = static_cast<TBaseClass *>(item)->GetClassPointer())
4317  if (TFunction* method = base->FindClassOrBaseMethodWithId(declId))
4318  return static_cast<TMethod *>(method);
4319 
4320  return nullptr;
4321 }

4325 /// form: "char*,int,double". Returns 0 in case method is not found.
4326 
4327 TMethod *TClass::GetMethodWithPrototype(const char *method, const char *proto,
4328  Bool_t objectIsConst /* = kFALSE */,
4329  ROOT::EFunctionMatchMode mode /* = ROOT::kConversionMatch */)
4330 {

4332  if (!fClassInfo) return 0;
4333

4335  Fatal("GetMethodWithPrototype", "gInterpreter not initialized");
4336

4338  method, proto,
4339  objectIsConst, mode);
4340 
4341  if (!decl) return 0;
4342  TMethod* f = FindClassOrBaseMethodWithId(decl);
4343  if (f) return f;
4344  Error("GetMethodWithPrototype",
4345  "\nDid not find matching TMethod <%s> with \"%s\" %sfor %s",
4346  method,proto,objectIsConst ? "const " : "", GetName());
4347  return 0;
4348 }

4350 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4351 /// Look for a method in this class that has the interface function
4352 /// address faddr.
4353 
4354 TMethod *TClass::GetClassMethod(Long_t faddr)
4355 {
4356  if (!HasInterpreterInfo()) return 0;
4357 
4358  TMethod *m;
4359  TIter next(GetListOfMethods());
4360  while ((m = (TMethod *) next())) {
4361  if (faddr == (Long_t)m->InterfaceMethod())
4362  return m;
4363  }
4364  return 0;
4365 }

4454 
4455 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4456 /// returns a pointer to the TVirtualStreamerInfo object for version
4457 /// If the object does not exist, it is created
4458 ///
4459 /// Note: There are two special version numbers:
4460 ///
4461 /// - 0: Use the class version from the currently loaded class library.
4462 /// - -1: Assume no class library loaded (emulated class).
4463 ///
4464 /// Warning: If we create a new streamer info, whether or not the build
4465 /// optimizes is controlled externally to us by a global variable!
4466 /// Don't call us unless you have set that variable properly
4467 /// with TStreamer::Optimize()!
4468 ///
4469 
4470 TVirtualStreamerInfo* TClass::GetStreamerInfo(Int_t version /* = 0 */) const
4471 {
4472  TVirtualStreamerInfo *sinfo = fLastReadInfo;
4473 
4474  // Version 0 is special, it means the currently loaded version.
4475  // We need to set it at the beginning to be able to guess it correctly.
4476 
4477  if (version == 0)
4478  version = fClassVersion;
4479 
4480  // If the StreamerInfo is assigned to the fLastReadInfo, we are
4481  // guaranteed it was built and compiled.
4482  if (sinfo && sinfo->GetClassVersion() == version)
4483  return sinfo;
4484 
4485  // Note that the access to fClassVersion above is technically not thread-safe with a low probably of problems.
4486  // fClassVersion is not an atomic and is modified TClass::SetClassVersion (called from RootClassVersion via
4487  // ROOT::ResetClassVersion) and is 'somewhat' protected by the atomic fVersionUsed.
4488  // However, direct access to fClassVersion should be replaced by calls to GetClassVersion to set fVersionUsed.
4489  // Even with such a change the code here and in these functions need to be reviewed as a cursory look seem
4490  // to indicates they are not yet properly protection against mutli-thread access.
4491  //
4492  // However, the use of these functions is rare and mostly done at library loading time which should
4493  // in almost all cases preceeds the possibility of GetStreamerInfo being called from multiple thread
4494  // on that same TClass object.
4495  //
4496  // Summary: need careful review but risk of problem is extremely low.
4497 
4498  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4499 
4500  // Warning: version may be -1 for an emulated class, or -2 if the
4501  // user requested the emulated streamerInfo for an abstract
4502  // base class, even though we have a dictionary for it.
4503 
4504  if ((version < -1) || (version >= fStreamerInfo->GetSize())) {
4505  Error("GetStreamerInfo", "class: %s, attempting to access a wrong version: %d", GetName(), version);
4506  // FIXME: Shouldn't we go to -1 here, or better just abort?
4507  version = fClassVersion;
4508  }
4509 
4510  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo *)fStreamerInfo->At(version);
4511 
4512  if (!sinfo && (version != fClassVersion)) {
4513  // When the requested version does not exist we return
4514  // the TVirtualStreamerInfo for the currently loaded class version.
4515  // FIXME: This arguably makes no sense, we should warn and return nothing instead.
4516  // Note: This is done for STL collections
4517  // Note: fClassVersion could be -1 here (for an emulated class).
4518  // This is also the code path take for unversioned classes.
4519  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) fStreamerInfo->At(fClassVersion);
4520  }
4521 
4522  if (!sinfo) {
4523  // We just were not able to find a streamer info, we have to make a new one.
4524  TMmallocDescTemp setreset;
4525  sinfo = TVirtualStreamerInfo::Factory()->NewInfo(const_cast<TClass*>(this));
4526  fStreamerInfo->AddAtAndExpand(sinfo, fClassVersion);
4527  if (gDebug > 0) {
4528  printf("Creating StreamerInfo for class: %s, version: %d\n", GetName(), fClassVersion);
4529  }
4530  if (HasDataMemberInfo() || fCollectionProxy) {
4531  // If we do not have a StreamerInfo for this version and we do not
4532  // have dictionary information nor a proxy, there is nothing to build!
4533  sinfo->Build();
4534  }
4535  } else {
4536  if (!sinfo->IsCompiled()) {
4537  // Streamer info has not been compiled, but exists.
4538  // Therefore it was read in from a file and we have to do schema evolution?
4539  // Or it didn't have a dictionary before, but does now?
4540  sinfo->BuildOld();
4541  }
4542  }
4543 
4544  // Cache the current info if we now have it.
4545  if (version == fClassVersion)
4546  fCurrentInfo = sinfo;
4547 
4548  // If the compilation succeeded, remember this StreamerInfo.
4549  if (sinfo->IsCompiled())
4550  fLastReadInfo = sinfo;
4551 
4552  return sinfo;
4553 }
4554 
4555 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4556 /// For the case where the requestor class is emulated and this class is abstract,
4557 /// returns a pointer to the TVirtualStreamerInfo object for version with an emulated
4558 /// representation whether or not the class is loaded.
4559 ///
4560 /// If the object does not exist, it is created
4561 ///
4562 /// Note: There are two special version numbers:
4563 ///
4564 /// - 0: Use the class version from the currently loaded class library.
4565 /// - -1: Assume no class library loaded (emulated class).
4566 ///
4567 /// Warning: If we create a new streamer info, whether or not the build
4568 /// optimizes is controlled externally to us by a global variable!
4569 /// Don't call us unless you have set that variable properly
4570 /// with TStreamer::Optimize()!
4571 ///
4572 
4573 TVirtualStreamerInfo* TClass::GetStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated(Int_t version /* = 0 */) const
4574 {
4575  TVirtualStreamerInfo *sinfo = nullptr;
4576 
4577  TString newname(GetName());
4578  newname += "@@emulated";
4579 
4580  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4581 
4582  TClass *emulated = TClass::GetClass(newname);
4583 
4584  if (emulated)
4585  sinfo = emulated->GetStreamerInfo(version);
4586 
4587  if (!sinfo) {
4588  // The emulated version of the streamerInfo is explicitly requested and has
4589  // not been built yet.
4590 
4591  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) fStreamerInfo->At(version);
4592 
4593  if (!sinfo && (version != fClassVersion)) {
4594  // When the requested version does not exist we return
4595  // the TVirtualStreamerInfo for the currently loaded class version.
4596  // FIXME: This arguably makes no sense, we should warn and return nothing instead.
4597  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) fStreamerInfo->At(fClassVersion);
4598  }
4599 
4600  if (!sinfo) {
4601  // Let's take the first available StreamerInfo as a start
4602  Int_t ninfos = fStreamerInfo->GetEntriesFast() - 1;
4603  for (Int_t i = -1; sinfo == 0 && i < ninfos; ++i)
4604  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo *)fStreamerInfo->UncheckedAt(i);
4605  }
4606 
4607  if (sinfo) {
4608  sinfo = dynamic_cast<TVirtualStreamerInfo *>(sinfo->Clone());
4609  if (sinfo) {
4610  sinfo->SetClass(0);
4611  sinfo->SetName(newname);
4612  sinfo->BuildCheck();
4613  sinfo->BuildOld();
4614  sinfo->GetClass()->AddRule(TString::Format("sourceClass=%s targetClass=%s",GetName(),newname.Data()));
4615  } else {
4616  Error("GetStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated", "could not create TVirtualStreamerInfo");
4617  }
4618  }
4619  }
4620  return sinfo;
4621 }
4622 
4623 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4624 /// For the case where the requestor class is emulated and this class is abstract,
4625 /// returns a pointer to the TVirtualStreamerInfo object for version with an emulated
4626 /// representation whether or not the class is loaded.
4627 ///
4628 /// If the object does not exist, it is created
4629 ///
4630 /// Warning: If we create a new streamer info, whether or not the build
4631 /// optimizes is controlled externally to us by a global variable!
4632 /// Don't call us unless you have set that variable properly
4633 /// with TStreamer::Optimize()!
4634 ///
4635 
4636 TVirtualStreamerInfo* TClass::FindStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated(UInt_t checksum) const
4637 {
4638  TVirtualStreamerInfo *sinfo = nullptr;
4639 
4640  TString newname(GetName());
4641  newname += "@@emulated";
4642 
4643  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4644 
4645  TClass *emulated = TClass::GetClass(newname);
4646 
4647  if (emulated)
4648  sinfo = emulated->FindStreamerInfo(checksum);
4649 
4650  if (!sinfo) {
4651  // The emulated version of the streamerInfo is explicitly requested and has
4652  // not been built yet.
4653 
4654  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) FindStreamerInfo(checksum);
4655 
4656  if (!sinfo && (checksum != fCheckSum)) {
4657  // When the requested version does not exist we return
4658  // the TVirtualStreamerInfo for the currently loaded class version.
4659  // FIXME: This arguably makes no sense, we should warn and return nothing instead.
4660  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) fStreamerInfo->At(fClassVersion);
4661  }
4662 
4663  if (!sinfo) {
4664  // Let's take the first available StreamerInfo as a start
4665  Int_t ninfos = fStreamerInfo->GetEntriesFast() - 1;
4666  for (Int_t i = -1; sinfo == 0 && i < ninfos; ++i)
4667  sinfo = (TVirtualStreamerInfo *)fStreamerInfo->UncheckedAt(i);
4668  }
4669 
4670  if (sinfo) {
4671  sinfo = dynamic_cast<TVirtualStreamerInfo*>( sinfo->Clone() );
4672  if (sinfo) {
4673  sinfo->SetClass(0);
4674  sinfo->SetName( newname );
4675  sinfo->BuildCheck();
4676  sinfo->BuildOld();
4677  sinfo->GetClass()->AddRule(TString::Format("sourceClass=%s targetClass=%s",GetName(),newname.Data()));
4678  } else {
4679  Error("GetStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated", "could not create TVirtualStreamerInfo");
4680  }
4681  }
4682  }
4683  return sinfo;
4684 }
4685 
4686 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4687 /// When the class kIgnoreTObjectStreamer bit is set, the automatically
4688 /// generated Streamer will not call TObject::Streamer.
4689 /// This option saves the TObject space overhead on the file.
4690 /// However, the information (fBits, fUniqueID) of TObject is lost.
4691 ///
4692 /// Note that to be effective for objects streamed object-wise this function
4693 /// must be called for the class deriving directly from TObject, eg, assuming
4694 /// that BigTrack derives from Track and Track derives from TObject, one must do:
4695 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4696 /// Track::Class()->IgnoreTObjectStreamer();
4697 /// ~~~
4698 /// and not:
4699 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4700 /// BigTrack::Class()->IgnoreTObjectStreamer();
4701 /// ~~~
4702 /// To be effective for object streamed member-wise or split in a TTree,
4703 /// this function must be called for the most derived class (i.e. BigTrack).
4704 
4705 void TClass::IgnoreTObjectStreamer(Bool_t doIgnore)
4706 {
4707  // We need to tak the lock since we are test and then setting fBits
4708  // and TStreamerInfo::fBits (and the StreamerInfo state in general)
4709  // which can also be modified by another thread.
4710  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4711 
4712  if ( doIgnore && TestBit(kIgnoreTObjectStreamer)) return;
4713  if (!doIgnore && !TestBit(kIgnoreTObjectStreamer)) return;
4714  TVirtualStreamerInfo *sinfo = GetCurrentStreamerInfo();
4715  if (sinfo) {
4716  if (sinfo->IsCompiled()) {
4717  // -- Warn the user that what they are doing cannot work.
4718  // Note: The reason is that TVirtualStreamerInfo::Build() examines
4719  // the kIgnoreTObjectStreamer bit and sets the TStreamerElement
4720  // type for the TObject base class streamer element it creates
4721  // to -1 as a flag. Later on the TStreamerInfo::Compile()
4722  // member function sees the flag and does not insert the base
4723  // class element into the compiled streamer info. None of this
4724  // machinery works correctly if we are called after the streamer
4725  // info has already been built and compiled.
4726  Error("IgnoreTObjectStreamer","Must be called before the creation of StreamerInfo");
4727  return;
4728  }
4729  }
4730  if (doIgnore) SetBit (kIgnoreTObjectStreamer);
4731  else ResetBit(kIgnoreTObjectStreamer);
4732 }
4733 
4734 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4735 /// Return kTRUE if this class inherits from a class with name "classname".
4736 /// note that the function returns kTRUE in case classname is the class itself
4737 
4738 Bool_t TClass::InheritsFrom(const char *classname) const
4739 {
4740  if (strcmp(GetName(), classname) == 0) return kTRUE;
4741 
4742  return InheritsFrom(TClass::GetClass(classname,kTRUE,kTRUE));
4743 }
4744 
4745 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4746 /// Return kTRUE if this class inherits from class cl.
4747 /// note that the function returns KTRUE in case cl is the class itself
4748 
4749 Bool_t TClass::InheritsFrom(const TClass *cl) const
4750 {
4751  if (!cl) return kFALSE;
4752  if (cl == this) return kTRUE;
4753 
4754  if (!HasDataMemberInfo()) {
4755  TVirtualStreamerInfo *sinfo = ((TClass *)this)->GetCurrentStreamerInfo();
4756  if (sinfo==0) sinfo = GetStreamerInfo();
4757  TIter next(sinfo->GetElements());
4758  TStreamerElement *element;
4759  while ((element = (TStreamerElement*)next())) {
4760  if (element->IsA() == TStreamerBase::Class()) {
4761  TClass *clbase = element->GetClassPointer();
4762  if (!clbase) return kFALSE; //missing class
4763  if (clbase->InheritsFrom(cl)) return kTRUE;
4764  }
4765  }
4766  return kFALSE;
4767  }
4768  // cast const away (only for member fBase which can be set in GetListOfBases())
4769  if (((TClass *)this)->GetBaseClass(cl)) return kTRUE;
4770  return kFALSE;
4771 }
4772 
4773 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4774 /// Cast obj of this class type up to baseclass cl if up is true.
4775 /// Cast obj of this class type down from baseclass cl if up is false.
4776 /// If this class is not a baseclass of cl return 0, else the pointer
4777 /// to the cl part of this (up) or to this (down).
4778 
4779 void *TClass::DynamicCast(const TClass *cl, void *obj, Bool_t up)
4780 {
4781  if (cl == this) return obj;
4782 
4783  if (!HasDataMemberInfo()) return 0;
4784 
4785  Int_t off;
4786  if ((off = GetBaseClassOffset(cl, obj)) != -1) {
4787  if (up)
4788  return (void*)((Long_t)obj+off);
4789  else
4790  return (void*)((Long_t)obj-off);
4791  }
4792  return 0;
4793 }
4794 
4795 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4796 /// Cast obj of this class type up to baseclass cl if up is true.
4797 /// Cast obj of this class type down from baseclass cl if up is false.
4798 /// If this class is not a baseclass of cl return 0, else the pointer
4799 /// to the cl part of this (up) or to this (down).
4800 
4801 const void *TClass::DynamicCast(const TClass *cl, const void *obj, Bool_t up)
4802 {
4803  return DynamicCast(cl,const_cast<void*>(obj),up);
4804 }
4805 
4806 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4807 /// Return a pointer to a newly allocated object of this class.
4808 /// The class must have a default constructor. For meaning of
4809 /// defConstructor, see TClass::IsCallingNew().
4810 ///
4811 /// If quiet is true, do no issue a message via Error on case
4812 /// of problems, just return 0.
4813 ///
4814 /// The constructor actually called here can be customized by
4815 /// using the rootcint pragma:
4816 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4817 /// #pragma link C++ ioctortype UserClass;
4818 /// ~~~
4819 /// For example, with this pragma and a class named MyClass,
4820 /// this method will called the first of the following 3
4821 /// constructors which exists and is public:
4822 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4823 /// MyClass(UserClass*);
4824 /// MyClass(TRootIOCtor*);
4825 /// MyClass(); // Or a constructor with all its arguments defaulted.
4826 /// ~~~
4827 ///
4828 /// When more than one pragma ioctortype is used, the first seen as priority
4829 /// For example with:
4830 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4831 /// #pragma link C++ ioctortype UserClass1;
4832 /// #pragma link C++ ioctortype UserClass2;
4833 /// ~~~
4834 /// We look in the following order:
4835 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4836 /// MyClass(UserClass1*);
4837 /// MyClass(UserClass2*);
4838 /// MyClass(TRootIOCtor*);
4839 /// MyClass(); // Or a constructor with all its arguments defaulted.
4840 /// ~~~
4841 
4842 void *TClass::New(ENewType defConstructor, Bool_t quiet) const
4843 {
4844  void* p = 0;
4845 
4846  if (fNew) {
4847  // We have the new operator wrapper function,
4848  // so there is a dictionary and it was generated
4849  // by rootcint, so there should be a default
4850  // constructor we can call through the wrapper.
4851  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
4852  p = fNew(0);
4853  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
4854  if (!p && !quiet) {
4855  //Error("New", "cannot create object of class %s version %d", GetName(), fClassVersion);
4856  Error("New", "cannot create object of class %s", GetName());
4857  }
4858  } else if (HasInterpreterInfo()) {
4859  // We have the dictionary but do not have the
4860  // constructor wrapper, so the dictionary was
4861  // not generated by rootcint. Let's try to
4862  // create the object by having the interpreter
4863  // call the new operator, hopefully the class
4864  // library is loaded and there will be a default
4865  // constructor we can call.
4866  // [This is very unlikely to work, but who knows!]
4867  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
4868  p = gCling->ClassInfo_New(GetClassInfo());
4869  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
4870  if (!p && !quiet) {
4871  //Error("New", "cannot create object of class %s version %d", GetName(), fClassVersion);
4872  Error("New", "cannot create object of class %s", GetName());
4873  }
4874  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && fCollectionProxy) {
4875  // There is no dictionary at all, so this is an emulated
4876  // class; however we do have the services of a collection proxy,
4877  // so this is an emulated STL class.
4878  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
4879  p = fCollectionProxy->New();
4880  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
4881  if (!p && !quiet) {
4882  //Error("New", "cannot create object of class %s version %d", GetName(), fClassVersion);
4883  Error("New", "cannot create object of class %s", GetName());
4884  }
4885  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && !fCollectionProxy) {
4886  // There is no dictionary at all and we do not have
4887  // the services of a collection proxy available, so
4888  // use the streamer info to approximate calling a
4889  // constructor (basically we just make sure that the
4890  // pointer data members are null, unless they are marked
4891  // as preallocated with the "->" comment, in which case
4892  // we default-construct an object to point at).
4893 
4894  // Do not register any TObject's that we create
4895  // as a result of creating this object.
4896  // FIXME: Why do we do this?
4897  // FIXME: Partial Answer: Is this because we may never actually deregister them???
4898 
4899  Bool_t statsave = GetObjectStat();
4900  if(statsave) {
4901  SetObjectStat(kFALSE);
4902  }
4903  TVirtualStreamerInfo* sinfo = GetStreamerInfo();
4904  if (!sinfo && !quiet) {
4905  Error("New", "Cannot construct class '%s' version %d, no streamer info available!", GetName(), fClassVersion);
4906  return 0;
4907  }
4908 
4909  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
4910  p = sinfo->New();
4911  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
4912 
4913  // FIXME: Mistake? See note above at the GetObjectStat() call.
4914  // Allow TObject's to be registered again.
4915  if(statsave) {
4916  SetObjectStat(statsave);
4917  }
4918 
4919  // Register the object for special handling in the destructor.
4920  if (p) {
4921  RegisterAddressInRepository("New",p,this);
4922  } else {
4923  Error("New", "Failed to construct class '%s' using streamer info", GetName());
4924  }
4925  } else {
4926  Fatal("New", "This cannot happen!");
4927  }
4928 
4929  return p;
4930 }
