5105 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5106 /// Return a pointer to a newly allocated object of this class.
5107 /// The class must have a default constructor. For meaning of
5108 /// defConstructor, see TClass::IsCallingNew().
5109 
5110 void *TClass::NewArray(Long_t nElements, void *arena, ENewType defConstructor) const
5111 {
5112  void* p = 0;
5113 
5114  if (fNewArray) {
5115  // We have the new operator wrapper function,
5116  // so there is a dictionary and it was generated
5117  // by rootcint, so there should be a default
5118  // constructor we can call through the wrapper.
5119  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
5120  p = fNewArray(nElements, arena);
5121  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
5122  if (!p) {
5123  Error("NewArray with placement", "cannot create object of class %s version %d at address %p", GetName(), fClassVersion, arena);
5124  }
5125  } else if (HasInterpreterInfo()) {
5126  // We have the dictionary but do not have the constructor wrapper,
5127  // so the dictionary was not generated by rootcint (it was made either
5128  // by cint or by some external mechanism). Let's try to create the
5129  // object by having the interpreter call the new operator, either the
5130  // class library is loaded and there is a default constructor we can
5131  // call, or the class is interpreted and we will call the default
5132  // constructor that way, or no default constructor is available and
5133  // we fail.
5134  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
5135  p = gCling->ClassInfo_New(GetClassInfo(),nElements, arena);
5136  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
5137  if (!p) {
5138  Error("NewArray with placement", "cannot create object of class %s version %d at address %p", GetName(), fClassVersion, arena);
5139  }
5140  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && fCollectionProxy) {
5141  // There is no dictionary at all, so this is an emulated
5142  // class; however we do have the services of a collection proxy,
5143  // so this is an emulated STL class.
5144  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
5145  p = fCollectionProxy->NewArray(nElements, arena);
5146  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
5147  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && !fCollectionProxy) {
5148  // There is no dictionary at all and we do not have
5149  // the services of a collection proxy available, so
5150  // use the streamer info to approximate calling a
5151  // constructor (basically we just make sure that the
5152  // pointer data members are null, unless they are marked
5153  // as preallocated with the "->" comment, in which case
5154  // we default-construct an object to point at).
5155 
5156  // ???BUG??? ???WHY???
5157  // Do not register any TObject's that we create
5158  // as a result of creating this object.
5159  Bool_t statsave = GetObjectStat();
5160  if(statsave) {
5161  SetObjectStat(kFALSE);
5162  }
5163 
5164  TVirtualStreamerInfo* sinfo = GetStreamerInfo();
5165  if (!sinfo) {
5166  Error("NewArray with placement", "Cannot construct class '%s' version %d at address %p, no streamer info available!", GetName(), fClassVersion, arena);
5167  return 0;
5168  }
5169 
5170  TClass__GetCallingNew() = defConstructor;
5171  p = sinfo->NewArray(nElements, arena);
5172  TClass__GetCallingNew() = kRealNew;
5173 
5174  // ???BUG???
5175  // Allow TObject's to be registered again.
5176  if(statsave) {
5177  SetObjectStat(statsave);
5178  }
5179 
5180  if (fStreamerType & kEmulatedStreamer) {
5181  // We always register emulated objects, we need to always
5182  // use the streamer info to destroy them.
5183  }
5184 
5185  // Register the object for special handling in the destructor.
5186  if (p) {
5187  RegisterAddressInRepository("TClass::NewArray with placement",p,this);
5188  }
5189  } else {
5190  Error("NewArray with placement", "This cannot happen!");
5191  }
5192 
5193  return p;
5194 }

5196 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5197 /// Explicitly call destructor for object.
5198 
5199 void TClass::Destructor(void *obj, Bool_t dtorOnly)
5200 {
5201  // Do nothing if passed a null pointer.
5202  if (obj == 0) return;
5203 
5204  void* p = obj;
5205 
5206  if (dtorOnly && fDestructor) {
5207  // We have the destructor wrapper, use it.
5208  fDestructor(p);
5209  } else if ((!dtorOnly) && fDelete) {
5210  // We have the delete wrapper, use it.
5211  fDelete(p);
5212  } else if (HasInterpreterInfo()) {
5213  // We have the dictionary but do not have the
5214  // destruct/delete wrapper, so the dictionary was
5215  // not generated by rootcint (it could have been
5216  // created by cint or by some external mechanism).
5217  // Let's have the interpreter call the destructor,
5218  // either the code will be in a loaded library,
5219  // or it will be interpreted, otherwise we fail
5220  // because there is no destructor code at all.
5221  if (dtorOnly) {
5222  gCling->ClassInfo_Destruct(fClassInfo,p);
5223  } else {
5224  gCling->ClassInfo_Delete(fClassInfo,p);
5225  }
5226  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && fCollectionProxy) {
5227  // There is no dictionary at all, so this is an emulated
5228  // class; however we do have the services of a collection proxy,
5229  // so this is an emulated STL class.
5230  fCollectionProxy->Destructor(p, dtorOnly);
5231  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && !fCollectionProxy) {
5232  // There is no dictionary at all and we do not have
5233  // the services of a collection proxy available, so
5234  // use the streamer info to approximate calling a
5235  // destructor.
5236 
5237  Bool_t inRepo = kTRUE;
5238  Bool_t verFound = kFALSE;
5239 
5240  // Was this object allocated through TClass?
5241  std::multiset<Version_t> knownVersions;
5242  R__LOCKGUARD2(gOVRMutex);
5243 
5244  {
5245  RepoCont_t::iterator iter = gObjectVersionRepository.find(p);
5246  if (iter == gObjectVersionRepository.end()) {
5247  // No, it wasn't, skip special version handling.
5248  //Error("Destructor2", "Attempt to delete unregistered object of class '%s' at address %p!", GetName(), p);
5249  inRepo = kFALSE;
5250  } else {
5251  //objVer = iter->second;
5252  for (; (iter != gObjectVersionRepository.end()) && (iter->first == p); ++iter) {
5253  Version_t ver = iter->second.fVersion;
5254  knownVersions.insert(ver);
5255  if (ver == fClassVersion && this == iter->second.fClass) {
5256  verFound = kTRUE;
5257  }
5258  }
5259  }
5260  }
5261 
5262  if (!inRepo || verFound) {
5263  // The object was allocated using code for the same class version
5264  // as is loaded now. We may proceed without worry.
5265  TVirtualStreamerInfo* si = GetStreamerInfo();
5266  if (si) {
5267  si->Destructor(p, dtorOnly);
5268  } else {
5269  Error("Destructor", "No streamer info available for class '%s' version %d at address %p, cannot destruct emulated object!", GetName(), fClassVersion, p);
5270  Error("Destructor", "length of fStreamerInfo is %d", fStreamerInfo->GetSize());
5271  Int_t i = fStreamerInfo->LowerBound();
5272  for (Int_t v = 0; v < fStreamerInfo->GetSize(); ++v, ++i) {
5273  Error("Destructor", "fStreamerInfo->At(%d): %p", i, fStreamerInfo->At(i));
5274  if (fStreamerInfo->At(i) != 0) {
5275  Error("Destructor", "Doing Dump() ...");
5276  ((TVirtualStreamerInfo*)fStreamerInfo->At(i))->Dump();
5277  }
5278  }
5279  }
5280  } else {
5281  // The loaded class version is not the same as the version of the code
5282  // which was used to allocate this object. The best we can do is use
5283  // the TVirtualStreamerInfo to try to free up some of the allocated memory.
5284  Error("Destructor", "Loaded class %s version %d is not registered for addr %p", GetName(), fClassVersion, p);
5285 #if 0
5286  TVirtualStreamerInfo* si = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) fStreamerInfo->At(objVer);
5287  if (si) {
5288  si->Destructor(p, dtorOnly);
5289  } else {
5290  Error("Destructor2", "No streamer info available for class '%s' version %d, cannot destruct object at addr: %p", GetName(), objVer, p);
5291  Error("Destructor2", "length of fStreamerInfo is %d", fStreamerInfo->GetSize());
5292  Int_t i = fStreamerInfo->LowerBound();
5293  for (Int_t v = 0; v < fStreamerInfo->GetSize(); ++v, ++i) {
5294  Error("Destructor2", "fStreamerInfo->At(%d): %p", i, fStreamerInfo->At(i));
5295  if (fStreamerInfo->At(i) != 0) {
5296  // Do some debugging output.
5297  Error("Destructor2", "Doing Dump() ...");
5298  ((TVirtualStreamerInfo*)fStreamerInfo->At(i))->Dump();
5299  }
5300  }
5301  }
5302 #endif
5303  }
5304 
5305  if (inRepo && verFound && p) {
5306  UnregisterAddressInRepository("TClass::Destructor",p,this);
5307  }
5308  } else {
5309  Error("Destructor", "This cannot happen! (class %s)", GetName());
5310  }
5311 }
5312 
5313 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5314 /// Explicitly call operator delete[] for an array.
5315 
5316 void TClass::DeleteArray(void *ary, Bool_t dtorOnly)
5317 {
5318  // Do nothing if passed a null pointer.
5319  if (ary == 0) return;
5320 
5321  // Make a copy of the address.
5322  void* p = ary;
5323 
5324  if (fDeleteArray) {
5325  if (dtorOnly) {
5326  Error("DeleteArray", "Destructor only is not supported!");
5327  } else {
5328  // We have the array delete wrapper, use it.
5329  fDeleteArray(ary);
5330  }
5331  } else if (HasInterpreterInfo()) {
5332  // We have the dictionary but do not have the
5333  // array delete wrapper, so the dictionary was
5334  // not generated by rootcint. Let's try to
5335  // delete the array by having the interpreter
5336  // call the array delete operator, hopefully
5337  // the class library is loaded and there will be
5338  // a destructor we can call.
5339  gCling->ClassInfo_DeleteArray(GetClassInfo(),ary, dtorOnly);
5340  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && fCollectionProxy) {
5341  // There is no dictionary at all, so this is an emulated
5342  // class; however we do have the services of a collection proxy,
5343  // so this is an emulated STL class.
5344  fCollectionProxy->DeleteArray(ary, dtorOnly);
5345  } else if (!HasInterpreterInfo() && !fCollectionProxy) {
5346  // There is no dictionary at all and we do not have
5347  // the services of a collection proxy available, so
5348  // use the streamer info to approximate calling the
5349  // array destructor.
5350 
5351  Bool_t inRepo = kTRUE;
5352  Bool_t verFound = kFALSE;
5353 
5354  // Was this array object allocated through TClass?
5355  std::multiset<Version_t> knownVersions;
5356  {
5357  R__LOCKGUARD2(gOVRMutex);
5358  RepoCont_t::iterator iter = gObjectVersionRepository.find(p);
5359  if (iter == gObjectVersionRepository.end()) {
5360  // No, it wasn't, we cannot know what to do.
5361  //Error("DeleteArray", "Attempt to delete unregistered array object, element type '%s', at address %p!", GetName(), p);
5362  inRepo = kFALSE;
5363  } else {
5364  for (; (iter != gObjectVersionRepository.end()) && (iter->first == p); ++iter) {
5365  Version_t ver = iter->second.fVersion;
5366  knownVersions.insert(ver);
5367  if (ver == fClassVersion && this == iter->second.fClass ) {
5368  verFound = kTRUE;
5369  }
5370  }
5371  }
5372  }
5373 
5374  if (!inRepo || verFound) {
5375  // The object was allocated using code for the same class version
5376  // as is loaded now. We may proceed without worry.
5377  TVirtualStreamerInfo* si = GetStreamerInfo();
5378  if (si) {
5379  si->DeleteArray(ary, dtorOnly);
5380  } else {
5381  Error("DeleteArray", "No streamer info available for class '%s' version %d at address %p, cannot destruct object!", GetName(), fClassVersion, ary);
5382  Error("DeleteArray", "length of fStreamerInfo is %d", fStreamerInfo->GetSize());
5383  Int_t i = fStreamerInfo->LowerBound();
5384  for (Int_t v = 0; v < fStreamerInfo->GetSize(); ++v, ++i) {
5385  Error("DeleteArray", "fStreamerInfo->At(%d): %p", v, fStreamerInfo->At(i));
5386  if (fStreamerInfo->At(i)) {
5387  Error("DeleteArray", "Doing Dump() ...");
5388  ((TVirtualStreamerInfo*)fStreamerInfo->At(i))->Dump();
5389  }
5390  }
5391  }
5392  } else {
5393  // The loaded class version is not the same as the version of the code
5394  // which was used to allocate this array. The best we can do is use
5395  // the TVirtualStreamerInfo to try to free up some of the allocated memory.
5396  Error("DeleteArray", "Loaded class version %d is not registered for addr %p", fClassVersion, p);
5397 
5398 
5399 
5400 #if 0
5401  TVirtualStreamerInfo* si = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) fStreamerInfo->At(objVer);
5402  if (si) {
5403  si->DeleteArray(ary, dtorOnly);
5404  } else {
5405  Error("DeleteArray", "No streamer info available for class '%s' version %d at address %p, cannot destruct object!", GetName(), objVer, ary);
5406  Error("DeleteArray", "length of fStreamerInfo is %d", fStreamerInfo->GetSize());
5407  Int_t i = fStreamerInfo->LowerBound();
5408  for (Int_t v = 0; v < fStreamerInfo->GetSize(); ++v, ++i) {
5409  Error("DeleteArray", "fStreamerInfo->At(%d): %p", v, fStreamerInfo->At(i));
5410  if (fStreamerInfo->At(i)) {
5411  // Print some debugging info.
5412  Error("DeleteArray", "Doing Dump() ...");
5413  ((TVirtualStreamerInfo*)fStreamerInfo->At(i))->Dump();
5414  }
5415  }
5416  }
5417 #endif
5418 
5419 
5420  }
5421 
5422  // Deregister the object for special handling in the destructor.
5423  if (inRepo && verFound && p) {
5424  UnregisterAddressInRepository("TClass::DeleteArray",p,this);
5425  }
5426  } else {
5427  Error("DeleteArray", "This cannot happen! (class '%s')", GetName());
5428  }
5429 }

5491 
5492 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5493 /// Load class description from I/O buffer and return class object.
5494 
5495 TClass *TClass::Load(TBuffer &b)
5496 {
5497  UInt_t maxsize = 256;
5498  char *s = new char[maxsize];
5499 
5500  Int_t pos = b.Length();
5501 
5502  b.ReadString(s, maxsize); // Reads at most maxsize - 1 characters, plus null at end.
5503  while (strlen(s) == (maxsize - 1)) {
5504  // The classname is too large, try again with a large buffer.
5505  b.SetBufferOffset(pos);
5506  maxsize = 2*maxsize;
5507  delete [] s;
5508  s = new char[maxsize];
5509  b.ReadString(s, maxsize); // Reads at most maxsize - 1 characters, plus null at end.
5510  }
5511 
5512  TClass *cl = TClass::GetClass(s, kTRUE);
5513  if (!cl)
5514  ::Error("TClass::Load", "dictionary of class %s not found", s);
5515 
5516  delete [] s;
5517  return cl;
5518 }
5519 
5520 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5521 /// Helper function used by TClass::GetClass().
5522 /// This function attempts to load the dictionary for 'classname'
5523 /// either from the TClassTable or from the list of generator.
5524 /// If silent is 'true', do not warn about missing dictionary for the class.
5525 /// (typically used for class that are used only for transient members)
5526 ///
5527 /// The 'requestedname' is expected to be already normalized.
5528 
5529 TClass *TClass::LoadClass(const char *requestedname, Bool_t silent)
5530 {
5531  // This function does not (and should not) attempt to check in the
5532  // list of loaded classes or in the typedef.
5533 
5534  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5535 
5536  TClass *result = LoadClassDefault(requestedname, silent);
5537 
5538  if (result) return result;
5539  else return LoadClassCustom(requestedname,silent);
5540 }
5541 
5542 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5543 /// Helper function used by TClass::GetClass().
5544 /// This function attempts to load the dictionary for 'classname' from
5545 /// the TClassTable or the autoloader.
5546 /// If silent is 'true', do not warn about missing dictionary for the class.
5547 /// (typically used for class that are used only for transient members)
5548 ///
5549 /// The 'requestedname' is expected to be already normalized.
5550 
5551 TClass *TClass::LoadClassDefault(const char *requestedname, Bool_t /* silent */)
5552 {
5553  // This function does not (and should not) attempt to check in the
5554  // list of loaded classes or in the typedef.
5555 
5556  DictFuncPtr_t dict = TClassTable::GetDictNorm(requestedname);
5557 
5558  if (!dict) {
5559  if (gInterpreter->AutoLoad(requestedname,kTRUE)) {
5560  dict = TClassTable::GetDictNorm(requestedname);
5561  }
5562  }
5563 
5564  if (dict) {
5565  TClass *ncl = (dict)();
5566  if (ncl) ncl->PostLoadCheck();
5567  return ncl;
5568  }
5569  return 0;
5570 }
5571 
5572 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5573 /// Helper function used by TClass::GetClass().
5574 /// This function attempts to load the dictionary for 'classname'
5575 /// from the list of generator.
5576 /// If silent is 'true', do not warn about missing dictionary for the class.
5577 /// (typically used for class that are used only for transient members)
5578 ///
5579 /// The 'requestedname' is expected to be already normalized.
5580 
5581 TClass *TClass::LoadClassCustom(const char *requestedname, Bool_t silent)
5582 {
5583  // This function does not (and should not) attempt to check in the
5584  // list of loaded classes or in the typedef.
5585 
5586  TIter next(gROOT->GetListOfClassGenerators());
5587  TClassGenerator *gen;
5588  while ((gen = (TClassGenerator*) next())) {
5589  TClass *cl = gen->GetClass(requestedname, kTRUE, silent);
5590  if (cl) {
5591  cl->PostLoadCheck();
5592  return cl;
5593  }
5594  }
5595  return 0;
5596 }
5597 
5598 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5599 /// Try to load the ClassInfo if available. This function may require parsing
5600 /// the header file and/or loading data from the clang pcm. If further calls to
5601 /// this function cannot affect the value of fClassInfo, fCanLoadClassInfo is set
5602 /// to false.
5603 
5604 void TClass::LoadClassInfo() const
5605 {
5606  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5607 
5608  // Return if another thread already loaded the info
5609  // while we were waiting for the lock
5610  if (!fCanLoadClassInfo)
5611  return;
5612 
5613  bool autoParse = !gInterpreter->IsAutoParsingSuspended();
5614 
5615  if (autoParse)
5616  gInterpreter->AutoParse(GetName());
5617 
5618  if (!fClassInfo)
5619  gInterpreter->SetClassInfo(const_cast<TClass *>(this));
5620 
5621  if (autoParse && !fClassInfo) {
5622  if (fImplFileLine == -1 && fClassVersion == 0) {
5623  // We have a 'transient' class with a ClassDefInline and apparently no interpreter
5624  // information. Since it is transient, it is more than likely that the lack
5625  // will be harmles.
5626  } else {
5627  ::Error("TClass::LoadClassInfo", "no interpreter information for class %s is available"
5628  " even though it has a TClass initialization routine.",
5629  fName.Data());
5630  }
5631  return;
5632  }
5633 
5634  fCanLoadClassInfo = false;
5635 }

5732 
5733 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5734 /// Do the initialization that can only be done after the CINT dictionary has
5735 /// been fully populated and can not be delayed efficiently.
5736 
5737 void TClass::PostLoadCheck()
5738 {
5739  // In the case of a Foreign class (loaded class without a Streamer function)
5740  // we reset fClassVersion to be -1 so that the current TVirtualStreamerInfo will not
5741  // be confused with a previously loaded streamerInfo.
5742 
5743  if (IsLoaded() && HasInterpreterInfo() && fClassVersion==1 /*&& fStreamerInfo
5744  && fStreamerInfo->At(1)*/ && IsForeign() )
5745  {
5746  SetClassVersion(-1);
5747  }
5748  // Note: We are careful to check the class version first because checking
5749  // for foreign can trigger an AutoParse.
5750  else if (IsLoaded() && HasDataMemberInfo() && fStreamerInfo && ((fClassVersion > 1) || !IsForeign()))
5751  {
5752  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5753 
5754  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)(fStreamerInfo->At(fClassVersion));
5755  // Here we need to check whether this TVirtualStreamerInfo (which presumably has been
5756  // loaded from a file) is consistent with the definition in the library we just loaded.
5757  // BuildCheck is not appropriate here since it check a streamerinfo against the
5758  // 'current streamerinfo' which, at time point, would be the same as 'info'!
5759  if (info && GetListOfDataMembers() && !GetCollectionProxy()
5760  && (info->GetCheckSum()!=GetCheckSum() && !info->CompareContent(this,0,kFALSE,kFALSE, 0) && !(MatchLegacyCheckSum(info->GetCheckSum()))))
5761  {
5762  Bool_t warn = ! TestBit(kWarned);
5763  if (warn && info->GetOldVersion()<=2) {
5764  // Names of STL base classes was modified in vers==3. Allocators removed
5765  //
5766  TIter nextBC(GetListOfBases());
5767  TBaseClass *bc;
5768  while ((bc=(TBaseClass*)nextBC()))
5769  {if (TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(bc->GetName())) warn = kFALSE;}
5770  }
5771 
5772  if (warn) {
5773  if (info->GetOnFileClassVersion()==1 && fClassVersion>1) {
5774  Warning("PostLoadCheck","\n\
5775  The class %s transitioned from not having a specified class version\n\
5776  to having a specified class version (the current class version is %d).\n\
5777  However too many different non-versioned layouts of the class have\n\
5778  already been loaded so far. To work around this problem you can\n\
5779  load fewer 'old' file in the same ROOT session or load the C++ library\n\
5780  describing the class %s before opening the files or increase the version\n\
5781  number of the class for example ClassDef(%s,%d).\n\
5782  Do not try to write objects with the current class definition,\n\
5783  the files might not be readable.\n",
5784  GetName(), fClassVersion, GetName(), GetName(), fStreamerInfo->GetLast()+1);
5785  } else {
5786  Warning("PostLoadCheck","\n\
5787  The StreamerInfo version %d for the class %s which was read\n\
5788  from a file previously opened has the same version as the active class\n\
5789  but a different checksum. You should update the version to ClassDef(%s,%d).\n\
5790  Do not try to write objects with the current class definition,\n\
5791  the files will not be readable.\n"
5792  , fClassVersion, GetName(), GetName(), fStreamerInfo->GetLast()+1);
5793  }
5794  info->CompareContent(this,0,kTRUE,kTRUE,0);
5795  SetBit(kWarned);
5796  }
5797  }
5798  }
5799 }
5800 
5801 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5802 /// Set TObject::fBits and fStreamerType to cache information about the
5803 /// class. The bits are
5804 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
5805 /// kIsTObject : the class inherits from TObject
5806 /// kStartWithTObject: TObject is the left-most class in the inheritance tree
5807 /// kIsForeign : the class doe not have a Streamer method
5808 /// ~~~
5809 /// The value of fStreamerType are
5810 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
5811 /// kTObject : the class inherits from TObject
5812 /// kForeign : the class does not have a Streamer method
5813 /// kInstrumented: the class does have a Streamer method
5814 /// kExternal: the class has a free standing way of streaming itself
5815 /// kEmulatedStreamer: the class is missing its shared library.
5816 /// ~~~
5817 
5818 Long_t TClass::Property() const
5819 {
5820  // Check if we can return without taking the lock,
5821  // this is valid since fProperty is atomic and set as
5822  // the last operation before return.
5823  if (fProperty!=(-1)) return fProperty;
5824 
5825  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5826 
5827  // Check if another thread set fProperty while we
5828  // were waiting.
5829  if (fProperty!=(-1)) return fProperty;
5830 
5831  // Avoid asking about the class when it is still building
5832  if (TestBit(kLoading)) return fProperty;
5833 
5834  // When called via TMapFile (e.g. Update()) make sure that the dictionary
5835  // gets allocated on the heap and not in the mapped file.
5836  TMmallocDescTemp setreset;
5837 
5838  TClass *kl = const_cast<TClass*>(this);
5839 
5840  kl->fStreamerType = TClass::kDefault;
5841  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerDefault;
5842 
5843  if (InheritsFrom(TObject::Class())) {
5844  kl->SetBit(kIsTObject);
5845 
5846  // Is it DIRECT inheritance from TObject?
5847  Int_t delta = kl->GetBaseClassOffsetRecurse(TObject::Class());
5848  if (delta==0) kl->SetBit(kStartWithTObject);
5849 
5850  kl->fStreamerType = kTObject;
5851  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerTObject;
5852  }
5853 
5854  if (HasInterpreterInfo()) {
5855 
5856  // This code used to use ClassInfo_Has|IsValidMethod but since v6
5857  // they return true if the routine is defined in the class or any of
5858  // its parent. We explicitly want to know whether the function is
5859  // defined locally.
5860  if (!const_cast<TClass*>(this)->GetClassMethodWithPrototype("Streamer","TBuffer&",kFALSE)) {
5861 
5862  kl->SetBit(kIsForeign);
5863  kl->fStreamerType = kForeign;
5864  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerStreamerInfo;
5865 
5866  } else if ( kl->fStreamerType == TClass::kDefault ) {
5867  if (kl->fConvStreamerFunc) {
5868  kl->fStreamerType = kInstrumented;
5869  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::ConvStreamerInstrumented;
5870  } else if (kl->fStreamerFunc) {
5871  kl->fStreamerType = kInstrumented;
5872  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerInstrumented;
5873  } else {
5874  // We have an automatic streamer using the StreamerInfo .. no need to go through the
5875  // Streamer method function itself.
5876  kl->fStreamerType = kInstrumented;
5877  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerStreamerInfo;
5878  }
5879  }
5880 
5881  if (fStreamer) {
5882  kl->fStreamerType = kExternal;
5883  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerExternal;
5884  }
5885 
5886  if (const_cast<TClass *>(this)->GetClassMethodWithPrototype("Hash", "", kTRUE)) {
5887  kl->SetBit(kHasLocalHashMember);
5888  }
5889 
5890  if (GetClassInfo()) {
5891  // In the case where the TClass for one of ROOT's core class
5892  // (eg TClonesArray for map<int,TClonesArray*>) is requested
5893  // during the execution of rootcling, we could end up in a situation
5894  // where we should have the information (since TClonesArray has
5895  // a dictionary as part of libCore) but do not because the user
5896  // only include a forward declaration of TClonesArray and we do not
5897  // forcefully load the header file either (because the autoparsing
5898  // is intentionally disabled).
5899  kl->fClassProperty = gCling->ClassInfo_ClassProperty(fClassInfo);
5900  // Must set this last since other threads may read fProperty
5901  // and think all test bits have been properly set.
5902  kl->fProperty = gCling->ClassInfo_Property(fClassInfo);
5903  }
5904  } else {
5905 
5906  if (fStreamer) {
5907  kl->fStreamerType = kExternal;
5908  kl->fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerExternal;
5909  }
5910 
5911  kl->fStreamerType |= kEmulatedStreamer;
5912  kl->SetStreamerImpl();
5913  // fProperty was *not* set so that it can be forced to be recalculated
5914  // next time.
5915  return 0;
5916  }
5917 
5918  return fProperty;
5919 }
5920 
5921 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5922 /// Internal routine to set calculate the class properties that can only be
5923 /// known at run-time, for example whether the Hash member function and the
5924 /// destructor are consistent.
5925 
5926 void TClass::SetRuntimeProperties()
5927 {
5928  // For now, no need to lock this routines as fRuntimeProperties is
5929  // the only atomic set here and this is done at the end
5930  // and there is no downside if the execution is done twice.
5931 
5932  // Note SetRuntimeProperties is set to const as it is technically
5933  // thread-safe.
5934 
5935  UChar_t properties = static_cast<UChar_t>(ERuntimeProperties::kSet);
5936 
5937  if (ROOT::Internal::TCheckHashRecursiveRemoveConsistency::Check(*this))
5938  properties |= static_cast<UChar_t>(ERuntimeProperties::kConsistentHash);
5939 
5940  const_cast<TClass *>(this)->fRuntimeProperties = properties;
5941 }
5942 
5943 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5944 /// Internal routine to set fStreamerImpl based on the value of
5945 /// fStreamerType.
5946 
5947 void TClass::SetStreamerImpl()
5948 {
5949  switch (fStreamerType) {
5950  case kTObject: fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerTObject; break;
5951  case kForeign: fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerStreamerInfo; break;
5952  case kExternal: fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerExternal; break;
5953  case kInstrumented: {
5954  if (fConvStreamerFunc) fStreamerImpl = &TClass::ConvStreamerInstrumented;
5955  else if (fStreamerFunc) fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerInstrumented;
5956  else fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerStreamerInfo;
5957  break;
5958  }
5959 
5960  case kEmulatedStreamer: // intentional fall through
5961  case kForeign|kEmulatedStreamer: // intentional fall through
5962  case kInstrumented|kEmulatedStreamer: fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerStreamerInfo; break;
5963  case kExternal|kEmulatedStreamer: fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerExternal; break;
5964  case kTObject|kEmulatedStreamer: fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerTObjectEmulated; break;
5965  case TClass::kDefault: fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerDefault; break;
5966  default:
5967  Error("SetStreamerImpl","Unexpected value of fStreamerType: %d",fStreamerType);
5968  }
5969 }

5971 
5972 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5973 /// Create the collection proxy object (and the streamer object) from
5974 /// using the information in the TCollectionProxyInfo.
5975 
5976 void TClass::SetCollectionProxy(const ROOT::Detail::TCollectionProxyInfo &info)
5977 {
5978  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5979 
5980  delete fCollectionProxy;
5981 
5982  // We can not use GetStreamerInfo() instead of TVirtualStreamerInfo::Factory()
5983  // because GetStreamerInfo call TStreamerInfo::Build which need to have fCollectionProxy
5984  // set correctly.
5985 
5986  TVirtualCollectionProxy *p = TVirtualStreamerInfo::Factory()->GenExplicitProxy(info,this);
5987  fCollectionProxy = p;
5988 
5989  AdoptStreamer(TVirtualStreamerInfo::Factory()->GenExplicitClassStreamer(info,this));
5990 
5991  if (fCollectionProxy && !fSchemaRules) {
5992  // Numeric Collections have implicit conversions:
5993  GetSchemaRules(kTRUE);
5994  }
5995  fCanSplit = -1;
5996 }

5998 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5999 /// Change (i.e. set) the title of the TNamed.
6000 
6001 void TClass::SetContextMenuTitle(const char *title)
6002 {
6003  fContextMenuTitle = title;
6004 }
6005 
6006 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6007 /// This function installs a global IsA function for this class.
6008 /// The global IsA function will be used if there is no local IsA function (fIsA)
6009 ///
6010 /// A global IsA function has the signature:
6011 ///
6012 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6013 /// TClass *func( TClass *cl, const void *obj);
6014 /// ~~~
6015 ///
6016 /// 'cl' is a pointer to the TClass object that corresponds to the
6017 /// 'pointer type' used to retrieve the value 'obj'
6018 ///
6019 /// For example with:
6020 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6021 /// TNamed * m = new TNamed("example","test");
6022 /// TObject* o = m
6023 /// ~~~
6024 /// and
6025 /// the global IsA function would be called with TObject::Class() as
6026 /// the first parameter and the exact numerical value in the pointer
6027 /// 'o'.
6028 ///
6029 /// In other word, inside the global IsA function. it is safe to C-style
6030 /// cast the value of 'obj' into a pointer to the class described by 'cl'.
6031 
6032 void TClass::SetGlobalIsA(IsAGlobalFunc_t func)
6033 {
6034  fGlobalIsA = func;
6035 }
6036 
6037 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6038 /// Call this method to indicate that the shared library containing this
6039 /// class's code has been removed (unloaded) from the process's memory
6040 
6041 void TClass::SetUnloaded()
6042 {
6043  if (TestBit(kUnloaded) && !TestBit(kUnloading)) {
6044  // Don't redo the work.
6045  return;
6046  }
6047  SetBit(kUnloading);
6048 
6049  //R__ASSERT(fState == kLoaded);
6050  if (fState != kLoaded) {
6051  Fatal("SetUnloaded","The TClass for %s is being unloaded when in state %d\n",
6052  GetName(),(int)fState);
6053  }
6054 
6055  // Make sure SetClassInfo, re-calculated the state.
6056  fState = kForwardDeclared;
6057 
6058  delete fIsA; fIsA = 0;
6059  // Disable the autoloader while calling SetClassInfo, to prevent
6060  // the library from being reloaded!
6061  {
6062  TInterpreter::SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoloadOff(gInterpreter);
6063  TInterpreter::SuspendAutoParsing autoParseRaii(gCling);
6064  gInterpreter->SetClassInfo(this,kTRUE);
6065  }
6066  fDeclFileName = 0;
6067  fDeclFileLine = 0;
6068  fImplFileName = 0;
6069  fImplFileLine = 0;
6070  fTypeInfo = 0;
6071 
6072  if (fMethod.load()) {
6073  (*fMethod).Unload();
6074  }
6075  if (fData) {
6076  fData->Unload();
6077  }
6078  if (fEnums.load()) {
6079  (*fEnums).Unload();
6080  }
6081 
6082  if (fState <= kForwardDeclared && fStreamerInfo->GetEntries() != 0) {
6083  fState = kEmulated;
6084  }
6085 
6086  ResetBit(kUnloading);
6087  SetBit(kUnloaded);
6088 }
6089

6217 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6218 /// Return true if the checksum passed as argument is one of the checksum
6219 /// value produced by the older checksum calculation algorithm.
6220 
6221 Bool_t TClass::MatchLegacyCheckSum(UInt_t checksum) const
6222 {
6223  for(UInt_t i = 1; i < kLatestCheckSum; ++i) {
6224  if ( checksum == GetCheckSum( (ECheckSum) i ) ) return kTRUE;
6225  }
6226  return kFALSE;
6227 }
6228 
6229 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6230 /// Call GetCheckSum with validity check.
6231 
6232 UInt_t TClass::GetCheckSum(ECheckSum code) const
6233 {
6234  bool isvalid;
6235  return GetCheckSum(code,isvalid);
6236 }
6237 
6238 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6239 /// Return GetCheckSum(kCurrentCheckSum,isvalid);
6240 
6241 UInt_t TClass::GetCheckSum(Bool_t &isvalid) const
6242 {
6243  return GetCheckSum(kCurrentCheckSum,isvalid);
6244 }
6245 
6246 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6247 /// Compute and/or return the class check sum.
6248 ///
6249 /// isvalid is set to false, if the function is unable to calculate the
6250 /// checksum.
6251 ///
6252 /// The class ckecksum is used by the automatic schema evolution algorithm
6253 /// to uniquely identify a class version.
6254 /// The check sum is built from the names/types of base classes and
6255 /// data members.
6256 /// Original algorithm from Victor Perevovchikov (perev@bnl.gov).
6257 ///
6258 /// The valid range of code is determined by ECheckSum.
6259 ///
6260 /// - kNoEnum: data members of type enum are not counted in the checksum
6261 /// - kNoRange: return the checksum of data members and base classes, not including the ranges and array size found in comments.
6262 /// - kWithTypeDef: use the sugared type name in the calculation.
6263 ///
6264 /// This is needed for backward compatibility.
6265 ///
6266 /// WARNING: this function must be kept in sync with TStreamerInfo::GetCheckSum.
6267 /// They are both used to handle backward compatibility and should both return the same values.
6268 /// TStreamerInfo uses the information in TStreamerElement while TClass uses the information
6269 /// from TClass::GetListOfBases and TClass::GetListOfDataMembers.
6270 
6271 UInt_t TClass::GetCheckSum(ECheckSum code, Bool_t &isvalid) const
6272 {
6273  // fCheckSum is an atomic variable. Also once it has
6274  // transition from a zero Value it never changes. If two
6275  // thread reach past this if statement and calculated the
6276  // 'kLastestCheckSum', they will by definition obtain the
6277  // same value, so technically we could simply have:
6278  // if (fCheckSum && code == kCurrentCheckSum) return fCheckSum;
6279  // However save a little bit of barrier time by calling load()
6280  // only once.
6281 
6282  isvalid = kTRUE;
6283 
6284  UInt_t currentChecksum = fCheckSum.load();
6285  if (currentChecksum && code == kCurrentCheckSum) return currentChecksum;
6286 
6287  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6288 
6289  // kCurrentCheckSum (0) is the default parameter value and should be kept
6290  // for backward compatibility, too be able to use the inequality checks,
6291  // we need to set the code to the largest value.
6292  if (code == kCurrentCheckSum) code = kLatestCheckSum;
6293 
6294  UInt_t id = 0;
6295 
6296  int il;
6297  TString name = GetName();
6298  TString type;
6299  il = name.Length();
6300  for (int i=0; i<il; i++) id = id*3+name[i];
6301 
6302  TList *tlb = ((TClass*)this)->GetListOfBases();
6303  if (tlb && !GetCollectionProxy()) { // Loop over bases if not a proxied collection
6304 
6305  TIter nextBase(tlb);
6306 
6307  TBaseClass *tbc=0;
6308  while((tbc=(TBaseClass*)nextBase())) {
6309  name = tbc->GetName();
6310  Bool_t isSTL = TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(name);
6311  if (isSTL)
6312  name = TClassEdit::ShortType( name, TClassEdit::kDropStlDefault );
6313  il = name.Length();
6314  for (int i=0; i<il; i++) id = id*3+name[i];
6315  if (code > kNoBaseCheckSum && !isSTL) {
6316  if (tbc->GetClassPointer() == 0) {
6317  Error("GetCheckSum","Calculating the checksum for (%s) requires the base class (%s) meta information to be available!",
6318  GetName(),tbc->GetName());
6319  isvalid = kFALSE;
6320  return 0;
6321  } else
6322  id = id*3 + tbc->GetClassPointer()->GetCheckSum();
6323  }
6324  }/*EndBaseLoop*/
6325  }
6326  TList *tlm = ((TClass*)this)->GetListOfDataMembers();
6327  if (tlm) { // Loop over members
6328  TIter nextMemb(tlm);
6329  TDataMember *tdm=0;
6330  Long_t prop = 0;
6331  while((tdm=(TDataMember*)nextMemb())) {
6332  if (!tdm->IsPersistent()) continue;
6333  // combine properties
6334  prop = (tdm->Property());
6335  TDataType* tdt = tdm->GetDataType();
6336  if (tdt) prop |= tdt->Property();
6337 
6338  if ( prop&kIsStatic) continue;
6339  name = tdm->GetName(); il = name.Length();
6340  if ( (code > kNoEnum) && code != kReflex && code != kReflexNoComment && prop&kIsEnum)
6341  id = id*3 + 1;
6342 
6343  int i;
6344  for (i=0; i<il; i++) id = id*3+name[i];
6345 
6346  if (code > kWithTypeDef || code == kReflexNoComment) {
6347  type = tdm->GetTrueTypeName();
6348  // GetTrueTypeName uses GetFullyQualifiedName which already drops
6349  // the default template parameter, so we no longer need to do this.
6350  //if (TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(type))
6351  // type = TClassEdit::ShortType( type, TClassEdit::kDropStlDefault );
6352  if (code == kReflex || code == kReflexNoComment) {
6353  if (prop&kIsEnum) {
6354  type = "int";
6355  } else {
6356  type.ReplaceAll("ULong64_t","unsigned long long");
6357  type.ReplaceAll("Long64_t","long long");
6358  type.ReplaceAll("<signed char","<char");
6359  type.ReplaceAll(",signed char",",char");
6360  if (type=="signed char") type = "char";
6361  }
6362  }
6363  } else {
6364  type = tdm->GetFullTypeName();
6365  // GetFullTypeName uses GetFullyQualifiedName which already drops
6366  // the default template parameter, so we no longer need to do this.
6367  //if (TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(type))
6368  // type = TClassEdit::ShortType( type, TClassEdit::kDropStlDefault );
6369  }
6370 
6371  il = type.Length();
6372  for (i=0; i<il; i++) id = id*3+type[i];
6373 
6374  int dim = tdm->GetArrayDim();
6375  if (prop&kIsArray) {
6376  for (int ii=0;ii<dim;ii++) id = id*3+tdm->GetMaxIndex(ii);
6377  }
6378  if (code > kNoRange) {
6379  const char *left;
6380  if (code > TClass::kNoRangeCheck)
6381  left = TVirtualStreamerInfo::GetElementCounterStart(tdm->GetTitle());
6382  else
6383  left = strstr(tdm->GetTitle(),"[");
6384  if (left) {
6385  const char *right = strstr(left,"]");
6386  if (right) {
6387  ++left;
6388  while (left != right) {
6389  id = id*3 + *left;
6390  ++left;
6391  }
6392  }
6393  }
6394  }
6395  }/*EndMembLoop*/
6396  }
6397  // This should be moved to Initialization time however the last time
6398  // we tried this cause problem, in particular in the end-of-process operation.
6399  if (code==kLatestCheckSum) fCheckSum = id;
6400  return id;
6401 }

6405 /// represents a reference.
6406 /// When a new proxy is adopted, the old one is deleted.
6407 
6408 void TClass::AdoptReferenceProxy(TVirtualRefProxy* proxy)
6409 {
6410  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6411 
6412  if ( fRefProxy ) {
6413  fRefProxy->Release();
6414  }
6415  fRefProxy = proxy;
6416  if ( fRefProxy ) {
6417  fRefProxy->SetClass(this);
6418  }
6419  fCanSplit = -1;
6420 }

6441  }

6589 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6590 /// Default streaming in cases where either we have no way to know what to do
6591 /// or if Property() has not yet been called.
6592 
6593 void TClass::StreamerDefault(const TClass* pThis, void *object, TBuffer &b, const TClass *onfile_class)
6594 {
6595  if (pThis->fProperty==(-1)) {
6596  pThis->Property();
6597  }
6598 
6599  // We could get here because after this thread started StreamerDefault
6600  // *and* before check fProperty, another thread might have call Property
6601  // and this fProperty when we read it, is not -1 and fStreamerImpl is
6602  // supposed to be set properly (no longer pointing to the default).
6603  if (pThis->fStreamerImpl.load() == &TClass::StreamerDefault) {
6604  pThis->Fatal("StreamerDefault", "fStreamerImpl not properly initialized (%d)", pThis->fStreamerType);
6605  } else {
6606  (*pThis->fStreamerImpl)(pThis,object,b,onfile_class);
6607  }
6608 }

6610 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6611 /// Adopt a TClassStreamer object. Ownership is transfered to this TClass
6612 /// object.
6613 
6614 void TClass::AdoptStreamer(TClassStreamer *str)
6615 {
6616 // // This code can be used to quickly test the STL Emulation layer
6617 // Int_t k = TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(GetName());
6618 // if (k==1||k==-1) { delete str; return; }
6619 
6620  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6621 
6622  if (fStreamer) delete fStreamer;
6623  if (str) {
6624  fStreamerType = kExternal | ( fStreamerType&kEmulatedStreamer );
6625  fStreamer = str;
6626  fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerExternal;
6627  } else if (fStreamer) {
6628  // Case where there was a custom streamer and it is hereby removed,
6629  // we need to reset fStreamerType
6630  fStreamer = str;
6631  fStreamerType = TClass::kDefault;
6632  if (fProperty != -1) {
6633  fProperty = -1;
6634  Property();
6635  }
6636  }
6637 }
6638 
6639 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6640 /// Set a wrapper/accessor function around this class custom streamer.
6641 
6642 void TClass::SetStreamerFunc(ClassStreamerFunc_t strm)
6643 {
6644  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6645  if (fProperty != -1 && !fConvStreamerFunc &&
6646  ( (fStreamerFunc == 0 && strm != 0) || (fStreamerFunc != 0 && strm == 0) ) )
6647  {
6648  fStreamerFunc = strm;
6649 
6650  // Since initialization has already been done, make sure to tweak it
6651  // for the new state.
6652  if (HasInterpreterInfo() && fStreamerType != kTObject && !fStreamer) {
6653  fStreamerType = kInstrumented;
6654  fStreamerImpl = &TClass::StreamerInstrumented;
6655  }
6656  } else {
6657  fStreamerFunc = strm;
6658  }
6659  fCanSplit = -1;
6660 }

6753 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6754 /// Find the TVirtualStreamerInfo in the StreamerInfos corresponding to checksum
6755 
6756 TVirtualStreamerInfo *TClass::FindStreamerInfo(UInt_t checksum) const
6757 {
6758  TVirtualStreamerInfo *guess = fLastReadInfo;
6759  if (guess && guess->GetCheckSum() == checksum) {
6760  return guess;
6761  } else {
6762  if (fCheckSum == checksum) return GetStreamerInfo();
6763 
6764  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6765  Int_t ninfos = fStreamerInfo->GetEntriesFast()-1;
6766  for (Int_t i=-1;i<ninfos;++i) {
6767  // TClass::fStreamerInfos has a lower bound not equal to 0,
6768  // so we have to use At and should not use UncheckedAt
6769  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)fStreamerInfo->UncheckedAt(i);
6770  if (info && info->GetCheckSum() == checksum) {
6771  // R__ASSERT(i==info->GetClassVersion() || (i==-1&&info->GetClassVersion()==1));
6772  info->BuildOld();
6773  if (info->IsCompiled()) fLastReadInfo = info;
6774  return info;
6775  }
6776  }
6777  return 0;
6778  }
6779 }
6780 
6781 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6782 /// Find the TVirtualStreamerInfo in the StreamerInfos corresponding to checksum
6783 
6784 TVirtualStreamerInfo *TClass::FindStreamerInfo(TObjArray* arr, UInt_t checksum) const
6785 {
6786  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6787  Int_t ninfos = arr->GetEntriesFast()-1;
6788  for (Int_t i=-1;i<ninfos;i++) {
6789  // TClass::fStreamerInfos has a lower bound not equal to 0,
6790  // so we have to use At and should not use UncheckedAt
6791  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)arr->UncheckedAt(i);
6792  if (!info) continue;
6793  if (info->GetCheckSum() == checksum) {
6794  R__ASSERT(i==info->GetClassVersion() || (i==-1&&info->GetClassVersion()==1));
6795  return info;
6796  }
6797  }
6798  return 0;
6799 }

6801 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6802 /// Return a Conversion StreamerInfo from the class 'classname' for version number 'version' to this class, if any.
6803 
6804 TVirtualStreamerInfo *TClass::GetConversionStreamerInfo( const char* classname, Int_t version ) const
6805 {
6806  TClass *cl = TClass::GetClass( classname );
6807  if( !cl )
6808  return 0;
6809  return GetConversionStreamerInfo( cl, version );
6810 }
6811 
6812 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6813 /// Return a Conversion StreamerInfo from the class represented by cl for version number 'version' to this class, if any.
6814 
6815 TVirtualStreamerInfo *TClass::GetConversionStreamerInfo( const TClass* cl, Int_t version ) const
6816 {
6817  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6818  // Check if the classname was specified correctly
6819  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6820 
6821  if( !cl )
6822  return 0;
6823 
6824  if( cl == this )
6825  return GetStreamerInfo( version );
6826 
6827  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6828  // Check if we already have it
6829  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6830 
6831  TObjArray* arr = 0;
6832  if (fConversionStreamerInfo.load()) {
6833  std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>::iterator it;
6834  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6835 
6836  it = (*fConversionStreamerInfo).find( cl->GetName() );
6837 
6838  if( it != (*fConversionStreamerInfo).end() ) {
6839  arr = it->second;
6840  }
6841 
6842  if( arr && version > -1 && version < arr->GetSize() && arr->At( version ) )
6843  return (TVirtualStreamerInfo*) arr->At( version );
6844  }
6845 
6846  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6847 
6848  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6849  // We don't have the streamer info so find it in other class
6850  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6851 
6852  const TObjArray *clSI = cl->GetStreamerInfos();
6853  TVirtualStreamerInfo* info = 0;
6854  if( version >= -1 && version < clSI->GetSize() )
6855  info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)clSI->At( version );
6856 
6857  if (!info && cl->GetCollectionProxy()) {
6858  info = cl->GetStreamerInfo(); // instantiate the StreamerInfo for STL collections.
6859  }
6860 
6861  if( !info )
6862  return 0;
6863 
6864  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6865  // We have the right info so we need to clone it to create new object with
6866  // non artificial streamer elements and we should build it for current class
6867  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6868 
6869  info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)info->Clone();
6870 
6871  if( !info->BuildFor( this ) ) {
6872  delete info;
6873  return 0;
6874  }
6875 
6876  if (!info->IsCompiled()) {
6877  // Streamer info has not been compiled, but exists.
6878  // Therefore it was read in from a file and we have to do schema evolution?
6879  // Or it didn't have a dictionary before, but does now?
6880  info->BuildOld();
6881  }
6882 
6883  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6884  // Cache this streamer info
6885  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6886 
6887  if (!arr) {
6888  arr = new TObjArray(version+10, -1);
6889  if (!fConversionStreamerInfo.load()) {
6890  fConversionStreamerInfo = new std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>();
6891  }
6892  (*fConversionStreamerInfo)[cl->GetName()] = arr;
6893  }
6894  arr->AddAtAndExpand( info, info->GetClassVersion() );
6895  return info;
6896 }
6897 
6898 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6899 /// Return a Conversion StreamerInfo from the class 'classname' for the layout represented by 'checksum' to this class, if any.
6900 
6901 TVirtualStreamerInfo *TClass::FindConversionStreamerInfo( const char* classname, UInt_t checksum ) const
6902 {
6903  TClass *cl = TClass::GetClass( classname );
6904  if( !cl )
6905  return 0;
6906  return FindConversionStreamerInfo( cl, checksum );
6907 }
6908 
6909 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6910 /// Return a Conversion StreamerInfo from the class represented by cl for the layout represented by 'checksum' to this class, if any.
6911 
6912 TVirtualStreamerInfo *TClass::FindConversionStreamerInfo( const TClass* cl, UInt_t checksum ) const
6913 {
6914  //---------------------------------------------------------------------------
6915  // Check if the classname was specified correctly
6916  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6917 
6918  if( !cl )
6919  return 0;
6920 
6921  if( cl == this )
6922  return FindStreamerInfo( checksum );
6923 
6924  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6925  // Check if we already have it
6926  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6927 
6928  TObjArray* arr = 0;
6929  TVirtualStreamerInfo* info = 0;
6930  if (fConversionStreamerInfo.load()) {
6931  std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>::iterator it;
6932 
6933  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6934 
6935  it = (*fConversionStreamerInfo).find( cl->GetName() );
6936 
6937  if( it != (*fConversionStreamerInfo).end() ) {
6938  arr = it->second;
6939  }
6940  if (arr) {
6941  info = FindStreamerInfo( arr, checksum );
6942  }
6943  }
6944 
6945  if( info )
6946  return info;
6947 
6948  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6949 
6950  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6951  // Get it from the foreign class
6952  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6953 
6954  info = cl->FindStreamerInfo( checksum );
6955 
6956  if( !info )
6957  return 0;
6958 
6959  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6960  // We have the right info so we need to clone it to create new object with
6961  // non artificial streamer elements and we should build it for current class
6962  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6963 
6964  info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)info->Clone();
6965  if( !info->BuildFor( this ) ) {
6966  delete info;
6967  return 0;
6968  }
6969 
6970  if (!info->IsCompiled()) {
6971  // Streamer info has not been compiled, but exists.
6972  // Therefore it was read in from a file and we have to do schema evolution?
6973  // Or it didn't have a dictionary before, but does now?
6974  info->BuildOld();
6975  }
6976 
6977  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6978  // Cache this streamer info
6979  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6980 
6981  if (!arr) {
6982  arr = new TObjArray(16, -2);
6983  if (!fConversionStreamerInfo.load()) {
6984  fConversionStreamerInfo = new std::map<std::string, TObjArray*>();
6985  }
6986  (*fConversionStreamerInfo)[cl->GetName()] = arr;
6987  }
6988  arr->AddAtAndExpand( info, info->GetClassVersion() );
6989 
6990  return info;
6991 }

6993 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6994 /// Register the StreamerInfo in the given slot, change the State of the
6995 /// TClass as appropriate.
6996 
6997 void TClass::RegisterStreamerInfo(TVirtualStreamerInfo *info)
6998 {
6999  if (info) {
7000  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
7001  Int_t slot = info->GetClassVersion();
7002  if (fStreamerInfo->GetSize() > (slot-fStreamerInfo->LowerBound())
7003  && fStreamerInfo->At(slot) != 0
7004  && fStreamerInfo->At(slot) != info) {
7005  Error("RegisterStreamerInfo",
7006  "Register StreamerInfo for %s on non-empty slot (%d).",
7007  GetName(),slot);
7008  }
7009  fStreamerInfo->AddAtAndExpand(info, slot);
7010  if (fState <= kForwardDeclared) {
7011  fState = kEmulated;
7012  if (fCheckSum==0 && slot==fClassVersion) fCheckSum = info->GetCheckSum();
7013  }
7014  }
7015 }
7016 
7017 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7018 /// Remove and delete the StreamerInfo in the given slot.
7019 /// Update the slot accordingly.
7020 
7021 void TClass::RemoveStreamerInfo(Int_t slot)
7022 {
7023  if (fStreamerInfo->GetSize() >= slot) {
7024  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
7025  TVirtualStreamerInfo *info = (TVirtualStreamerInfo*)fStreamerInfo->At(slot);
7026  fStreamerInfo->RemoveAt(fClassVersion);
7027  delete info;
7028  if (fState == kEmulated && fStreamerInfo->GetEntries() == 0) {
7029  fState = kForwardDeclared;
7030  }
7031  }
7032 }

7034 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7035 /// Return true is the Hash/RecursiveRemove setup is consistent, i.e. when all
7036 /// classes in the class hierarchy that overload TObject::Hash do call
7037 /// ROOT::CallRecursiveRemoveIfNeeded in their destructor.
7038 /// i.e. it is safe to call the Hash virtual function during the RecursiveRemove operation.
7039 /// This routines is used for a small subset of the class for which we need
7040 /// the answer before gROOT is properly initialized.
7041 
7042 Bool_t ROOT::Internal::HasConsistentHashMember(const char *cname)
7043 {
7044  // Hand selection of correct classes, those classes should be
7045  // cross-checked in testHashRecursiveRemove.cxx
7046  static const char *handVerified[] = {
7047  "TEnvRec", "TDataType", "TObjArray", "TList", "THashList",
7048  "TClass", "TCling", "TInterpreter", "TMethod", "ROOT::Internal::TCheckHashRecursiveRemoveConsistency",
7049  "TCheckHashRecursiveRemoveConsistency", "TGWindow",
7050  "TDirectory", "TDirectoryFile", "TObject", "TH1",
7051  "TQClass", "TGlobal" };
7052 
7053  if (cname && cname[0]) {
7054  for (auto cursor : handVerified) {
7055  if (strcmp(cname, cursor) == 0)
7056  return true;
7057  }
7058  }
7059  return false;
7060 }

7073 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7074 /// Return true if we have access to a constructor useable for I/O. This is
7075 /// typically the default constructor but can also be a constructor specifically
7076 /// marked for I/O (for example a constructor taking a TRootIOCtor* as an
7077 /// argument). In other words, if this routine returns true, TClass::New is
7078 /// guarantee to succeed.
7079 /// To know if the class described by this TClass has a default constructor
7080 /// (public or not), use
7081 /// \code{.cpp}
7082 /// cl->GetProperty() & kClassHasDefaultCtor
7083 /// \code
7084 /// To know if the class described by this TClass has a public default
7085 /// constructor use:
7086 /// \code{.cpp}
7087 /// gInterpreter->ClassInfo_HasDefaultConstructor(aClass->GetClassInfo());
7088 /// \code
7089 
7090 Bool_t TClass::HasDefaultConstructor() const
7091 {
7092 
7093  if (fNew) return kTRUE;
7094 
7095  if (HasInterpreterInfo()) {
7096  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
7097  return gCling->ClassInfo_HasDefaultConstructor(GetClassInfo());
7098  }
7099  if (fCollectionProxy) {
7100  return kTRUE;
7101  }
7102  if (fCurrentInfo.load()) {
7103  // Emulated class, we know how to construct them via the TStreamerInfo
7104  return kTRUE;
7105  }
7106  return kFALSE;
7107 }
